title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Add the other ingredients.
Keep covered in refrigerator overnight before making into biscuits.
Bake at 450°.
This dough keeps well in refrigerator.

title: toffee squares
directions: Mix and spread on cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 325°. While still warm, frost with melted milk chocolate.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cut into squares and enjoy!

title: fruit cocktail pudding
directions: Mix well flour,
sugar,
salt,	soda,
egg, vanilla and fruit cocktail;
put in buttered pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.	Mix brown sugar and nuts.
Put on top.
Bake 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Peel oranges and remove white membrane from sections.
Slice thinly.
Mix with sugar and coconut.
Let stand until needed and add whipped cream.

title: cauliflower puff
directions: Cook cauliflower according to package directions until tender; drain.
Blend until smooth the cauliflower, egg yolks, milk, salt and pepper.
In a medium bowl, beat egg whites until stiff; fold in the cauliflower mixture, scallions and Cheddar cheese.
Spread over bottom of a 9-inch pie plate which has been buttered. Drizzle with melted butter and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° until golden brown and set, about 20 minutes.
Cut into wedges and remove with a wide spatula.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits in 4 1/2 cups salted water. When done, add butter, cheese, eggs and milk. Stir until melted.
Pour into greased casserole and sprinkle buttered bread crumbs on top. Bake 45 minutes or until center is done in a 350° oven.

title: frogmore stew
directions: Place corn, sausage and seasoning in large pot covering corn and sausage with water. Bring to a boil.
Add shrimp and return to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from pot to prevent overcooking shrimp. Serve with butter and cocktail sauce.

title: lemon-snap cookies(30 calories per cookie; lo-cal)
directions: In medium bowl, cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in egg, lemon juice and rind.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add gradually to sugar and shortening.
Mix until smooth.
Refrigerate until firm (about 1 to 2 hours). Preheat oven to 400°.
Roll to 1/8-inch thickness; cut as you wish.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes on lightly greased cookie sheet or until edges are golden brown.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Space about 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown, but still soft.
Yields 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: mexican pizza
directions: In a skillet, brown the ground beef with the onion.
Add the tomato sauce and simmer 15 minutes.
Butter both sides of 3 tortillas and place them in the bottom of a baking dish.
Add meat and sauce mixture to cover and sprinkle with cheese and olives.
Continue layering in this manner until all the meat mixture is used.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until the mixture bubbles.
Serves 6-8 and freezes well.

title: cajun spaghetti
directions: Combine all ingredients except soup, chicken, spaghetti and cheese.
Simmer until green peppers are soft.
Stir in soups and chicken.
Add spaghetti and cheese.
Cool and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: miniature brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line 72 mini-muffin tins with paper baking cups.
Melt butter in a 3-quart saucepan over medium-low heat.
Add chocolate chips and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar and vanilla until blended.
Add eggs and stir briskly. Gradually stir in flour, then nuts.
Fill baking cups 3/4 full. Bake 1 sheet at a time, 22 to 24 minutes until pick inserted in center comes out almost clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Store airtight. Brownies freeze well for up to 3 months.

title: paella
directions: Remove shells from shrimp, leaving tails.
Devein by making shallow incision down the back and running under cold water.
Set aside.
Scrub clams and mussels.
Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in a skillet.
Prick sausages with a fork to let out steam and cook in skillet until brown.
Pour off oil; add water to cover sausages.
Cover pan and simmer 5 minutes; set aside.
In a separate skillet, heat 3 tablespoons olive oil.
Mix 1/2 cup flour, 1 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Use to lightly coat chicken. Brown chicken until golden.
Set aside.

title: peanut butter bites(no bake)
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients; press into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and margarine in glass bowl on Low heat in microwave.
Spread hot chocolate mixture over the peanut butter mixture.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into squares, ready to eat.
Refrigerate.

title: indian soup
directions: Melt margarine in pot, then stir in flour.
Then add water, bouillon cubes and veggies.
Heat and serve.

title: light pineapple cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Combine cake mix, pineapple juice, water and egg whites in a large mixing bowl. Blend with mixer on low speed 30 seconds.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Divide batter between pans.
Bake at 350° for 29 to 32 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan.
Combine crushed pineapple and cornstarch in small saucepan.
Blend until smooth.
Heat over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Reduce heat and cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute.
Remove from heat and allow to cool.
Prepare Whipped Cream Frosting.
To assemble cake, place one cake layer on serving plate and spread top with frosting.
Spoon thickened pineapple sauce over frosting.
Top with second cake layer.
Frost sides and top of cake.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: In skillet, put in 2 tablespoons oil. Saute onion, pepper, celery and parsley until soft and done.
Add beef, pork, chicken broth and pepper.
Cook 20 minutes.
In big kettle of rice add sauce and all ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: uncooked chocolate candy
directions: First:
Heat a large pot of water to boiling.
Wash and dry fresh picked okra.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Blanch the slices in the boiling water for 2 to 3 minutes.
Cool them thoroughly in ice water and pat dry.
Roll the slices in seasoned corn meal until they are well coated.
Spread a single layer on cookie sheet; freeze overnight, or until slices are solid.
Bag the slices; return them to the freezer until ready to cook.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter in skillet and cook green pepper.
Add flour and stir.
Add milk, mushrooms, soups, cheddar cheese, chicken and cooked spaghetti.
Pour into 13x9-inch casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 mins.

title: beef salad
directions: In salad bowl, combine beef, potatoes and tomatoes.
In a mixing bowl, combine salt, pepper, vinegar, oil and tarragon; mix well.
Pour over salad.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Garnish with egg slices.
Serves 4.

title: shaker bean soup
directions: Sort and rinse beans.
Place in a Dutch oven or soup kettle; cover with water and bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 1 hour.
Drain beans and discard liquid.
In the same kettle, place ham bone or hocks, 3 quarts of water and beans. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours or until meat easily falls from the bone.
Remove bones from broth, trim off the meat and discard bones.
Add ham, onion, celery, carrots, salt, pepper and thyme.
Simmer, covered, 1 hour or until beans are tender.
Add tomatoes and brown sugar.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Just before serving, add spinach.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Prepare the first 3 ingredients. Combine the the remaining ingredients.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; rinse in cold water.
Add rest of ingredients. Mix and refrigerate.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Put the uncooked macaroni into a casserole.
Blend soup and milk until smooth and pour over macaroni.
Mix well.
Stir in dried beef and cheese.
(May be made earlier and placed in refrigerator.)
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: spinach wraps
directions: Combine all ingredients (except bacon), mixing well.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts, or a little larger.
Wrap each ball with 1/2 strip of bacon.
Freeze.

title: eddie's corn bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Beat next 3 ingredients together; add to dry mixture.
Bake in greased pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: denny's surprise(muffins)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time.
Mix in applesauce and spices.
Sift together, salt, soda and flour.
Add to applesauce mix and beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in lightly greased miniature muffin pans at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Yields 84 small muffins.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Combine 2 tablespoons juice with mayonnaise, soy sauce and curry.
Combine with remaining ingredients except noodles.
Toss. Add noodles just before serving.

title: wassail
directions: Mix and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: roll sausage and rice dish
directions: Crumble and fry sausage.
Drain.
Cook onion and pepper.
Add to rice, chicken broth, water and sausage.
Mix well.
Cover and bake at 350° until rice is done.

title: maple-pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a cookie sheet.
Combine the pumpkin, maple syrup, egg and vanilla in a blender.
Mix until smooth.
With an electric mixer, cream the butter in a small bowl. Add the creamed butter to the pumpkin mixture.

title: cherry-banana dream pie
directions: Heat fruit, sugar and flour; cook until thick, about 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and add dry jello.
Cool about 10 minutes.
Add pecans, bananas and food coloring.
Pour into cooked pie shells and put into icebox or freezer.
If pies are in freezer, allow 4 to 5 hours to thaw out.
Yields 3 pies.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar, jello, Knox gelatine and water; bring to a boil and boil one minute.
Remove from heat; add cream cheese and stir until dissolved.
Cool.
When it starts to set, stir in apples, celery and nuts.
Fold in whipping cream; let set several hours or overnight.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour in well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and add soup.
Chop shrimp and fold in with cheese and soup.
Chill.
Serve with triscuits or chips.

title: favorite chocolate krispie bars
directions: Mix corn syrup and sugar in large (microwaveable) mixing bowl. Put in microwave oven for 1 1/2 minutes (or until sugar is dissolved).
Add peanut butter to hot syrup.
Pour in Rice Krispies.
Stir thoroughly.

title: easy walnut fudge
directions: In a large saucepan, heat Eagle Brand on medium heat.
Add chocolate chips and stir until melted.
Take off heat and add nuts.
Stir.
Butter glass pan and pour in mixture.
Let chill about 2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding with milk as directed on box.
Stir in sour cream, then fold in Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers and sliced bananas in large container.
Cover with layer of pudding. Repeat.

title: black forest dump cake
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve liquid.
Spread pineapple in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Gently spread pie filling over pineapple. Sprinkle dry cake mix on pie filling; top with pecans.
Combine butter and pineapple juice and drizzle on mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve with Cool Whip.

title: stromboli
directions: Cook beef, onion, pepper and garlic until browned.
Drain and stir in spaghetti sauce.
Cool to room temperature.
On lightly floured surface unroll 1 package crescent rolls.
Pinch perforations together to seal well.
Roll to 11 x 9-inch rectangle.
Arrange 2 slices of cheese in center, spread 1/2 beef mixture to within 1 1/2-inches of edges.
Start at long edge, roll up.
Pinch seam well, place seam down on cookie sheet.
Repeat. Bake at 350° for 30
minutes or until brown.
Let stand for 5 minutes for easier slicing.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put
vegetables
in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle hamburger
on
top	of this.
Put pea juice in tomato soup and pour on top of this.
Dot with butter.
Salt each layer.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 325° in oven.

title: speedy cranberry sauce
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar, water, cranberries and chopped apples.
Boil rapidly until skins of berries pop open, about 5 minutes.
Cool.
Refrigerate until served.
Makes 1 1/4 quarts. Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: tuna-olive macaroni loaf
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add olives, onion, tuna and bread crumbs. Combine with macaroni, cheese sauce and oleo.
Line bottom of pan with aluminum foil.
Turn mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
May be served hot or cold.

title: bradley's shrimp casserole
directions: Saute first 4 ingredients in 4 tablespoons margarine for 5 minutes.
Mix bag of rice with water and add to mixture.
Then mix soup with milk and add to mixture.
Then add shrimp to mixture.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Fix package of Stove Top according to package directions; add 1/4 cup more water.
Parboil zucchini for 5 minutes and drain. Place 1/2 Stove Top mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole and press into bottom of pan.

title: brown rice
directions: Combine both packets of rice, jar of mushrooms and can of broth in a casserole dish.
Place stick of margarine on top and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Stir before serving.

title: cranberry-orange drink
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Chill well and serve in chilled glasses with sprig of mint or twist of orange.

title: scrambled eggs
directions: Crack open egg and put in a mixing bowl.
Add water and beat. Spray a nonstick pan with cooking spray.
Pour eggs into a warm pan and keep mixing with a wooden spoon until dry.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Add 2 cups Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Cover with one can cherry pie filling.
Chill 3 hours in fridge.
Serve.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients 50 strokes by hand.
Pour batter into a 9-inch pie crust pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Let cool for 1 hour.
Spread with topping.

title: 3 bean salad
directions: Drain beans well.
Mix all ingredients.
Put salad mixture in flat dish.
This salad is better if made a day before serving.
It will keep 2 weeks in the refrigerator.

title: sweet and sour slaw
directions: Cut up cabbage, onion and pepper.
Mix.
Put into a covered dish or pan and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: w.w. ii "ham" lunch
directions: Arrange Spam slices in a round cake pan.
Place unbaked rolls on top. Spread preserves over entire arrangement and bake in preheated oven.
Follow instructions on Brown 'N Serve rolls package for oven temperature.
Serve with apricot preserves or preserves of your choice.

title: lemon luck pie
directions: Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip and chopped nuts.

title: little white fruit cakes
directions: Wash and cover raisins with boiling water and simmer 30 minutes.
Drain and dry.
Place into bowl with cherries, pineapple and citron.
Set aside.

title: fruited ham salad
directions: In small mixing bowl combine all ingredients except lettuce and tomato and stir until thoroughly blended.
To serve, line center of serving platter with lettuce leaves and arrange tomato slices along side of platter; top lettuce with ham mixture.
Makes 2 servings.

title: grape salad
directions: Combine the Jell-O and water. Add pineapple and blueberry pie filling, juices included.
Let congeal.

title: lasagna with pepperoni
directions: Oil bottoms of two 9 x 14-inch roasting or cake pans.
Spoon 2/3 cup sauce on bottom of pans.
Place noodles 3 across in pan. Spread a spoonful of sauce over noodles.
(Take note of direction that noodles overlap, all noodle levels should go in the same direction or lasagna will not hold its form.) Dot noodles with Ricotta cheese (1-inch dollops, 3 inches apart).
Between dollops, put a cooked meatball.

title: cocoa kiss cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Combine flour and cocoa.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Add nuts. Beat on low speed until well blended.

Chill dough 1 hour or until firm enough to handle. Heat oven to 375°. Mold scant tablespoon of dough around each unwrapped kiss, covering kiss completely. Shape into balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until almost set.
Cool slightly.
Remove from cookie sheet onto wire rack.
Cool completely.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Salt and pepper chicken to taste.
Put in casserole dish.
Add cream of chicken mushroom soup.
Cook at 350° for approximately 1 hour, then add stuffing and potatoes.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes more.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix Cool Whip, sour cream and pudding all together.
Put in dish.
Add a layer of wafers, then bananas, then another layer of mixture, then wafers and banana until all is used.
Top edge of bowl with wafers.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Place in ice cream freezer container. Fill rest of container with milk.

title: "melt in your mouth" sugar cookies
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Beat until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Chill dough.
Roll into balls and put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press down with fork dipped in sugar. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for approximately 15 minutes. These are delicious!
Good Christmas cookies with green and red sprinkles.
Makes generous amount; depends on size.

title: scalloped broccoli
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix egg, milk and flour together.
Add to butter and onion.
Blend all the rest of ingredients except breadcrumbs and 2 tablespoons of butter (melted).
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle breadcrumbs on top and drizzle with melted butter.

title: makay's microwave meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Distribute evenly in a large ring mold, an especially made-for-microwave round container with spout in center or a 2-quart microproof round casserole with an inverted 6-ounce custard cup in center.
Cook on maximum power a total of 16 minutes, turning the container 1/4 turn after 4 minute intervals.
Let stand at least 5 minutes before serving.
This recipe serves 6 quite generously.
It may be made in advance and frozen for several months.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a boil, stirring constantly until real thick and turns loose from the sides of the pan. As soon as the mixture has cooled enough to handle, take the size you want and roll in your hands into a puppy. Place puppies on paper towels in Tupperware. Change the towels once. We think this is better to make one day and fry the next day. Changing the towels takes out the extra moisture, fries better. Fry in deep fat.

title: plum upside-down cake
directions: Place 1 tablespoon butter in a 9-inch round baking pan.
Put pan in a preheated 350° oven to melt.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with 1/3 cup sugar.
Arrange plum slices in a circular pattern over sugar. Bake for 10 minutes.

title: chicken rotel with pasta
directions: Simmer chicken in lightly salted water until tender, about 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove chicken and skim fat.
Cook vermicelli in broth, drain and set aside.
Reserve broth.

title: sauteed zucchini
directions: Salt zucchini slices; let drain in colander for 1/2 hour.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Melt butter.
Add garlic; cook over low heat for a few minutes.
Add drained zucchini.
Add basil, kosher salt and pepper.
Cover and cook on low for 5 minutes, until liquid evaporates.
Sprinkle cheese over top.

title: bread in a bag
directions: Put yeast, 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar and salt into the bag.
Add margarine and warm water.
Press most of the air out of the bag and seal.
Press and squeeze the bag with hands until dough is mixed.
Open bag and add last 1 1/2 cups flour.
Seal the bag again and keep pressing until the flour is mixed into the dough. Add more flour if dough is sticky.
Unzip the bag and let dough rest for 20 minutes.
Grease loaf pan.
Place dough in pan.
Let the dough rest for 1 hour in a warm place.
(Dough should double in size.)
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake bread for 25 to 30 minutes. Remove bread from pan to cool.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except ketchup, together in a bowl. Spray loaf pan with Pam.
Put ingredients in loaf pan.
Pour ketchup on top for garnish.
Place loaf pan in microwave for 14 minutes at maximum power and let stand for 5 minutes, covered. Place in a 375° oven for 8 minutes to brown, if you don't have a microwave that browns.

title: pizza bubble bread
directions: Sprinkle a greased 12-inch pizza pan with corn meal.
Separate biscuits and cut into 4 pieces.
Place in bowl; add sauce.
Toss to coat.
Arrange pieces on pan in 8-inch circle.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in 400° oven about 15 minutes or until brown.

title: dutch letters
directions: Mix butter and flour.
Stir in water and mix well.
Chill overnight or longer.
Beat almond paste with an electric mixer until smooth; add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and chill. When ready to bake, divide dough and filling into 14 equal parts. Roll 1 section of dough into a 14 x 4-inch strip.
Then take a section of filling and spread it down the center of dough strip. Lap one side of dough over the filling, then the other side and pinch ends shut.
Place on greased cookie sheet with seams on bottom.
Brush tops with beaten egg whites and sprinkle sugar on top.
Prick with fork every 2 inches for steam to escape.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat
oven
to
Grease
and flour an 8 or 9-inch tube pan.
Measure
all
ingredients into a large mixer bowl. Blend 1/2 minute on low speed scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3
minutes on
high
speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Pour into pan. Bake approximately 50 minutes.

title: fried bananas
directions: In a bowl, mix flour, 1/2 cup ice water and egg until smooth. Peel bananas; slice into 1-inch thick slices.
Drop a few into batter (must be well coated).
Fry a few at a time in hot oil (365°) for 1 to 2 minutes.
Drain on paper toweling.

title: crazy crunch
directions: Mix popcorn and nuts on a cookie sheet. Combine sugar, margarine and Karo syrup in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Continue boiling, stirring occasionally, 10 to 15 minutes or until mixture turns a light caramel color. Stir in vanilla. Pour over popcorn and nuts. Mix to coat well. Spread to dry. Break apart and store in tightly covered container.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream together sugar, oleo and Crisco.
Add the 5 egg yolks, one at a time. Dissolve the soda in the buttermilk and set aside. Alternately add milk and soda mixture with flour to the egg mixture. Add nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Beat the eggs
until stiff.
Fold in.
Bake in layers at 325° or bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: orange roughy almondine(microwave)
directions: Place fish into microwavable dish.
Cover with parsley, lime juice, salt and pepper.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave 5 to 6 minutes.
Pour almonds with oleo over the fish to serve.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs; beat after adding one at a time.
Add milk and flavoring.
Beat until smooth.
Add presifted dry ingredients.
Don't overbeat at this stage.
Fold in coconut. Put in Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana split cake
directions: First Layer:
Melt 1 stick of butter or margarine; add graham cracker crumbs.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chocolate cake roll
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Melt butter and pour into cookie sheet.
Add pecans and coconut, then the Eagle Brand milk.
Beat eggs until fluffy and gradually add rest of ingredients.
Pour cake batter over ingredients in cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until top springs back.
Sprinkle cake with powdered sugar and cover with a towel.
Invert cake on towel and remove pan and foil.
Roll cake starting at the short side.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well by hand.
Bake in a long greased pan at 350° for 25 to 40 minutes.

title: bar-b-cups
directions: Brown ground meat.
Drain the grease.
Add sauce.
Press biscuits into cupcake pan.
Shape biscuits into cups.
Put the meat mixture in cups.
Top with cheese.
Bake until brown at 350°.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat until fluffy; then add milk.
Slowly add flour and beat on low speed until batter is smooth.
Pour into tube pan or two loaf pans (greased and well floured).
Bake at 325° (tube pan for 1 1/2 to 2 hours and loaf pans for 45 to 60 minutes).

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Cook tomatoes, onion, salt, pepper and sugar together for 15 minutes.
Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly.
Add tomato mixture to milk mixture, stirring gradually.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and nutmeg.
Add milk (mixture will look like pancake batter).
Use 1 tablespoon melted butter in bottom and on sides of baking dish (medium pan).
Pour batter in baking pan.
Arrange peach slices on top; dot with remaining butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve warm or cold.

title: congealed salad
directions: Put lemon juice in condensed milk; add cherry jello, pineapple, fruit cocktail and Cool Whip.
Mix well and let chill before serving.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on cake.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Melt butter. Add flour, crabmeat and milk. Stir well.
Now add cheese and melt. Add seasoning to taste and serve hot.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place frozen hash browns into 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Pour melted butter over potatoes.
Mix sour cream, cream of chicken soup and cheese.
Pour all into potatoes and mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat.
Add vanilla and coloring and mix.
Sift flour, cocoa, salt and soda together.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in vinegar.
Mix well.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and frost.

title: chocolate chip crunchers
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together in a large bowl.
Then gradually add flour and salt.
Then add corn flakes, oats, chocolate chips and baking soda.
Place teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: man on the moon cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil until foamy.
Combine flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and sugar; add to egg mixture.
Add remaining ingredients, except Topping and mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done.
Remove from oven and spread with Lunar Landing Topping. Cool before cutting.
Yields 1 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) cake.

title: helen's special sugar cookies
directions: Cream together eggs, shortening and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350°.
When cookies are baked, but not brown, take out and put 1/2 of a marshmallow on top of each cookie.
Put back in oven and bake until marshmallow is soft. Remove from oven and flatten marshmallow with finger dipped in water.
Cool and top with the following:

title: apple dumplings
directions: Use favorite 2 crust pie pastry recipe. Divide into number of apples. Roll out.
Place apple in center.
Spoon 1 to 2 tablespoons sugar-cinnamon mixture into the cavity of pared, cored apple.
Dot with butter.
Wrap and seal.
Place in baking dish in a 375° oven.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat
eggs
lightly
with fork.
Stir in other ingredients, saving nuts for last.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken casserole
directions: Place cooked chicken in buttered dish.
Pour soup, sour cream and milk over chicken.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Top with 2 stacks crushed Ritz crackers.
Pour 1 stick melted butter over crackers.
Bake at 350° until hot (30 minutes).

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Parboil chicken breasts; remove skin and tear meat into bite-size pieces, placing in buttered casserole dish.
Prepare stuffing as directed on box; cover chicken with dressing.
Pour soup over it.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
You can substitute other chicken pieces, if desired.

title: fat cakes - 2 doz. doughnuts
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, salt and margarine; set aside. Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add milk mixture.
Add 1 cup flour, beating well by hand.
Add eggs, vanilla and nutmeg. Beat well.
Add remaining flour and beat well until smooth.
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Stir down.

title: crab louie
directions: Combine all.
Chill 4 hours.
Serve on a bed of lettuce. Makes 2 servings.
Can be doubled.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix dates, boiling water and baking soda.
Let stand while mixing other ingredients.

title: violet's punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in warm water and let cool.
Mix orange juice, pineapple juice, lemons and bananas.
Mix in sugar water; put in quart containers in freezer.
When containers are frozen, mix with 2 bottles of 7-Up for each quart.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit to make 2 cups.
Mix pudding and juice and cook like you would regular pudding.
Cool and pour over fruit.
Add cherries for color.

title: gavin's yummy in the tummy jambalaya
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain, but save grease.
Cook onion, celery and green pepper in the bacon fat until onion is tender. Add the tomatoes, garlic powder, cayenne pepper, chili powder and thyme.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add the shrimp, parsley and salt. Cook until shrimp are done.
Serve over the cooked rice.
Garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: southern banana pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir pudding mix into milk in medium saucepan.
Add egg yolks.
Stirring constantly, cook on medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Arrange layer of cookies on bottom and up sides of 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Add layer of banana slices; top with 1/3 of the pudding.
Repeat layers, ending with pudding.
Beat egg whites and salt with electric mixer on high until foamy.
Add in sugar; beat until stiff peaks form.
Spoon onto pudding.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until meringue is a light brown.
Serve warm or chilled.
Makes 8 servings.

title: dump cake(ellen's favorite recipe)
directions: Spread cherry pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top cherries with pineapple.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over pineapple. Pour melted margarine over the dry cake.
Top with coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pecan pie
directions: Place margarine, sugar and syrup in saucepan; bring to boil and cook until mixture coats spoon (just before it spins a thread).
Beat eggs; add salt and vanilla and add syrup mixture to eggs, beating well.
Put into unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean when inserted into pie.

title: chili cornbread
directions: Combine eggs, sour cream, onion and chili corn.
Mix well and add to dry ingredients (cornmeal, flour and baking powder).
Top with cheese.
Cook in iron pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Let butter soften to room temperature. Mix powdered sugar and butter together.
Mix in lemon and vanilla flavorings until blended well.
Slowly add flour to the butter mixture until batter is only slightly sticky. Roll dough into small balls.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press dough out with a fork. Bake cookies at 350° about 7 minutes.
Makes 3 to 5 dozen cookies depending on size.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Heat oven
In ungreased, 9 x 9-inch pan, stir together
flour,
sugar,
2 tablespoons cocoa, salt and baking powder.
Mix
in
milk, oil and vanilla.
Mix until smooth and stir in
nuts.
Spread
evenly
in	pan.
Sprinkle	with brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake 40 minutes.
When
cool,
cut	into squares and top with favorite ice cream.

title: patchwork casserole
directions: Cook and stir in a large skillet over medium-high heat until crumbled and brown, the beef, about 10 minutes.
Drain off fat. Add green pepper and onion; cook and stir until soft, about 4 minutes.
Stir in all remaining ingredients except cheese.
Spoon 1/2 of the meat mixture into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan or 3-quart baking dish; top with 1/2 the cheese.
Spoon remaining meat mixture evenly over cheese.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut remaining cheese slices into decorative shapes.
Place on top of casserole.
Let stand, loosely covered, until cheese melts.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix in bowl and serve right away.

title: baked acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half; take out seeds (also cut small piece of end off so they will sit up).
Bake, cavity side down, in a baking dish with about 1/2 inch of water.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Pour off water; turn squash over and fill with filling.

title: virginia's easy lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and water.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Cook lasagna.
In a bowl, stir together Ricotta, Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese, eggs, parsley, salt and pepper.
Pour about 1 cup sauce on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Arrange 3 pasta pieces lengthwise over sauce.
Cover with 1 cup sauce.
Spread 1/2 cheese filling over sauce.
Repeat layers of lasagna sauce and cheese filling.
Top with layer of lasagna and remaining sauce.
Heat in 350° until heated, about 20 minutes.

title: barbecue basting sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and heat until dissolved, stirring while mixture heats.
Baste chicken or other meats each time meat is turned.
Store remaining sauce in refrigerator.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave approx. 30 seconds.
Put first 5 ingredients in a bowl and mix with mixer until creamy.

title: low-fat peach crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Coat a 6 x 8-inch pie pan with nonstick spray.
Mix peaches with cornstarch and sugar until the cornstarch is invisible.
In a food processor or blender, process the topping ingredients until the mixture is moist and lumpy.
Spoon peaches into pie pan and cover with the topping.
Bake for 25 minutes. Serve warm.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray 9 x 13 casserole dish with Pam. Brown pork chops on both sides; set aside. Peel and slice potatoes; put in dish. Mix soup, milk and cheese; pour
over potatoes. Salt and pepper. Put pork chops on top. Cover with foil. Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until potatoes are tender. Serve with salad and bread.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread in 8 x 14-inch pan.
Sprinkle Cheddar over and then corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Serves 8 to 10.
(Use ham to make main dish meal or without ham as vegetable or potato dish.)

title: fried turkey
directions: You will also need a clothes hanger.

title: icebox slaw
directions: Place cabbage and onion in layers.
Boil vinegar, sugar, salt and celery seed for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; add salad oil. Pour over cabbage and onion while hot.
Cover tightly. Refrigerate overnight.
Keeps for 2 weeks.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: spanakopita(spinach pie)
directions: Thaw and drain spinach, squeezing out all liquid.
Place cheese and eggs in a mixing bowl.
Bring to room temperature.
Add spinach, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Grease an 8-inch pie pan with margarine.
Begin placing the sheets of filo on the pan, one at a time, in a crisscross pattern, buttering each sheet as you go.
Save one sheet for the top.
Place last sheet on top, folding it to fit the pan.
Tuck the edges of the filo in along the sides of the pan with the dull side of a knife.
Cut 4 lines about 1/4-inch deep across the top of the filo.
Paint the top with the remaining butter.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 30 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Cut into serving pieces.
Serve hot or cold.

title: pasta, pepper and broccoli salad
directions: Cook linguine.
Cut red peppers into 1/4-inch strips.
Cut broccoli into 2 x 1/2-inch pieces.
In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in 1 tablespoon hot olive oil, cook peppers and 1/4 teaspoon salt until tender-crisp.
Remove peppers to bowl.

title: crispy chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Stir together cooked rice and next 7 ingredients in a bowl. Spoon into a lightly greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle evenly with cereal. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden and bubbly.

title: party shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup and cream cheese until melted, stirring often. Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Add to hot mixture.
Stir. Remove from heat, pour in lightly oiled mold.
Garnish with fresh parsley and serve with assorted party crackers.

title: steak and mushroom gravy
directions: Cut steak into smaller portion sizes. Dip in flour and brown in oil. Season steaks to your taste. Place browned steak in a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with a nonstick spray.

title: glorious baked beans
directions: Soak beans early in a.m. (to cook at night).
Drain, in new water, boil until beans skins split when you blow on them.
(I cube salt pork and add to beans when boiling; it gives them a shiny look.)
Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Add beans and enough of the water you cooked them in to just cover the beans. Stir and cook on low all night.
"You're sure to get raves."

title: gram's cinnamon toast
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar and cream in butter or margarine. Spread on toast.
For a special treat, slide under the broiler until bubbly.

title: mexican wedding cake
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl and beat until well blended. Bake in an 8 x 12-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Combine chocolate chips, margarine and corn syrup in a medium nonstick saucepan.
Stir over low heat until melted and smooth. Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and sugar.
Add Rice Krispies. Mix lightly until well coated.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. (Butter pan if it doesn't have a nonstick surface.)
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cheese pecan ball
directions: Mix cheeses and onion by hand.
Add salt and Tabasco sauce. Refrigerate several hours.
Shape and roll in pecans and parsley. Can be frozen. Makes 30 servings.

title: ann's surprise dessert
directions: Spread frosting in bottom of pan.
Open biscuits; divide each biscuit.
Wrap around unwrapped chocolate kiss.
Place dough into frosting mixture in bottom of can.
Bake until biscuits are done.

title: oreo-ice cream dessert
directions: Crush cookies until fine crumbs.
Spread 1/3 of crumbs in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let ice cream soften until you can stir it.
Fold in Cool Whip, 1/3 of crumbs and nuts.
Spread over crumbs in pan and sprinkle with remaining 1/3 of cookie crumbs. Freeze.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: pizza
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix pizza dough and spread on pizza pan. Add tomato sauce.
Cook sausage or beef until brown.
Drain meat and spread on pan.
Add topping.
Add cheese.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.

title: peanut butter chocos
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, milk and butter; boil for 2 minutes. Then add the oats, peanut butter, salt, vanilla, nuts and coconut. Mix all together and then drop onto a piece of wax paper.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together the butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add one egg at the time, mixing well after each addition.
Gradually add flour and salt.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour mixture into buttered and floured 10-inch tube cake pan.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Roll in chopped nuts and chill.

title: chicken with maple and spices
directions: Combine maple syrup, soy sauce and coriander seed and set aside.
In a heavy saucepan, melt 1 tablespoon of butter.
Add onion and saute until translucent.
Add tomatoes and saffron threads.
Saute until liquid is nearly gone.
Set aside.
Season chicken breasts with salt and pepper.
In a skillet, saute chicken breasts in remaining butter over medium-high heat until three-fourths done, about 3 minutes.
Add maple-soy mixture; reduce heat and cook 1 minute.
With a slotted spoon, remove chicken to a plate and keep warm.
Add tomato-saffron mixture and vinegar to skillet and cook over medium-low heat, stirring, to reduce sauce slightly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
To serve, divide sauce among 4 plates; slice chicken breasts and arrange slices on top of sauce.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion and cook until browned.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 30 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/4 cups or enough for 3 pounds of meat.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Allow cream cheese and butter to soften, then mix together with electric mixer along with 3 cups of sugar.
After this is mixed well, add 1 egg at a time, mixing after each egg.
When all the eggs are mixed, add vanilla, then sifted flour.
Put in Bundt pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Cook at 325° for 1 or 1 1/2 hours.
Time will vary.

title: chocolate fudgies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate chips together.
Stir in flour, condensed milk, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well and drop onto cookie sheet about 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake 7 minutes only at 350°.

title: potato soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven saute the celery and onion in the oil for about 1 to 2 minutes or until the onions are tender.
Don't brown them.
Add the potatoes, water, butter, salt and black pepper. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-high and cook until the potatoes are fork-tender, not mushy.
In a small bowl combine the flour with 1/2 cup milk.
Whisk until smooth.
Add in the soup mixture and stir.
Keep warm until time to serve.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Lay raw meat and vegetables in bottom of roaster pan.
Mix the tomato juice, tapioca, sugar, salt and pepper and pour over meat and vegetables.
Bake 5 hours at 250° (covered).
Delicious.

title: seven layer mexican dip
directions: Combine mashed avocados with lemon juice.
Use 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and layer as follows:

title: french onion soup
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Saute onions until slightly brown. Add onions to beef broth in saucepan.
Simmer slowly for 10 minutes.
Pour into bowls.
Place croutons on top of each bowlful, and either sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and serve immediately, or cover croutons with Swiss cheese, then Parmesan and bake, covered, at 325° for 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 10 minutes.

title: quick pickled cucumbers
directions: About 4 1/2 hours before serving or a day ahead, in a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish, stir together vinegar, sugar, salt and crushed red pepper.
Cut each unpeeled cucumber lengthwise into 6 wedges.
Place in baking dish with marinade.
Peel carrot and cut crosswise in half; cut each half lengthwise into matchstick-thin strips.
Place carrots in baking dish with cucumbers; toss to coat.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix in all other ingredients and heat.
Freezes well.

title: saucy meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine beef, green pepper, celery, onion, eggs, soup mix, bread crumbs, milk, salt and pepper; blend well. Shape into a loaf.
Place in a 9 x 13 pan.
In a small bowl, combine tomato sauce, mushrooms, water and brown sugar; blend well and pour over the meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 50-60 minutes or until meat is no longer pink inside.

title: vodka sauce(for pasta)
directions: Saute diced onions in butter until soft in a large saucepan. Add diced tomatoes, tomato sauce and spices.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Uncover and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring often, at low heat.
Remove from heat and slowly add heavy cream, stirring constantly.
Mix completely.
Slowly add vodka.
Return to heat, low, and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over pasta (bow ties, rotini or penne).

title: dog biscuit treat
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients until well blended.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut out treats with cookie cutter shaped like a dog bone or a heart shaped one.
Microwave at 50 for 5 to 10 minutes, turning every 2 minutes or bake in oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until dry.
Grease the cookie sheet lightly.
If too dry, add a little more hot water.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cream the butter and cheese together.
Work in flour and seasonings.
Shape mixture into small balls.
Place on baking sheet. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Serve hot.
Yields 50 biscuits.

title: onion cucumber salad
directions: Pull tines of fork firmly down length of the cucumber. Repeat this all the way around the cucumber.
Thinly slice onion, separating rings.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over vegetables.
Marinate 1 hour.
Drain to serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Mix milk and water.
Add egg yolks and cook until it bubbles and is thick.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; cook a little longer and pour into baked crust.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together sugar, shortening and eggs.
Stir in buttermilk and banana.
Sift together and stir in the flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Blend in nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: ground beef - spinach casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Stir in tomato sauce, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir and simmer 10 minutes.
Combine spinach (pressed very dry), cottage cheese, parsley flakes, oregano and salt. Spoon spinach mixture around side of casserole dish.
Put hamburger mixture in center.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cake mix cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 c. of the warm water.

Add the rest of the ingredients and knead with the last cup flour.	May need more. Let rise in greased (or sprayed) bowl until double (45-50 minutes). Roll out on floured counter & spread with 1/2-3/4 stick of melted margarine & sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll up and cut.
Place rolls in a greased cake pan & let rise 40 minutes. Bake about 20 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
Frost if desired.
Easy and Good!

title: bacon mushroom hors d'oeuvres
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with garlic salt.
Cut away stem of mushroom and fill with cream cheese mixture.
Wrap each mushroom with 1/2 slice bacon and secure with a toothpick.
Bake at 350° until crisp (usually 1 hour).
Serve while hot.

title: hurry up supper
directions: Brown beef and onion in Dutch oven.
Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients, except macaroni.
Stir well and bring to boil.
Add macaroni.
Stir well again.
Cover.
Reduce heat to medium and cook until vegetables are tender, about 45 minutes. `Recipe may be doubled.
Very good on a cold night.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop the corn.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Place into a 2-quart glass bowl.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.

title: lemon pineapple carrot salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and 1 cup boiling water.
Place in refrigerator 30 minutes.
Remove and whip with fork.
Stir in 1 small can crushed pineapple and grated, peeled carrots.
Mix well. Stir in 2 tablespoons mayonnaise.
Chill several hours.

title: spanish liver
directions: Preheat oven.
Put oil	in skillet. roll liver in flour and place in skillet.
Brown,
turning	several times.	Remove from skillet, add onions and green pepper, let brown slightly. Add washed rice, tomatoes,
liver
and chili powder.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover.
Put in oven, turn heat to low, allow to cook for 45 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown hamburg and onion. Cook bacon and crumble. Add bacon, soup, salt and pepper. Bring water to boil; stir in rice. Cover and let stand 5 minutes. Mix rice and hamburg combination. Serve warm with garlic toast.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion and green pepper; cook slowly for 2 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for 10 minutes. Yields 8 servings.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Heavenly Father, we ask you to bless these little breads.

Each time we eat them may we be reminded of the special season we are in and that through prayer we will become better people to each other. Let us not forget those who are in need of our prayers daily.
Keep your loving arms around us, O Father, to protect us always.
Amen.

title: east breakfast(great for brunch)
directions: Trim crust from bread and place 6 slices in oblong baking dish. Put a slice of cheese and bacon on each bread slice and then cover with remaining bread.
Now beat eggs until fluffy, add milk, salt and pepper and dry mustard.
Pour over bread.
Refrigerate overnight or for at least 2 hours.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes or until set and brown on top.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and baking soda.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly by hand.
Bake in well-greased 10 x 15-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mama terry's chocolate banana cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs, bananas, water, oil and butter flavoring until blended.
Blend on medium speed.
Increase speed and whip a few minutes until smooth and creamy.
Grease and flour three 8 or 9-inch pans and fill 1/2 to 2/3 full only.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans.
Set until completely cool.

title: chicken taco rice
directions: Cook and stir chicken in hot oil until lightly browned.
Add water, tomato sauce and seasoning mix; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add corn and red pepper. Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes; fluff with fork.
Sprinkle with cheese. Serve with tortilla chips, if desired.

title: deer jerky
directions: Mix all ingredients together (to your own taste) except deer. Slice deer into thin strips.
Pour mixture over deer to cover. Salt and pepper, if desired.
Refrigerate 48 hours.
Place deer on oven pan.
Bake at 100° for 8 hours.
Remember that 2 pounds of meat makes 1/2 pound of jerky.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugars, egg yolks, milk and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Chill for 1 hour. Roll out and cut.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: creamy double decker fudge
directions: In 2-cup glass cup with handle, combine peanut butter chips and 2/3 cup sweetened condensed milk.
Cook on 100% power (High) for 1 to 2 minutes, until chips are melted and mixture is smooth. Stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread into foil lined 8-inch square pan.

title: chocolate cake with pudding mix
directions: Mix all together. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: turkey broccoli divan
directions: Cook rice and arrange in 3-quart baking dish.
Cook broccoli and drain; put on top of rice.
Top with turkey or chicken.
Mix soup and milk and pour over all.
Sprinkle cheese and bread crumbs mixed with margarine over top. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions into a large bowl.
Sprinkle salt over them.
Mix thoroughly.
Let set for 3 to 4 hours.
Drain well.
Mix sugar and white vinegar.
Mix well.
Pour over cuke-onion mix and stir well.
Put in freezer containers and freeze.
Defrost at room temperature.
Put 2 or 3 sprigs fresh parsley as garnish when you serve.

title: fried fruit pies
directions: You will need a rolling pin, fork and skillet.

title: frijoles a la charra(beans)
directions: Wash beans; place in large pot with water and boil until cooked (covered).
Place bacon in skillet and fry until cooked; remove all grease drippings and discard grease.
Put cooked bacon in cooked beans and stir under low-medium heat.
Place sausage slices in skillet and fry until brown.
Remove all grease drippings and discard grease.
Place cooked sausage slices in cooked beans and stir under low-medium heat.
Place tomatoes, onion, cilantro, jalapeno peppers and 1 teaspoon margarine in skillet and saute. Then place in cooked beans and stir under low-medium heat for 30 minutes so that flavors mix.
Enjoy!

title: marinated fruit
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice and set aside.
Combine pineapple, pear, apple and nectarine.
Set aside.
Combine reserved pineapple juice, orange juice concentrate, honey and mint.
Pour over fruit and toss gently.
Cover and chill, stirring occasionally.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together in order listed.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour. Remove from oven.
Let stand 10 minutes in pan before removing.

title: grandma ballard's sugar cookies
directions: Add enough flour to make a soft dough, about 3 to 4 cups. Roll out thin and cut with cookie cutter.
Sprinkle sugar on top and bake at 350° to 375° about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: new orleans style bread pudding(heritage)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mixture should be very moist.
Let mixture rest in the refrigerator overnight before baking.
Pour into a buttered 9x13 baking dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/4 hours or until top is golden brown.
Serve with caramel sauce.

title: oyster casserole
directions: Boil milk.
Remove from heat and drop in oysters for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove oysters.
Crumble 1/2 saltines in dish.
Top with 1/2 oysters, celery and cheese.
Repeat.
Top with thin layer of saltines and cheese.
Salt and pepper. Mix eggs, butter, Texas Pete and thyme in milk.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until brown.

title: easy peas and mushrooms
directions: Cook peas according to package directions; drain well.
Cook mushrooms and onion in butter or margarine until tender.
Stir in sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper. Add cooked peas and pimento. Cover and heat through.
Serves 4.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In a large pot cook celery and onion in butter until tender. Add remaining ingredients, except noodles.
Simmer 30 minutes. Remove bay leaf.
Add noodles and cook 10 minutes longer or until noodles are tender.
Makes about a half gallon.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook chicken with at least 1 1/2-quarts salted water.
When done, remove chicken and save broth.
Take chicken off bone and cut into bite size pieces.
Put stuffing in a large bowl reserving 1/2 cup plain.
Add enough broth to make stuffing consistency of cornbread batter.
Spray large pan with Pam; spread stuffing in pan.
Place chicken over stuffing.
Thin soup with 1/4 to 1/3 cup of broth.
Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle with reserved crumbs. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, until browned and bubbly in center.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: macaroni fruit salad
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt and flour together.
Drain juices from fruit into saucepan with the egg mixture.
Stir over low heat and cook until thick.
Add fruit.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, except mustard, catsup and brown sugar. Put in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on top of loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: my mother's chicken cacciatore (in a pot)
directions: Brown chicken in oil. Season with salt, pepper, garlic and basil. Cook for 10 minutes, turning frequently. Add the tomatoes which you have crushed by hand and sliced peppers.
Cook, covered, 45 to 60 minutes. Serve with plain or garlic bread.
Enjoy!

title: beef and macaroni
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Pour cooked macaroni over meat.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Top with cheese.
Put in 450° oven until cheese melts.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Stir together as for any other cake.
Pour batter into 4 coffee cans.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and press into a 9-inch pie plate (bottom and sides).
Bake for 15 minutes in a 425° oven. Pour off fat.
Pour the peas or peas and carrots into shell. Sprinkle with the cheese.
Boil the water.
Add the potato flakes, milk, egg, butter, salt, onion and garlic salt.
Mix thoroughly. (May need to add more potatoes if too thin or more milk if too thick.)
Cover pie with potato mixture. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake again for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and season to taste.
Place in shallow casserole pan and put Tater Tots on top.
Pour the mixture of soup and milk over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be made ahead and refrigerated until ready to bake.

title: baked beef brisket
directions: Bake all ingredients in roasting pan with at least most of the meat covered with water.
Set oven at 350° and bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Let meat cool before cutting.
Let gravy cool.
Slice across grain and put back in pan.
Let sit in cool area and heat before slicing.

title: minestrone
directions: Saute onions, peppers and garlic in oil until wilted. Add celery, carrots, zucchini, cayenne, thyme and basil. Mix well. Cover and steam for 10 minutes. Add beans, pasta, tomatoes and water. Simmer until veggies are just tender. Sprinkle with parsley.
Freezes well.

title: banana cake
directions: Preheat oven 350°F. Grease 2 layer pans or a 9 x 13
inch pan. Cream shortening, sugar and eggs, then bananas and vanilla. Mix dry ingredients
Add dry ingredients to banana mixture with buttermilk. Bake at 350° 30-35 minutes.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Blend all together and bake in oven for 20 to 25 minutes, until good and hot.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix.
Pour in 2 loaf pans and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: sour cream apple bars
directions: Cover the apples with water.
Simmer 20 minutes until apples are soft.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Bake beef roast until partially done.
Cool.
Cut in pieces. Put back in sauce.
Bake in oven a total of about 4 hours.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix ingredients into greased casserole dish.
Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry cherry mist
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; stir in cranberry sauce and 50/50.
Pour into a nice glass bowl.
Chill until set.
Top with a thin layer of sour cream and a sprinkle of cinnamon/sugar.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine filling ingredients in order given.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350°.
Bake for 45 minutes longer.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Saute vegetables without tomatoes in butter.
Should be crisp, not soft.
Drain well.
Add seasonings.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer in a large bowl on high speed for about 4 minutes.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat at medium speed about 5 minutes.
Combine milk and persimmon pulp.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Add persimmon mix and flour mix to egg mix.
Beat until combined.
Pour in a greased and floured 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
With a fork, poke holes in top of pudding and pour batter slowly over pudding.
Bake 15 minutes more.

title: basic best salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon, reserving 2 tablespoons of liquid.
Flake salmon.
Combine with liquid and remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Shape into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat crescent rolls flat on lightly greased cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: bread dip
directions: Make hole in top of bread and scoop out inside of loaf.
Tear into bite size pieces.
Put mayonnaise mixture into center of loaf and dip bread.
Enjoy!

title: molasses oat bread
directions: Combine 2 cups of flour, yeast and salt in large bowl.
Stir well to blend.
Add molasses and butter.
Add hot tap water.
Beat with electric mixer at medium for 2 minutes.
Add 1 more cup of flour.
Beat at high speed for 1 minute or until dough is thick and elastic.
Stir in oats.
Gradually stir in just enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn onto floured board.
Knead 5 to 10 minutes.
Cover with plastic wrap or towel.
Let sit 20 minutes on board.
Punch down and divide in half.
Shape into loaves; let rise.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Can refrigerate dough from 2 to 24 hours.

title: southwestern chicken salad(4 servings)
directions: Cook chicken.
Cool; shred into small pieces.
Combine mayo and 1/4 cup sour cream; stir well.
Add chilies and next 3 ingredients; stir well.
Combine chicken and onion; add to sour cream mix.
Stir, cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Place tortillas on a baking sheet; sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 300° for 10 minutes, until cheese melts.
Transfer to individual serving plates.
Arrange lettuce over tortillas.
Top with chicken. Garnish with sour cream and tomato.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: vegetable nut roast
directions: Combine all the ingredients in a bowl.
Lightly grease a loaf pan and press in mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Cook in pan with water to cover them. Drain and set aside.
Melt butter in heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Yield: About 2 1/2 cups.

title: slush
directions: Completely dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in water. Stir in juice and pineapple. Freeze in quart containers. To serve, thaw at room temperature for 3 hours.
Put partially thawed slush in punch bowl and add ginger ale.

title: chocolate pom pom
directions: Mix margarine, vanilla and peanut butter together.
Add powdered sugar and mix well together.
Melt wax and chocolate chips in a double boiler pan.
Roll mixture into balls and chill while chips and wax melts.
Roll in chocolate chips and set on wax paper.
Makes about 60 pieces.

title: vegetable mix
directions: Heat together green pepper, celery and onion.
When tender, add remaining ingredients and heat on low until heated thoroughly.

title: chile cornbread fiesta
directions: Add salt, tomatoes and corn; mix well.
Pour into 9-inch shallow casserole.
Combine cornbread mix, egg and milk; mix well. Spread evenly over top of hamburger mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese and bake 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: pork country ribs sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour over ribs in a fairly shallow pan or until ribs are just covered.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven 1 1/2 hours.
Turning ribs partially through cooking time is a good idea.
Extra sauce can easily be strained, fat removed and thickened if desired and poured over rice.

title: fish fillets in wine sauce
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour and then cream of mushroom soup and Sauterne.
Cook, stirring constantly until mix boils and thickens.
Add Parmesan cheese.
Arrange fish fillets in single layer in greased, shallow baking dish.
Pour sauce over fish and bake 25 minutes at 375°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon frappe
directions: Place all ingredients in blender jar.
Blend at crushed ice speed for 30 seconds.
Pour into glasses.
Serve immediately. Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: cheese ball
directions: Place all ingredients except pecans in mixing bowl and let soften.
Mix together and roll into balls (makes two).
Roll balls in chopped pecans and chill in refrigerator.

title: chuck wagon biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add buttermilk and remaining ingredients.
Mix well; place in covered bowl in refrigerator.
Use a little each day.
No need to let rise.
Knead a little before cutting.
Grease both sides of biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
If you don't use all the dough at once, punch dough down daily.
It will keep a week or longer.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix egg, brown sugar, sugar, peanut butter, shortening, vanilla and milk.
Then mix in flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well together.
Form dough into equal size balls, roll in sugar and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Cook at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Top each one immediately with chocolate kiss, pressing down firmly so cookie cracks around the edges. Makes about 48 cookies.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: In medium saucepan bring rice and water to a boil.
Simmer covered until rice is tender (about 25 minutes).
In small bowl stir together sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir into hot rice with half and half.
Stirring constantly bring to a boil and boil for 1 full minute.
Add butter and vanilla.
In a small bowl slightly beat eggs.
Into this gradually stir in 1 cup hot rice mixture. Gradually stir this back into the remaining rice.
Stir often until mixture bubbles.
Let stand at room temperature until cool.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: old-fashioned raisin pie
directions: Line pie plate with one crust.
Combine 1 tablespoon sugar and 2 tablespoons flour.
Rub over pastry to prevent sogginess.
Cook raisins in buttermilk and water until tender.
Combine remaining sugar, flour, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Add to raisin mixture. Let cool.
Add beaten egg, lemon juice and butter.
Pour into pastry shell.
Cut remaining crust into strips and place over filling.
Bake at 475° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 350° for 30 minutes longer.
Keeps well up to 2 weeks.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat instant pudding and milk until thick; add whipped cream, sour cream and sugar.
Then layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding in dish.
Refrigerate until serving.
Serves 6 people.

title: cherry mash
directions: Mix the sugar, cherries, milk, vanilla and frosting mix.
Roll in balls and place on cookie sheet; chill.

title: cumin rice
directions: In bacon grease, saute bell pepper, onion, and uncooked rice until rice is golden brown. Add consomme, worcestershire sauce, salt, and cumin seed. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until liquid is almost dissolved.

title: pumpkin torte
directions: Combine graham crackers, butter and sugar and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add eggs and sugar; beat until smooth.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes; strain to remove skin and seeds.
Put celery, pepper, onion and parsley through food processor or blender.
Add to prepared juice.
Cook until boiling, then simmer for 30 minutes or thicken.
Add butter and remaining ingredients.
Continue simmering.
You may want to thicken with a little cornstarch or flour in a paste.
Add to sauce.
Ladle into jars or containers if freezing.
Process 10 minutes at 5 pounds pressure.

title: chocolate mousse cups
directions: Melt 8 ounces of the chocolate over simmering water.
Cool slightly.
Divide paper cups into stacks of 3 each.
Using a small brush, coat the inside of the cup with a thin layer of chocolate. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Carefully peel off paper.
Melt remaining chocolate over simmering water; stir in butter.
Stir in egg yolks, one at a time.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff, adding sugar gradually.
Stir in framboise.
Fold a cup of egg whites into mousse mixture to lighten it.
Fold in remaining egg whites.

title: sassy sausages
directions: In skillet, heat 1 cup water, the cinnamon candies and a few drops red food coloring until candies are melted.
Place apple rings in syrup; cook slowly, turning occasionally, about 20 minutes or until tender.
Place links in another skillet; add 3 tablespoons water.
Cover tightly; cook slowly for 8 minutes. Uncover; cook, turning sausages until well browned.
To serve, insert hot sausage link in center of each apple slice.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a cookie sheet.
In medium-large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat all ingredients.
Drop mixture by rounded tablespoonfuls, at least 2-inches apart, onto cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes or until top springs back when pressed with finger.
With spatula, remove cookies to wire racks to cool.

title: hamburger-one dish meal
directions: Brown hamburg, onions and pepper; add 1/2 can tomato soup to meat mixture.
Mix well.
Add cooked vegetables to meat mixture. Pour mixture into 1-quart baking dish.
Top with mashed potatoes. Bake at 375° until topping is browned.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: barbecued pot roast
directions: Rub roast with salt and pepper; brown in fat.
Add water, tomato sauce, tomato paste, bouillon cubes, onions and garlic. Cover; cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over meat.
Cover; continue cooking about 1 hour or until tender.
Add more water if needed. Remove to hot platter.
Skim off fat from gravy, then thicken with 2 tablespoons flour mixed to smooth paste with water.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo in dish.
Pour in bread mix; add corn.
Stir in sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Add cheese and let melt.

title: quick lemon pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into graham cracker pie crust.
Freeze for 2 hours and serve.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Boil water and sugar for 2 minutes.
Place chocolate chips in blender and pour boiled sugar/water over them.
Blend for 2 minutes.
Add egg yolk and blend one minute.
Add flavoring and blend a few seconds.
Fold chocolate mixture into whipped cream. Place in serving dishes.
Chill 1 hour and serve.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer slowly.
This is good to use with leftover beef or pork roast and put in buns.

title: bruschetta with tomatoes and capers
directions: Cut tomatoes in half and squeeze out the seeds.
Dice the flesh and combine with capers or arugula or basil, 1 teaspoon oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.

title: pasta primavera
directions: If you are using packaged dressing mix, prepare according to directions and refrigerate.
Mix together and set aside, shrimp, snowpeas, olives, pimentos, artichoke hearts, scallions and tomatoes.
Cook and drain pasta and toss with all ingredients.
Add dressing and garnish with parsley.
For variety, add seasonal vegetables.

title: chocolate clair dessert
directions: Using a whisk, mix pudding with milk.
Fold in whipped topping. Place layer of graham crackers on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with half of pudding mix.
Repeat layers: graham crackers, remaining pudding, graham crackers.
Top with Chocolate Sauce.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix 1/4 cup flour with raisins and nuts before adding to cake mix.

title: mocha flavored coffee
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender or food processor until powdered.
You can also use decaffeinated coffee.
Store in airtight container.
Put 2 rounded teaspoonfuls into a cup filled with hot water.

title: best-ever cole slaw
directions: Sprinkle the sugar over the cabbage, green pepper and onion. Bring the remaining ingredients to a boil and pour while hot over the cabbage mixture. Cover. Cool and refrigerate overnight.
Makes 1 quart.

title: overnight salad
directions: Mix together lettuce, green pepper, onion and celery and put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together peas, eggs, cheese, bacon, salad dressing and sugar and put on top of first layer.
Mix some cheese and bacon with dressing.
When complete, cover with foil and put in fridge overnight.

title: no sugar icing for cake
directions: Mix pudding mix and milk until smooth and as it thickens, add the Cool Whip.
Let set in refrigerator until firm, then spread over a small sheet cake.
For special times, ice your cake out of the pan, then add a layer of no-sugar Just Fruit Preserves and then another layer of Cool Whip.

title: classroom bread
directions: Put in a pinch of boys and a teaspoon of girls.
A half cup of teacher and stir good.
After that put in your science teacher and book.
Here's a big part, put in your brain!
Now add your Social Studies book.
Stir one more time.
Put in oven for five hours. Then you've got a good school day!

title: butter rum pound cake
directions: Cream butter gradually.
Beat in 2 1/2 cups sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Combine flour and soda; add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir in vanilla and lemon extract.
Beat egg whites at room temperature until foamy. Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, one tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff peaks form.
Gently fold into batter.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes, or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: tapioca salad
directions: Take juice from pineapple and oranges; add enough water to make 3 cups. Cook tapioca in liquid and sugar. When thick, add orange juice and fruit; chill.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Line 1 1/2-quart casserole with 1 tablespoon butter.
Pour in half of boiled rice.
Place 1 tablespoon butter in pint size saucepan; add flour and brown.
Add onion and chili pepper and cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add shrimp, celery and tomato sauce.
Salt and paprika to taste.
Pour sauce in casserole; top with remaining rice.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: old fashioned peach custard pie
directions: Place peaches in pan; cover with boiling water.
Cook until tender.
Sweeten to taste with 1/2 cup sugar, more or less.
Allow to cool.

title: sausage jambalaya
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a greased 2-quart casserole with a lid, combine all ingredients.
Bake, covered, until rice is cooked, about 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: mrs. ozzie's hominy
directions: I use fresh field corn, not sweet corn.
Shuck and silk corn thoroughly.
Cut corn off cob and wash.
Put corn in plastic container 3/4 full of baking soda water.
Let soak 2 days.
Corn will swell.
In wash pot, cook corn in fresh water with salt about 6 hours (cooking hard) until tender.
Wash corn well, rubbing with hands until skins fall off.
Eat as is or salt and pepper and fry. Yum, yum!

title: potatoes rancheros casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Mix potatoes, sauce mix, water, corn and milk in ungreased 2-quart casserole. Stir in beef and 3/4 cup cheese. Bake, uncovered, 30 to 35 minutes or until top is golden brown. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Let stand a few minutes.

title: chili sauce
directions: Scald tomatoes; peel.
Cook 15 minutes; drain off half the juice.
Chop remaining vegetables; add tomatoes.
Simmer about 1 1/2 hours.
Tie spices in cloth bag; add with remaining ingredients to tomato mixture.
Continue cooking 1 1/2 hours. Remove spices; seal in hot, sterilized jars.
Makes 6 pints.

title: tater soup
directions: Cover potatoes with water; salt and pepper to taste.
Add onion.
Bring to boil; simmer for 12 to 14 minutes, until tender but not mushy.
Gently mash into small chunks.
Add cayenne pepper, all-purpose seasoning, the margarine, cheese, milk and bouillon cubes.
Bring to a gentle boil, stirring occasionally. Simmer until cheese and margarine melt.
Recipe can be halved or doubled.

title: skinny fried chicken
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spoon over chicken and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Chop chicken into small pieces.
Add all other ingredients to chicken.
Save 1/2 cup cheese for top of dish.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: blueberry cheese cake
directions: Combine and press in 9-inch spring-form pan. Lightly grease pan. Can use graham cracker crust.

title: cheese wafers(3 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 400° ten minutes before wafers are to go in. Grease cookie sheets.
Combine all ingredients and work into smooth dough.
Divide dough in half making 2 rolls about 8-inches long and 1 1/4-inches in diameter; put them in refrigerator to chill.
When firm, slice into wafers 1/8-inch thick.
Place on prepared cookie sheets and prick with fork.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: toffee-nut bars
directions: Mix shortening and brown sugar. Stir in flour. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Combine remaining ingredients. Spread over first mixture. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: atheroma spread
directions: Saute onions in butter until transparent (DO NOT BROWN).
Add sherry and cook until reduced.
Mix cooked onions with cheese, mayo, pepper and garlic salt.
Bake in an 8X8 glass dish at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Pour mixture into hollowed round bread, sprinkle with paprika and broil 2 minutes.
Serve with crackers and bread.
Serves 10-12.

title: escalloped tomatoes
directions: In 1 1/2-quart saucepan, melt margarine and saute onion until tender.
Stir in bread crumbs, sugar, salt and pepper.
Arrange a layer of tomatoes in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with onion and bread crumbs.
Repeat layers until all is used, ending with crumbs. Bake, uncovered, in preheated oven at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: van's banana bread
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and eggs, using mixer.
Add bananas, apples and orange juice.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients by hand.
Mix together nuts and add gently into the batter.
Place in greased long, large loaf pan (4 1/2 x 2 1/2 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for about 60 minutes.
Makes 1 large loaf.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine; pour over bread stuffing.
Put 1/2 mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Boil chicken; tear off bone.
Add layer of chicken and 1/2 soup and water mixture.
Add layer of chicken and remainder of soup mixture.
Top with 1/2 bread crumbs. Bake until heated.

title: quick nut fudge
directions: Combine all the ingredients (except nuts) in top of double boiler.
Place over hot water.
Stir until smooth.
Add nuts and mix well.
Spread candy in buttered 9 x 5-inch pan. Cool and cut.

title: roasted poultry - whole
directions: Note:
If you are going to do a turkey, use double the amounts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In medium casserole dish, place crackers (broken into large pieces).
Melt oleo and pour over crackers, stirring lightly to coat.
Boil chicken, debone and arrange on top of crackers.
Mix together soup, sour cream, chicken broth, pepper, salt, garlic salt and celery salt.
Pour over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until bubbly.

title: easy pina colada cake
directions: *Omit if included in cake mix.

title: sally's lentil soup
directions: Place lentils in bowl.
Add water; soak overnight.
Drain and discard soaking water.
Wash lentils well in water.
Place lentils in soup pot; cover with 3 quarts of water and bring to a boil. Add onion, celery, carrots, tomatoes, olive oil and spinach.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add grated cheese.

title: pea `n' cheese salad
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 6 ingredients. In a small bowl, combine the mayonnaise, relish and seasonings. Stir into pea mixture. Cover and refrigerate until serving. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Chop tomatoes and chili peppers.
