Mix all ingredients together and cook.
Serve with shredded cheese on top, if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: 1. Cook broccoli 5 minutes and put in large greased cass erole dish.
Sprinkle onion over broccoli. 2. Pour soup and sprinle cheese on.
Mix stuffing with Margarine and put on top. 3. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes with cover on then 15 minutes with uncovered.

title: creamed broccoli pudding
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix mayonnaise, cheese, eggs, soup and onions.
Add broccoli and mix well.
Pour into well-greased casserole dish.
Dot with butter and top with cracker crumbs. Bake in 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: iron skillet chocolate pie
directions: Melt butter in iron skillet over low heat.
Add sugar, flour and cocoa; mix lightly.
Combine egg yolks and milk to mixture. Stir constantly until thick.
Add vanilla and mix.
Pour into baked pie shell; cover with meringue and brown.

title: beef dip
directions: Beat cream cheese, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add everything else.
Put in glass baking dish at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Use as a dip with crackers or bread.

title: bambinis - miniature calzones
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine Ricotta, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese in a medium bowl.
Separate biscuits from can; slice each one horizontally.
Press each sliced biscuit into oblong shape, approximately 2 1/2 x 4-inch.
Place one slice of pepperoni and 1 teaspoon of cheese mixture onto each pressed biscuit.
Fold over and press edge to seal.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Yields 16.

title: puppies and potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and mash them with butter, salt, pepper and a little milk or cream.
Boil one package of hot dogs.
Put hot dogs on a large cookie sheet.
Cover hot dogs with mashed potatoes. Indent mashed potatoes and fill with grated cheese.
Put in oven until cheese is melted.
Serve.

title: red beans and rice with polish sausage or ham
directions: Mix beans, Ro-Tel and cooked onions.
Simmer about 30 minutes and add ham or sausage.
Brown sausage.
Pour over rice in casserole dish and put in oven to warm.

title: smothered steak for crock-pot
directions: Put
steak, seasonings and flour in crock-pot.	Stir to coat. Add
vegetables
and soy sauce.
Cover and cook on high for 1 hour.
Turn
to
low
for
8 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles. Easy!

title: popcorn ball
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Add milk.
Cook to soft ball stage and add vanilla.
Pour over popcorn and make into ball.

title: best ever homemade baked beans
directions: Chop onion fine or put in blender.
Mix everything together well in mixing bowl.
Then pour on top of beans in a roaster. Stir well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered.
Stir a few times.

title: beef-n-broccoli
directions: Slice beef into thin strips, spray skillet with vegetable cooking spray, heat over med. heat 1 minute.
Stir-fry broccoli and onion until crisp.
Remove from pan, set aside.
Stir fry beef until brown, add gravy, soy sauce and garlic.
Remove vegetables and heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into 1/2-inch strips.
Saute in butter.
Add spices. Stir occasionally.
Cook until tender.
Chop onions and peppers into strips. Add onions, peppers, celery and water.
Cover and let simmer for 1 hour or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Beat butter until soft.
Add sugar.
Blend until creamy.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Stir in well and then add flour.
Roll dough into small balls and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake about 30 minutes.
While warm, roll in 10x sugar.
Preheat oven to 300°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut chuck roast into small pieces.
Put into ovensafe pan.
Mix onion soup mix, mushroom soup and 2 cans milk together.
Pour over chuck roast.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours and 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and turn off.
Mix sour cream in and return to off oven for 15 minutes.
Remove after 15 minutes and serve over buttered noodles.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine margarine, sugar, salt and corn syrup in medium saucepan.
Heat while stirring until full boil.
Cook and stir for 5 minutes.
Add vanilla and 1/2 teaspoon soda; stir.
Place popped corn on two large jell roll pans or cookie sheets.
Pour 1/2 sauce over each pan.
Stir to coat.
Bake at 250° for 1/2 hour stirring at 15 minutes.
Remove form oven.
Cool on pan.
Break apart and store in closed container.

title: no beat popovers
directions: Break eggs into mixing bowl; add milk, flour and salt.
Mix well with spoon (disregard lumps).
Fill greased (Pam spray works) muffin pan 3/4 each.
Place into cold oven and set at 450°.
Turn on oven and bake 30 minutes.

title: swiss green beans
directions: Drain green beans.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine, then add flour, salt, sugar, sour cream and onion.
Fold beans into the above mixture.
Spread into a 2-quart dish.
Mix corn flakes and 1 tablespoon melted margarine together.
Sprinkle beans with Swiss cheese and corn flakes.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: quick and easy casserole
directions: Tear up bread, any kind and put in 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased dish.
Brown and drain sausage or links.
Drain (cut link in slices).
Spoon sausage over bread.
Sprinkle with grated sharp Cheddar cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Great for holiday mornings.

title: finger sandwich
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread on bread.
(Use white sandwich bread, cut and remove crust.)
Cut into four slices each.

title: beans and meat
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain off grease.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruited gelatin cupcakes
directions: Pour gelatin into bowl.
Add 1 cup boiling water to gelatin. Stir with rubber spatula until gelatin is completely dissolved, about 2 minutes.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Using measuring cup, scoop gelatin from bowls into 6 muffin pan cups.
Put pan into refrigerator to chill until gelatin is thickened, about 45 minutes.
Take pan out of refrigerator.
Add fruit to each cup; stir gently.
Put pan into refrigerator to chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Put about 1-inch of warm water in sink.
Dip just bottom of pan into warm water for 5 seconds.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add beaten eggs, pineapple and nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 12-inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Brown the meat, draining away the excess grease.
Mix in soups.
Add remaining ingredients except the tater tots.
Place this mixture in a 9 by 13 in. casserole dish and top with the frozen tater tots.
Bake for 20 minutes. Sprinkle shredded cheese over the top of the tots and return to the oven for 10 min. or just until the cheese melts. Remove and enjoy!

title: the wayside inn's corn muffins
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except the oil, for 3 minutes using the lowest speed of the mixer, or by hand, until well mixed.
Then slowly add the oil as you mix for another 3 minutes, again using the lowest speed or stirring by hand.
Fill well-greased muffin tins 3/4 full of batter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, until golden brown.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cut vegetables up into bite-size pieces and place in large bowl.
Mix vinegar with oil and sugar.
Pour over the vegetables. Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with raw vegetables, chips or crackers.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Cut cooked chicken into cubes.
Combine chicken, celery, salt, onion, lemon juice, mayonnaise and vermouth.
Refrigerate 1 hour to blend.
Spoon mixture into buttered 9 x 13-inch dish. Top with crumbs and cheese before putting in oven.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and heated through. Serves 12 to 15.

title: glazed carrots and pineapple
directions: Cover and cook carrots with salt and water until almost tender.
Drain liquid from carrots into measuring cup and add pineapple juice to make 1 cup.
Pour into saucepan and mix cornstarch, cook stirring constantly until thick and clear.
Stir in butter, add carrots and tidbits.
Heat and serve.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together. Shape into balls and brown in skillet. Place in baking dish. In a separate bowl, combine sugar and mustard, then next 3 ingredients. Pour over meatballs and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fruit sauce
directions: Mix together.
Keeps for days in refrigerator.

title: garlic feta cheese spread
directions: Put all ingredients into a food processor.
Blend until the mixture is combined well.
Transfer the spread to crock or serving dish.
Cover; chill for 2 hours.
Keeps covered and chilled for one week or longer.
Serve with crackers or celery or carrot sticks.

title: oven-fried potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line baking dish with tinfoil.
Melt butter in dish (in oven).
Add potatoes, parsley and bacon bits, stirring occasionally, until well done.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat and sausage with onion and drain.
Put in crock-pot.
Cut cheese up.
Add cheese, soup and tomatoes.
Let cook until cheese melts.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocados with potato masher.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: better  butter
directions: Beat oil and butter together until fluffy. Refrigerate. Spreads easily after a few minutes from the refrigerator.

title: holiday mix
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients, then cover with melted chocolate or almond bark.

title: pineapple-peach frappes
directions: Use grind cycle in blender and whirl pineapple, peach and pineapple juice in blender until pureed.
Add yogurt, milk and honey.
Whirl on "frappe" cycle until smooth and thick.
Pour into tall glasses.

title: protein cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend eggs, vanilla, lemon juice and sweetener in blender until smooth.
Gradually add cottage cheese and pure cinnamon.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into Pam sprayed pie plate.
Bake approximately 45 minutes.
Let cool 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Then refrigerate.
One slice equals 1 protein.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and salad oil.
Add kraut, celery, pepper and onion.
Refrigerate for up to a week.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef; add refried beans and cumin.
Thin with about 3/4 can water.
Simmer for a few minutes.
Warm tortillas according to package directions.
Put a small amount of meat/bean mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Roll up tortillas with cheese and a little onion.
Arrange in the pan and cover with remaining meat mixture.
Cover and bake at 350° until heated through, about 30 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Turn broiler on and preheat for 5 minutes.
Add Worcestershire sauce to milk and soup mix.
Mix into ground beef.
Allow 1 tablespoon of meat mixture per meatball.
Form meatballs.
Place under broiler about 4-inches from heat.
Broil 5 to 6 minutes or until brown without turning.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Use these ingredients to make seven layers in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: chef's salad
directions: Mix the greens with the vegetables and oil.
Mix the lemon juice and top with turkey breast and shrimp.
Add sliced egg last.

title: meat loaf
directions: Sauce:
Mix 2 tablespoons A.1. sauce and 1 (8 ounce) can tomato sauce.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook rice in 2 cups boiling water until tender.
Cut bacon into small pieces and saute in skillet until done.
Remove bacon from skillet and add the beef; stir until lightly browned.
Pour off fat.
Add bacon and beef to remaining ingredients.
Mix well and turn into casserole.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Add water if needed.

title: sweet pea salad
directions: Chop carrot, cucumber, onion and bell pepper in small pieces. Combine peas and noodles.
Toss with cucumber dressing.
Chill and serve.

title: good casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Heat Cheez Whiz, onion, garlic salt, soup and chili powder until bubbly, stirring often.
Combine beef and hominy.
Stir in cheese mixture and mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with crushed Fritos. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pies
directions: Beat together first five ingredients; stir in nuts; pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° until a knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean (about 50 minutes).
Cool.

title: peppery scalloped potatoes
directions: In a small bowl, combine the soup, milk, salt and cayenne; set aside. Place a third of the potatoes in a greased 9 X 13 inch pan. Layer with a third of the butter, flour and soup mixture. Repeat layers twice. Bake, uncovered at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Serves 6 to 8.

title: pasta salad
directions: In a large pot of salted, boiling water, cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and rinse under cold water.
Drain again and set aside.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix
ground
ham, ground pork, eggs, milk, onion powder and milk.
Pack
into
loaf
pan and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Make mixture of brown sugar, mustard and vinegar and pour
over	top
of
loaf.	Continue
baking for about 30 more minutes at	325°.
Remove
from
oven
and	let stand 10 to 15 minutes
before turning out onto platter to slice.	Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini skillet
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring occasionally.
Add onions and cook 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients (except Parmesan cheese).
Cook 5 minutes, uncovered, stirring occasionally.
Serve sprinkled with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix with mixer at room temperature.
Make cheese ball.
Roll in 1/4 cup shredded dried beef after chilled roll.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients; pour into angel food cake pan or Bundt pan.
This recipe will serve 4 people.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter in 3-quart saucepan.
Place layer of chicken over onion mixture, then add noodles.
Combine liquids and spices and pour over noodles.
Cover and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, for 20 minutes or until noodles are tender.
May garnish with Parmesan cheese.

title: easy filled cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Stir in water and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir in.
Drop by teaspoon.
Place 1/2 teaspoon filling on top.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: angel biscuits(club member: luke robinson)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Stir in oil. Add buttermilk and yeast (dissolved in warm water). Mix with spoon until flour is moist. Cover bowl and place in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: pork chop creole
directions: Heat oil in skillet on medium-high heat.
Brown pork chops on both sides.
Lower heat to medium.
Add onions; cook until wilted. Add all other ingredients except rice.
Cover and cook on low heat for 30 minutes.
Place pork chops on rice.
Cook sauce on high heat for 5 minutes to thicken.
Pour over chops and rice.
Makes 2 servings.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Roll out biscuits like you are making fried pies.
Put chopped apples on half of each.
Sprinkle with cinnamon; crimp edges together.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.

title: garden potato salad
directions: If fresh potatoes are used, cook in jackets until just done. Peel and dice while warm.
Combine onion and vinegar in mixing bowl; let stand a few minutes.
Add mustard, salad oil, sugar and other seasonings.
Add potatoes; toss to coat.
Let chill several hours or overnight.
Add celery, pickle and 3 eggs (diced).
Use 1 egg for garnish.
Blend together mayonnaise and milk; pour over potatoes.
Mix well; garnish.

title: hot holly day punch
directions: Cook together and strain the first 6 ingredients.
Beat together next 4 ingredients.
Combine with first 6 ingredients. Serve warm in mugs with cinnamon sticks.

title: peanut honey slices
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar, honey, shortening, butter and egg. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Shape into strip and roll up to 10 x 2 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch piece.
Wrap and refrigerate at least 8 hours.
Heat oven to 400°.
Cut strip into 1/8-inch slices.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet, 7 to 8 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind mangoes and onions; pour 1 quart boiling water over and let stand for 1 hour.
Drain.
Add salt and mustard seed.
Add sugar and vinegar.
Cook 3 minutes after it starts to boil.
Add celery (cut fine) and boil 1 minute.
Can and seal.

title: hot cheese sandwich
directions: Mix ingredients and set aside.
Trim crust from bread.
Put a layer of cheese mixture on bread, cut into 1/4 slices, then put another layer of cheese on top.
Sprinkle with Italian seasoning mix.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: spicy mustard sauce
directions: Stir together the mustard and vinegar and let set at room temperature overnight.
In a small saucepan, combine the sugar and egg; add mustard mixture.
Stir over low heat until thickened. Can serve hot or cold.
Great on ham, corned beef, pastrami, roast beef; whatever pleases you.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Chop mushrooms and saute with onions in 1/2 stick margarine. Cover rice with mushrooms and onions; add beef broth.
Bake in a 2-quart casserole dish, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: microwave corn pudding(tangier style)
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together until cornstarch is well mixed. Add corn, then eggs. Mix well, then add cream, margarine or butter and vanilla. Mix well. Put in greased baking dish. Cook in microwave on level 7 for 13 minutes. Turn around halfway through cooking. Remove and serve. Enjoy.

title: herb-roasted new potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Toss together all ingredients.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes or until soft. Serve as a side dish with beef, chicken or pork.
Serves 4.

title: cheeseburger pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Meanwhile, press biscuits into 12-inch round on greased baking sheets or 12-inch pizza pan.
Pinch edges of biscuits together to seal.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, in 10-inch skillet over medium heat, cook beef and onion until beef is browned and onion is tender, stirring to separate meat.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in next 5 ingredients; heat through.

title: gobs(cookies)
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients. Add half.
Mix.
Add rest of flour mixture with buttermilk and coffee.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon or tablespoon onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Bring chicken, soup and broth to a boil.
Pour in a sheet pan (12 x 9 x 2-inch).
Make a batter of flour, baking powder, pepper, salt, milk and margarine.
Pour this mixture over chicken in pan. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot sweet and sour pork
directions: Blend cornstarch with water.
Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook 2 to 3 hours on high or 6 to 8 on low.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chili cheese cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients until moist.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: dreamsicle cake
directions: Beat ingredients for 3 minutes.
Pour into 3 pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Punch holes in cake with toothpicks.

title: potato salad with the difference
directions: Cook potatoes in jacket until done.
Allow to cool, then peel by gently pulling skin away with fingers.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise, horseradish and celery seed together in small bowl.

title: green bean wraps
directions: Cut sliced bacon in half and roll 4 to 5 green beans up in each half slice and use toothpicks to hold them together. Put wraps in a large baking dish. Melt butter and add enough brown sugar to butter to make mixture thick. Pour over wraps and bake at 350 for
45 min. to 1 hour.

title: honey-mustard dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.
Cover and chill several hours before using.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: teeny weeny pizza
directions: Combine cheese, bacon, chili sauce and honey in bowl.
Mix well.
Spread on muffins.
Place on baking sheet.
Broil for 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 12 servings.

title: no-cook strawberry jam
directions: Wash and remove stems from strawberries.
Chop berries one layer at a time.
Measure directed amount and place into a large container.
Mix sugar into fruit and let stand for 10 minutes.
Mix water and Sure-Jell in a saucepan.
Bring to a full boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Stir this mixture into the fruit. Stir for 3 minutes.
Pour into glass containers which have been washed and rinsed in boiling water.
Fill to 1/2-inch of tops. Cover at once with tight lids.
Let stand overnight, then store in freezer.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add onion, then buttermilk and finally add beaten egg.
Drop by spoonfuls into the pan in which fish is being fried.
Fry to a golden brown; drain on paper towels. Yields 4 servings.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Whip softened cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice, salt and Cool Whip.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Place in freezer until firm. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: old fashioned bread pudding
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and vanilla well. Add milk.
Heat to bubbly. Pour over bread pieces that have been placed in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Don't stir and let stand for 1 hour.
Make sure all bread is soaked with mixture and all the mixture is soaked up. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: frozen fruit slush
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Place in small plastic glasses and freeze until needed.
When ready to drink let stand 10 minutes, then stir to a slush.

title: cranberry delight
directions: Combine pineapple juice and water; heat to boiling.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Stir in cranberry sauce, lemon juice and nutmeg.
Chill until mixture thickens slightly.
Add sour cream.
Stir until combined.
Fold in pineapple and pecans.
Pour into an 8 cup mold.
Chill until firm.

title: kale soup
directions: Saute onion in oil in a 12 quart pot over medium heat. Add linguica. Cook until

is heated through. Fill pot half way with water. Add fresh kale. Cook over moderate heat until kale is fully cooked and wilted. Add potatoes, salt, pepper, paprika and beans with juice. Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Sift together flour and soda.

Cream together shortening and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition. Beginning and ending with dry ingredients, add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add, mixing well, vanilla, bananas and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and let cool 5 minutes before removing from pan and finish cooling on rack.
Ice with favorite icing.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jello jubilee
directions: Mix Jell-O and cottage cheese (no water).
Add drained fruits and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill overnight or 2 to 3 hours. Serves about 8.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken, tortillas and cheeses. Put small bowl of mixture aside.
Add chicken to remaining mixture.
Spray a large baking pan with nonstick spray.
Put small amount of mixture without chicken in bottom of pan.
Put good amount of chicken mixture on tortillas and roll.
Fill pan.
Put remaining mixture on top.
Sprinkle with shredded cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with more salsa and lettuce, if desired.

title: fruit pie
directions: Cook the first four ingredients over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Pour over the drained fruit.
Mix lightly and pour into a 9-inch pie crust.
Dot with butter on top of fruit.
Cover with crust which has slits cut in.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, turn oven down to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until crust is golden brown.

title: potato nuggets
directions: Heat the butter in a heavy saucepan and add the potatoes and 1 cup of flour.
Stir constantly over moderate heat for about 5 minutes.
Add the eggs and cook for 5 more minutes, continuing to stir.
Remove from the heat and stir in the parsley, pimiento, salt and pepper.
Taste for seasoning.
With 2 teaspoons, shape the mixture into 36 balls.
Dust each one lightly with the remaining flour.

title: toutiere pie
directions: Mix dough for 2 double crust pies; roll out.
Cook meat over low heat in greased pot.
Add mashed potatoes, onions and seasonings to meat and mix well.
Place mixture between raw crusts in 2 separate pie dishes or pans.
Bake at 400° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop on cookie sheets.	Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly grease baking sheet or spray with butter flavored non-stick cooking spray.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a large bowl; mix well.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender or two knives until coarse crumbs form.
Stir in sour cream and milk with a fork until a soft, moist dough forms; stir in Cheddar.
Knead dough on lightly floured surface until no longer sticky, 8-10 times.
Roll dough to a 1/2-thickness.
Cut out biscuits with floured 3-inch round cutter. Place on prepared baking sheet.
Re-roll dough scraps and repeat as needed.
Bake until biscuits are golden, 9-12 minutes.
Serve warm. Makes 10 biscuits.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook onion, add hamburger, salt and pepper.
Cook color out. Add all the rest of the ingredients.
Turn heat down and simmer. Pour over spaghetti.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and beat.
Stir in unwhipped cream, pineapple and bread cubes.
Mix well.
Pour into a lightly greased 8-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: play dough
directions: Mix and place in quart size pan or skillet over medium heat until it pulls away from the sides of the pan.
Turn off heat and roll into a pint size ball.

title: gourmet pasta
directions: Cook noodles; drain and immediately add cream cheese, sour cream and onions.
Saute garlic in small amount of oil, meat and tomato sauce.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Grease a 3-quart Pyrex pan. Spoon 1/2 of noodle mixture, 1/2 grated cheese, 1/2 tomato meat mixture.
Repeat, ending with cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: deluxe pound cake
directions: Let butter and Crisco come to room temperature.
Cream with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating one minute after each egg is added.
Add flavorings.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add to butter mixture alternately with milk, beginning with flour and ending with flour.

title: mom miller's bacon dip
directions: Fry diced bacon almost crisp.
Then place in bowl with paper towels.
Once dry, add bacon, horseradish and garlic salt to cheese.
Mix well.
Add mayo.
Mix until creamy.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in bowl and cover with ice cold water.
Let stand 4 hours.
In pot combine vinegar, sugar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil.
Add drained mixture of cukes, peppers and celery.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Boil jar lids.
Fill jars to ring and seal.
Ready to eat.

title: sesame-ginger chicken
directions: Soak chicken halves in water with salt.
Drain on paper towels. Remove fat and tail along with giblets.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper, paprika and Accent.
Rub Italian dressing in inner part of chicken and place skin side down on broiler.
Broil for approximately 50 minutes.
Turn and broil for additional 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add egg, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Mix in sifted flour, baking soda and salt.
Shape into small balls and flatten with fork.
Bake on cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 375°.

title: sutters beans
directions: Combine beans with liquid in crock-pot.
Brown together the hamburger, bacon and onion. Add to the beans.
Add remaining ingredients and cook in crock-pot until fully heated or put in oven at 300° for 1 to 2 hours.

title: french fried onions
directions: Mix all ingredients, except onions.
Slice onions and separate rings.
Dip in mixture; fry until nice and brown.

title: grilled deer steak
directions: Combine last 5 ingredients and pour over deer steak.
Let stand 24 hours.
Grill.
Do not overcook.

title: salmon puff
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oil.
Drop batter by tablespoon into deep oil heated to 370°.
Cook until golden brown, turning once.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: grape wine
directions: You will also need a one gallon jug and a large 10 cent balloon.

title: puppy chow
directions: Mix chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine in microwave oven.
Pour over Rice Chex.
Pour mixture in jelly roll pan.
Let cool.
Place in large container and work in powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix flour, salt and soda; set aside.
Mix butter and peanut butter.
Add both kinds of sugar.
Mix well, add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour into peanut butter mixture.
Drop dough from a spoon onto baking pan.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 375°.

title: hot polenta
directions: Saute onion in the oil and oleo.
Add ground meat, garlic and peppers.
Cook slowly for three or four minutes.
Add tomatoes and 2 quarts of water.
Add the sugar and salt to taste.
Simmer for about 2 hours.

title: chicken & rice
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender. Break into pieces. Cook rice. Add chicken, soups and seasonings. Add chicken broth for your desired thickness. Cook over heat for 10 minutes.

title: barbecued beef for sandwiches
directions: Combine all ingredients except roast beef and buns.
Cook until onion is tender and ingredients are well blended.
Add meat. Cook 30 minutes more or until meat is seasoned through.
Serve hot on buns.
This is a great way to use up that leftover roast beef.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cover potatoes with water; cook until tender.
Drain and mash. While hot, add oleo and remaining ingredients.
Makes enough for two 9-inch pies.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients all together.
Mix the mayo and sugar; pour over salad.

title: swiss steaks in tomato sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 10-inch nonstick skillet, heat oil. Add onion and celery and saute until onion is translucent. Sprinkle flour over vegetables and cook, stirring constantly for 1 minute.
Gradually stir in water.
Stir in tomatoes and puree. Add broth mix and, stirring constantly, bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and stir in pepper strips.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Boil 2 cups water.
Add jello and dissolve thoroughly.
Add raspberries and applesauce; mix.
Chill until firm.

title: sour cream pound cake or jewish coffee cake
directions: Sift flour before measuring, then resift with baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cream margarine.
Gradually add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Beat in the eggs, then add the flour mixture alternately with the pint of sour cream.
Do not overbeat; beat only until the flour is blended.
Grease and flour a large tube pan.
Turn on the oven at least 10 minutes before putting the cake in.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.

title: celery au gratin
directions: Dice and cook celery until tender.
Drain, but hold 1/2 can water.
Mix ingredients together and put in greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and grated Cheddar cheese.
Heat in oven for 20 minutes at 350°.
Better if made night before and reheated.

title: taco bake
directions: Brown and drain hamburger meat. Add taco seasoning and 2/3 c. water. Let simmer.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Mix jello according to package directions, but use 1/2 cup less water than called for in directions. Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop up and mix ingredients.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in oblong pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs evenly.
Layer chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, coconut and condensed milk.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool, cut in squares.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make into 2 logs. Roll in chili powder and chill.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with the topping.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until set in the middle.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Brown meat lightly with onion.
Cook noodles as directed. Combine all ingredients but bread crumbs and butter.
Pour in casserole.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: greek cabbage salad
directions: Gently toss all ingredients together.
Serves 4.

title: autumn cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat on high speed 3 minutes.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: crock-pot pheasant
directions: Brown pheasant pieces in butter; place in crock-pot or other slow cooker.
Add vegetables to pheasant.
Pour soup over vegetables.
Cook, covered, at low setting for about 6 1/2 hours or until pheasant is tender and vegetables are soft.
Serves 4.

title: seafood fettucini
directions: Melt and saute butter, onions, celery and peppers.
Add flour and stir for 15 minutes, until thick.
Add parsley and seafood and cook for 20 minutes.
Add in and blend half and half, Velveeta, garlic and salt and pepper well.
Cook the fettucini.
Toss mixture with fettucini.
Pour into 3-quart buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: shipwreck
directions: Butter baking dish.
Make a layer of potatoes, salt and pepper, layer of meat 1/2-inch thick, the carrots and last pour over tomato soup.
Repeat in layers until dish is filled.
Bake in oven at 350° until potatoes are done, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: spinach dip(serves 10)
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor until well blended. Serve with assorted raw vegetables.

title: recipe secrets "souperior" meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
On a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
On a large baking pan, shape into a loaf.
Bake for 1 hour, or until done.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: orange salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple.
Place in bowl.
Sprinkle dry Jell-O over contents in bowl.
Stir in cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Layer chicken, peas and carrots.
Add flour to margarine. Gradually add milk and mix well. Pour over layered ingredients. Use an oblong Pyrex dish.
Do not grease dish.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar, cocoa, margarine, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well. Stir in flour, coconut and pecans.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
When cake is done, spread marshmallow cream on hot cake.
Cool before frosting.
Frost with a cream cheese frosting.

title: molasses sauce
directions: Boil together for 20 minutes.
This sauce is good for apples or rice pudding.
Great on hot oatmeal too!

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Coat chops with flour and pepper mixture.
Brown in a small amount of fat.
Place pork chops in a casserole dish and pour soup over.
Cover and bake for 35-40 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: gingered fruit
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill 2 hours.

title: chocolate nut fudge
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan, mix sugar, oleo, Marshmallows Creme and evaporated milk.
Cook and stir to a full all over boil.
Boil and stir over medium heat for 5 minutes, then remove from burner.
Stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Stir in broken nut pieces.
Pour into buttered 8 or 9-inch pan.
Let cool before cutting.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits according to package directions.
When done, stir in butter and milk.
Set aside.

title: ham and cheese whatever
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in an oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pizza bites
directions: Pull biscuits apart.
You can get 3 to 4 from each biscuit. Place on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam or lightly greased.
Prick biscuits with fork.
Place in oven until just slightly brown. Take out of oven and add toppings:
1 teaspoon full of sauce, 1 slice of pepperoni or teaspoonful of sausage.
Top with Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese melts and biscuits are golden brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Cook beef and onion in a large skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble meat; drain well.
Stir in tomato sauce and spaghetti mix.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with sour cream and sprinkle evenly with cheese. Unroll crescent rolls and place on top of cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: orange whip salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except Cool Whip. When mixed well, add the Cool Whip and chill well.

title: block party beans
directions: In a large Dutch oven, brown beef over medium-high heat; drain fat.
Add onion and celery; cook until tender.
Stir in soup, tomato paste and ketchup; simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spoon into large kettle or roaster.
Add all remaining ingredients, draining only the liquid from the wax and green beans.
Stir well.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Yields about 25 servings.

title: kari's caramel squares
directions: Mix together German chocolate cake mix, butter and 1/3 cup sweetened condensed milk.
Press half of mix in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Melt caramels and 1/3 cup sweetened condensed milk.
Stir frequently.
Pour over baked layer.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Sprinkle reserved half of cake mix over the top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut in small squares as these are very rich.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip squares
directions: Melt butter in a 2-quart saucepan and add peanut butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Stir well and add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well and add chocolate chips.
Bake in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Don't overcook.

title: dieter's pineapple muffins
directions: Combine dry milk and bread, made into small pieces.
Mix in the eggs.
Melt margarine; add to ingredients.
Add sweetener, baking powder, extract and pineapple (add some of the juice, too). Pour into Teflon or sprayed muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: ever so easy fruit cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300 degrees.
Generously grease and flour 10 inch tube pan (preferably fluted).
Sift together flour and baking soda and set aside.

title: judy's pecan buttermilk muffins
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine buttermilk, butter and egg.
Add milk mixture all at once to dry ingredients.
Add pecans and mix only enough to combine.
Mixture will be lumpy. Fill well greased muffin pan 2/3 full.
Bake at 400 degrees for 25 minutes.
Makes one dozen.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Stir together peanut butter, oleo and powdered sugar.
Press into buttered 9-inch square pan.
Melt chocolate and 1 tablespoon oleo and spread over peanut butter layer.
Set in refrigerator 10 minutes to set chocolate.
Cut into small squares.

title: crock-pot beans
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix all ingredients well.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 3 to 5 hours.

title: leona's biscuits
directions: Cut the oleo into the dry ingredients and slowly add in the milk.
Stir and knead and put on a floured board.
Cut with biscuit cutter and place in lightly greased baking pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: french hot chocolate
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan over low heat, heat chocolate and corn syrup until chocolate is melted and smooth.
Stir occasionally (a double boiler may be used).
Cover and refrigerate until mixture is cool (30 minutes).
Stir in vanilla.
Heat milk over medium-low heat until very hot.
Do not boil!
In small bowl, mix whipping cream and chocolate mixture until soft peaks form (medium-low speed).
Pour milk into coffeepot.
Spoon equal amounts of whip cream mixture into 8 warmed coffee cups, gently pour hot milk mixture into cups and serve.

title: linda's crab salad
directions: Mix carefully. Do not break up the meat chunks. Serve stuffed in tomatoes with crackers.

title: stuffed pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease rectangular 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Cook and stir sausage and ground beef until brown and drain.
Set aside.

title: cherry dream bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine cake mix, 6 tablespoons of margarine and 1 cup rolled oats.
Mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup for topping.

title: custard pie
directions: Dilute milk with hot water.
Beat eggs very slightly and add to milk.
Add salt and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
This custard will never get runny or weep if you beat the eggs very slightly.

title: terrora campground chicken and rice
directions: Saute
the
ingredients in 1 tablespoon Weight Watchers reduced calorie
margarine.
Add
one
ounce
can of sliced mushrooms (with
liquid),
cans of Swanson boned chicken, 1 cup of
Minute
rice, 1 cup of boiling water and 1 envelope of Herb-Ox chicken bouillon seasoning.
Season with oregano, red pepper, basil,
garlic,
salt
and pepper to taste.
Cover and allow to stand for 5 minutes.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Let meat soak overnight in fajita spices in a covered dish in refrigerator.
Brown the onion and peppers in a large skillet. Then brown meat after adding Accent.
Add the tomato paste and salsa.
Let simmer for several hours (to get tomato paste flavor cooked out); stir occasionally.
Place dough on greased pan and ladle on sauce.
Then add cheese toppings.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 425°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick butter, mix in crumbs and granulated sugar.
Press into 9 X 12 in pan.
Beat powdered sugar, eggs and 1 stick softened butter for 10-12 minutes.
Spread over crumbs.
Slice 5 bananas over this.
Drain pineapple and spread over bananas.
Spread cool whip over crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate overnight for best results.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Experiment!
This makes a great cheese bread, too!
This is best eaten soon after baking, as the yeast in the beer tends to ferment.

title: apple-raisin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottoms only of 2 loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Beat eggs, oil, apples, sugar and vanilla on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally, for 1 minute.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Beat on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally, until moistened, about 15 seconds.
Beat on medium speed 45 seconds.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Spread in pans.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Defrost broccoli.
Melt oleo in a large saucepan.
Add eggs, cornbread mix, cottage cheese and broccoli.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan (no need to grease pan) for 25 minutes at 400°.

title: amish friendship bread
directions: Do not use metal spoon or metal utensils.

title: eagle brand pound cake
directions: Let eggs and butter stand until they are room temperature (overnight).
Blend butter and sugar well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a large tube pan.
Preheat oven to 250°.
Bake for 2 to 2 1/2 hours. More than likely it will take the 2 1/2 hours.
May take longer than 2 1/2 hours.

title: bacon cheddar oven pancake
directions: Combine pancake mix, sugar, milk and syrup in a bowl.
Mix well. Stir in 1/4 cup cheese.
Pour into greased pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until light brown. Sprinkle with bacon and 1/4 cup cheese. Bake until cheese melts.
Cut into wedges. Serve with syrup.
Yields 2 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix honey, shortening and eggs together.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Stir all together. Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in 3 bread pans at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: sherried sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water with salt just until tender; drain.
In saucepan, combine brown sugar, cornstarch and salt. Blend in orange peel and orange juice; add raisins.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until thickened and bubbly. Cook 1 minute more, add butter, sherry and walnuts.
Stir until butter melts.
Pour over potatoes; bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: burritos
directions: Wrap tortillas in foil; place in 350° oven for five minutes to soften.
Cook ground beef and onion until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain.
Stir in beans, undrained tomatoes and chili powder.
Simmer, uncovered, for about five minutes or desired consistency.
Spoon onto tortilla; top with cheese if desired. Fold opposite sides in.
Tuck in bottom end.
Put in oven until cheese melts.

title: shish-kabob (laham mishwee)
directions: Soak the meat overnight in the Italian Dressing.
Add red wine and vinegar also.
Cut onions into 8 pieces, cut tomatoes into 9 or 10 pieces.
Cut green peppers into 12 pieces.
Put meat on the skewers, adding pieces of onion, tomato and green pepper between every 2 to 3 cubes of meat.
Cook to taste (rare, medium or well) on the grill and enjoy!

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits in water until done.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: spice seasoning mix
directions: Combine ingredients.
Makes 6 tablespoons mix.
Good seasoning for meats, stews or soups in camp cooking.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Add flour enough to thicken to roll out dough. Cut with cookie cutter according to the seasons. Bake 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Frost the baked cookies with 7 minute frosting.

title: ham and cauliflower casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepot, cook cauliflower. Drain well.
Meanwhile, in large saucepan melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper; add milk and onion.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in cheese until melted. Gently fold in ham, mushrooms and cauliflower.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Crackers and 1 tablespoon melted butter can be sprinkled on top.
Bake at 350° until heated through, about 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: potted shrimp(cornish)
directions: Heat butter and add the prepared shrimp.
Add wine and other ingredients.
Heat gently but do not boil.
Pot and eat cold with green salad.

title: potato skins
directions: Go to your favorite store.
Pick out your favorite variety of M&M's (almond M&M's are my personal favorite).
Take your M&M's home and put them in a pretty bowl.
Eat 'em all up.
Think of me...the original M&M.

title: mexican nacho casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
While meat is browning, stir in taco seasoning.
Dice pepper and tomato.
Mix 1/2 of the browned ground beef and the pepper and tomato in a bowl.
Empty 1/2 of the taco sauce into this mixture.
Empty the other 1/2 of the taco sauce into remaining ground beef; stir.
Empty meat mixture with peppers and tomatoes into casserole dish.
Put one layer of crumbled nacho chips on top.
Next put remaining meat mixture on top of the nacho chips.
Finally, put another layer of nachos on top and bake for 10 minutes in a 360° oven.

title: callaloo soup
directions: Remove thick stems of leaves, chop roughly and put into saucepan with all ingredients except okras and crab.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender.
Add okras; cook for 8 minutes. Remove pepper and blend.
Add crab, reheat and adjust seasonings. Serve piping hot with slices of avocado pear and hot bread.

title: filled doughnuts
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Add sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add sour milk, vinegar and butter.
Blend.
Roll 1/4-inch thick. Place filling in cut circles. Fold dough over filling.
Seal edges.
Fry in deep fat (350°).
Drain.

title: potato patties
directions: Use hands to mix all together.
Roll into small balls and then mash flat.
Fry in deep fat until brown.

title: scalloped carrots
directions: Make a white sauce of butter, flour and milk; add salt, pepper, grated cheese and onion.
In a casserole place a layer of carrots alternately with white sauce until dish is full.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake until bacon is crisp.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Make a paste by creaming the butter and flour together.
Heat milk in saucepan; add paste in small pieces, stirring constantly, then add chicken broth and cook over medium heat, stirring, until thickened.
Saut onion in small skillet with an additional tablespoon butter and add to creamed mixture.
Add baked potatoes; mix and taste for seasoning.
Serve in bowls topped with bacon, chopped green onion and grated cheese.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: play dough
directions: Mix and cook over medium heat for 3 minutes.
Keep in airtight container.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and celery. Add remaining ingredients. Boil; turn heat down to low and cover. Simmer for 15 or 20 minutes. Add 1 cup shredded cheese on top.

title: old-fashioned apple crisp pie
directions: Grease Pyrex dish with margarine.
Pour sliced apples into dish.
Mix ingredients and put on top of apples.
Mixture will melt nicely on pie top.
Cook pie until top is browned.
Top with vanilla ice cream.
Delicious!

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: snapper roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine first 4 seasonings, rub fish with half of this mix. Heat butter in large skillet over medium heat, add onions, celery and bell pepper, cooking until soft. Add rest of seasonings and shrimp. Cook until shrimp are pink, add bread crumbs and stir to mix. Remove from heat and let cool. Combine egg and parmesan, add to shrimp mixture and stir. Transfer to a bowl, cover and chill for about 30 minutes. Spoon equal amounts of the mixture on each filet and roll up jelly roll style, secure with a tooth pick. Place roll-ups in shallow baking pan, sprinkle with chicken broth and bake until fish flakes easily with fork, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix salt and soda together and set aside.
Cook first 3 ingredients to a hard ball stage.
Add peanuts, cook to a hard crack stage (350° on a candy thermometer).
Remove from heat.
Add melted oleo and salt and soda mixture, stir quickly and pour in sheet pans.
Let cool and crack into chunks.

title: orange-lemon tea fizz
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bag; let brew 5 minutes.
Remove bag; cool slightly, then pour into pitcher.
Stir in rest of ingredients; serve over ice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: excellent roast
directions: Place roast on a large piece of foil.
Brush freely with A.1. sauce.
Over this pour the onion soup mix.
Top with the mushroom soup.
Seal foil tightly.
Bake at 325° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: philly cheese ball
directions: Mix thoroughly and serve with crackers.

title: creole sauce
directions: Heat oil; cook onion, green pepper and mushrooms over low heat about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes and seasonings; cook until sauce is thick, about 40 minutes.
Use with meat, fish or poultry.
Yield: about 2 1/2 cups.

title: broccoli different
directions: Thaw broccoli, but do not cook.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish and sprinkle with salt.
Combine cream-style corn, milk and eggs and stir.
Pour over broccoli.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° until firm and broccoli is tender, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Beat in egg.
Add onion and bell pepper.
Stir in milk and mix well.
Drop small balls of the mixture into hot, deep fat.
Fry until golden brown.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine; press into a 9-inch square dish. Combine softened cream cheese, sugar, milk and 1/2 teaspoon extract.
Mix well.
Spread mixture over crust and sprinkle with nuts.
Combine pie filling with 1/2 teaspoon almond extract and spread over cream.
Chill, then munch!

title: no bake chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Mix sugar and syrup in a 3-quart saucepan on stove or 3-quart Corning Ware for microwave.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring frequently, until it bubbles.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Add Rice Krispies.
Stir until blended.
Press mixture into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips together in microwave dish until blended and spread over top.
Cool until firm. Cut into squares.
Yields 48 bars.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat ingredients until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Test for doneness. For a delicious raisin cake fold in 1 cup raisins.
Will keep fresh for two weeks if wrapped.
Good toasted.

title: meat loaf
directions: Cook another 15 or 20 minutes.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients until dough sticks together.
Roll into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Bake about 25 minutes. Drain on paper towels.
Makes about 75.

title: reese's bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler and spread on top of graham cracker mix.
Chill in refrigerator.
Cut into bars. Enjoy.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into 4 portions.
Divide flour into equal portions, combine 1 portion with salt and set aside 2 tablespoons.

Pound remaining flour into meat; brown on both sides in heated oil. Place meat in baking dish; blend reserved flour with drippings in skillet; add tomatoes, broth, celery, carrots, onion and Worcestershire.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens. Pour over meat; cover and bake in a 350° oven until meat is tender (1 to 2 hours).
Melt cheese on top.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add milk gradually and blend until smooth.
Knead dough for 2 minutes.
Divide dough into 4 pieces. Take one section and roll out to a round shape about 8 1/2 inches in diameter.
If thin tortillas are desired, divide into 5 pieces.

title: hearty dip
directions: Brown
the
beef in a skillet and stir in the remaining ingredients.
Blend
well.
Bring
to
a
boil then reduce the heat.
Cover
and simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Serve hot with corn chips.
Makes 2 cups of dip.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix butter, sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour along with milk and with baking powder.
Add flavor.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until done.

title: tex-mex skillet
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Add tomatoes, beans, rice, chili powder, cumin and 1 cup of water. Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, 20 minutes or until rice is tender. Top with cheese.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake sugar dough as directed on can.
Spread on pizza pan or cookie sheet and bake.
Let cool completely.
Mix cheese and sugar until smooth. Slice bananas and soak in pineapple juice 10 to 15 minutes (do apples same way).
Spread cream cheese mixture on cooled cookie crust like icing.
Put bananas, pineapple, apples and other fruit on and sprinkle with
nuts.
Pur it in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Cook all together on top of stove until thick and pour into baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 1 hour, until zucchini is tender and rice is done.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir. Pour peaches and the juice on top of batter.
Bake until brown or until a toothpick comes out clean (about 30 minutes).

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Using Pam saute eggplant, onion and green pepper.
Transfer to casserole dish.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Mix and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: funeral pie(real old recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line pie pan with crust.

title: beer-braised loin of pork
directions: Brown pork loin well on all sides in kettle or Dutch oven; remove from pan.
(Or brown in a large, heavy roasting pan on surface burners.)
Saute onions and carrots in pork drippings until soft.
Stir in beer, salt, pepper and bay leaf (if substituting butter beans for carrots, add them at this point). Return pork to kettle and cover.
(If using roasting pan, cover tightly with aluminum foil.)
Braise in a 350° oven for 2 hours, or until pork is tender when pierced with two-tined fork.
Place pork on a platter and keep warm.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Place chicken in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top with mixed vegetables and potatoes.
Mix cream of chicken soup, chicken broth, salt and pepper to taste and cornstarch.
Pour mixture over vegetables.

title: jello and pudding dessert
directions: Cook Jell-O as directed on box.
Pour Jell-O into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass dish.
Place in refrigerator until firm.
Mix instant pudding.
Place pudding on top of firm Jell-O.
Slice bananas and place on top of pudding.
Spread Cool Whip over bananas.
Drain cherries and arrange decoratively on top of Cool Whip.
Chill in refrigerator (1 to 2 hours).

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, vanilla, oil and eggs; mix well and add flour. Combine remaining ingredients.
Mix all together and bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pickled beets
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and water in a saucepan.
Boil until sugar dissolves, then pour over beets.
Makes 3 pints.
Let set a few days before eating.

title: no worms apple pie
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar in a gallon plastic jug.
Hang in tree when tree is in blossom.
Leave in tree all summer.
Magic, no worms come in fall.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Grease two 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pans.
In large mixing bowl, stir flour, brown sugar, baking soda and salt.
In mixing bowl, combine egg, buttermilk, oil and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients; mix well.
Toss rhubarb with 2 tablespoons flour; fold rhubarb into batter.
Pour into pans.
Dot each loaf with butter and sprinkle with 2 to 3 teaspoons sugar.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pans. Remove.

title: finger pudding paint
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions, spoon
pudding into small bowls and let the kids paint
on paper or plates. They can lick and paint at the same time. (Have your cam corder handy.) Add food coloring to vanilla pudding for different colors.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve orange and lemon jello in boiling water.
Add bananas and marshmallows while hot.
After marshmallows melt (or almost melt), add cold water.
Pour into oblong baking dish; let set until firm.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients and pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Recipe yields 8 servings.

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: In small bowl, combine crushed croutons and set aside.
In medium mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, 2 tablespoons margarine and seasoning; mix well.
Stir in chicken and mushrooms.
Set aside.

title: mary's corn casserole
directions: Combine first six ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine cornmeal and remaining ingredients; stir into corn mixture.
Pour into a lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients except shrimp.
Add shrimp. Chill.
Use regular potato chips for dipping.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Combine butter, sugar, salt, flour and eggs.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook over hot water until thick and smooth. Add flavoring and let cool, then add bananas. Pour into baked pastry shell.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix well
and
put on top of apples.
Bake until apples are tender and crust is brown.	Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal chippers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla until creamy.
Gradually add combined flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients.

title: lemon-vegetable salad
directions: Combine jello and hot water.
Add cold water.
Beat in salad dressing.
Fold in remaining ingredients and chill until set.
May use a bowl or mold.

title: pecan pie with chips
directions: Sprinkle pecans and chocolate evenly on bottom of pie crust. Combine eggs, butter, Karo, sugar and vanilla; mix until light and fluffy.
Pour over pecan and chocolate layer.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350° or until pie is golden.

title: sweet hot mustard
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and mix well.
Let stand 3 to 4 hours at room temperature.
Put mixture in doubler boiler.
Beat eggs and add slowly to mixture in double boiler.
Cook on low heat until thick.
Keep in fridge.
Makes 1 quart.

title: almond joy cake
directions: While cake is baking, mix 1 cup milk and sugar.
Bring to rapid boil; remove from heat and add marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved. Add coconut and pour over cake.
In another pan, mix sugar, 1/2 cup milk and oleo.
Heat to rapid boil; remove from heat and add chocolate chips and pecans.
Stir to mix and spread over top of coconut mixture.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place hash brown potatoes in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix all ingredients together and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt 2/3 of the margarine in a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Empty in hash browns.
Sprinkle onion on top.
Sprinkle on the shredded cheese.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together.
Stir in water to make dough like.
Spoon onto pan.
Bake until brown, 20 to 30 minutes, at 350°.

title: chili con queso
directions: Saute onions in shortening until transparent.
Add tomatoes, chilies, salt and pepper to onions.
Simmer slowly until well blended.
Add cheese to hot sauce.
Blend.
Thin with tomato juice if too thick.
Serve as dip for corn tostados.

title: oven beef soup
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven, over medium-high heat in hot oil, cook 1/2 of beef until brown, stirring often.
Remove; set aside. Repeat with remaining beef.
Spoon off fat.

title: lemon square gems
directions: Mix together flour and margarine (use a pastry blender).
Stir in nuts.
Press mixture in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: baked dijon chicken
directions: Combine garlic, green onions, mustard, wine, lemon juice, tarragon and pepper to make sauce.
Place chicken in the sauce, turning to coat both sides.
Spray a baking dish lightly with olive oil or Pam.
Place chicken breast in baking dish.
Spoon a little of the sauce over the chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, depending on the thickness of chicken breast.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix well the first 3 ingredients, then blend in the rest. Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean when punched in center.
Top with chocolate fudge frosting.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Soften and cream the first 3 ingredients. Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Check with knife.

title: bleu cheese dip
directions: Cream the cheeses and sour cream.
Mix in other ingredients. Chill and serve with chips.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and milk.
Add all other ingredients, except the crabmeat and Cheddar cheese.
Fold in crabmeat.
Put in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: corn pudding
directions: Cut off ears of tender corn or use canned corn if desired. Stir all ingredients together and put in casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: palmer creme pie
directions: Mix ingredients (except dream whip) in saucepan and cook until smooth and thick.
Cool overnight or several hours.
Whip prepared dream whip until stiff and add to the cooked mixture. Beat until smooth.
Pour into baked shells.
Decorate tops with chocolate curls or nuts.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender (no salt or pepper).
Drain.
Add green pepper and onion.
Put aside.

title: hi ho cherry-o pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar and almond extract.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crust and pour pie filling on top. Refrigerate, covered, for 12 hours or overnight.

title: wanda's corn dogs
directions: Mix
flour,
meal,
sugar,
mustard and onion together. Combine
egg
and milk; mix with dry ingredients.
Roll frankfurters in dough mixture.
Fry in deep fat until golden brown. Yields 6 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Place ingredients in a bowl in order listed.
Cover tightly. Chill all day.
Toss before serving.

title: creamy pesto
directions: Wash and dry basil.
Place in food processor.
Chop basil. Add the next 4 ingredients.
Process until smooth.
With machine on, add oil slowly in a thin stream.
Great on pasta.
Keeps for 10 days.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Beat first 7 ingredients and pour into ungreased 9 x 13 cake pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix over batter. Pour melted butter over cake mix. Sprinkle with nuts. Bake 1 hour, no longer, at 350°.

title: ann landers' meat loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients
thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan. Cover with bacon strips (optional).
Pour the can of tomato sauce over top.
Bake one hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: wild ducks in orange sauce
directions: Soak ducks in cold water with baking soda.
Drain ducks and place in iron Dutch oven with apple and onion in cavity.
Season with salt and pepper and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Baste occasionally with melted butter.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef; pour off grease.
Put all ingredients in 5-quart pan.
Cook on medium heat for 1 hour.
Serve over your favorite pasta.

title: "jessi's" hot dogs
directions: Mix mustard and preserves together; pour over hot dogs.
Cook in microwave until hot and sauce bubbles.
Let set for a few minutes before serving.

title: play dough
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour and salt.
Keep stirring while gradually adding oil and approximately 3/4 cup water.
Add the water very slowly at the end so the mixture doesn't get too wet. Knead together until you obtain a consistency similar to bread dough.
Store in a tightly closed plastic bag in the refrigerator. If it is too sticky the next time, roll it in flour and re-knead it.

title: peanut butter krispie bar
directions: Combine first three ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies.
Spread mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips together and pour over Krispie mixture.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: In 1-quart shallow casserole, combine peaches, sugar, 1 tablespoon baking mix and cinnamon.
In medium bowl, mix remaining 2/3 cup baking mix with brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture is size of small peas.
Stir in milk until moistened.
Drop by spoonfuls onto peaches.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: e-z apple crunch
directions: Grease a large 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with margarine or butter. Pour both cans of pie filling in pan. Sprinkle cake mix evenly over apples.
Melt butter and pour over mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grape jelly
directions: Combine grape juice and Sure-Jell in sauce pot.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Stir in sugar and return to a rolling boil.
Boil hard for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and put into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: stuffed meatballs
directions: Prepare 1 cup stuffing according to package directions.
Mix ground chuck with milk and divide into six patties, flattening to circles on waxed paper.
Spoon stuffing into center of each, dividing evenly.
Draw edges of patty over stuffing and seal into a ball with palm of hand.
Place balls into 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Pour off drippings.
Combine Worcestershire sauce, soup and catsup in a saucepan.
Heat until bubbly.
Pour over meatballs and return to oven for 15 more minutes.
Makes six servings.

title: broccoli-cheese chicken
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot margarine, cook chicken 10 minutes or until browned on both sides.
Remove chicken and set aside.

title: the nittany lion artichoke dip
directions: Butter a 1-quart casserole and break up (drained) artichoke hearts into the casserole.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients. Top with extra Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve hot with crackers.
This recipe was given to us by a Penn State Alumni.

title: big dutch baby
directions: To make this fluffy pancake you first must have the correct pan.
Mine is a heavy cast-iron 3 1/2-quart casserole with sloping sides.
First heat the pan with butter at 425° until butter is melted.
Then in a blender combine eggs, milk and flour.
Pour batter into hot melted butter.
Don't peek for 20 to 25 minutes. This makes an easy weekend breakfast served with lemon juice and powdered sugar or maple syrup.

title: hilton style hawaiian potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and boil whole; test with fork after 20 to 30 minutes.
Dump hot; chill with cold water.
Slice like French fries, then dice.
Stir salt, pepper and garlic powder into potatoes.
Mix in mayonnaise and white onions.
Mix in hard-boiled eggs (hold 2 egg yolks to the side and dice the balance).
Toss and mix.
Put onto large platter and shape into an oval shape like 1/2 of a watermelon.
Spread 2 tablespoons mayonnaise over shape.

title: swedish cake
directions: Mix by hand.
Bake in long dish.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mince cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into a tube pan and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours on the top rack of the oven.

title: fruit sorbet
directions: Put fruit, sugar, water and lemon juice into blender or food processor.
(Ask an adult for help or permission to use the blender or food processor.)
Blend until it's all slushy.
Pour the mixture into a plastic container.
Place the mixture in the freezer for about an hour.

title: dreamsicle
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Add ice or water to make 2 cups and let sit for 5 minutes.
With mixer, add vanilla pudding.
Add drained oranges and fold into Cool Whip.

title: grated apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl.
Add apples and toss gently.
Stir in egg and butter.
Spoon mixture into pastry shell.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for 50 minutes.

title: fried spaghetti pie
directions: Prepare spaghetti according to package instructions, using 2 teaspoons salt, boiling water and 1 tablespoon of margarine.
Do not add herb and spice mix.
Cool spaghetti to room temperature and stir in package of grated Parmesan cheese, eggs, parsley and 1/4 teaspoon of salt and pepper.

title: no bake orange cookies
directions: Crush vanilla wafers (fine); orange juice should be mushy. Heat confectioners sugar and margarine together and beat until light and fluffy.
Add crushed wafers and orange juice.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
If too moist, add more wafers.
Roll small balls in coconut.

title: dried beef ball
directions: Combine horseradish and cream cheese and mix by hand.
Shred dried beef and add to cream cheese mixture.
Form into a ball. Refrigerate overnight.
Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes before serving.
Serve with various kinds of crackers.

title: sausage and mushrooms
directions: Brown sausage on cookie sheet in oven at 350°.
Slice mushrooms and fry with onion and seasonings.
Remove sausage when browned. Cool and slice.
Add to mushroom mixture and serve.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in blender, remove and set aside.
In blender, combine pudding and milk.
In another container, blend cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Combine the two mixtures together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer cream mixture with cookies, beginning and ending with cookies.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and pepper in butter.
Mix together tuna with juice, mushroom soup, chow mein noodles and salted peanuts. Bake uncovered at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Serve with remaining noodles.

title: broccoli and cheese
directions: Saute onions and pepper in margarine until tender. Add cheese spread, cooked rice, broccoli and soup. Stir until cheese is melted. Pour into an 8 x 8-inch buttered baking dish. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple salad
directions: Peel apples.
Mix all other ingredients.
Serve within 1 hour.

title: cinnamon flop(sour cream coffee cake)
directions: In medium bowl, beat egg until frothy; beat in sugar and melted butter.
Cream until fluffy.
Add sour cream or buttermilk and vanilla; blend well.
Sift the 1 1/2 cups flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda together; add to creamed mixture. Blend well.
Pour into greased 8-inch square baking pan and set aside.

title: lemon cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl; beat with electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Pour into prepared Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: black bean salsa
directions: Stir together all ingredients at least one hour before serving.
Store in refrigerator.
Serve with chips or as a side dish.

title: cinnamon-raisin 9-grain cereal
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil.
Stir in 9-grain cereal. After 2 minutes, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 15 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with butter and brown sugar or honey.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine crumbled bacon, broccoli and onion.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar together in small bowl.
Pour over broccoli. Refrigerate overnight.

title: corn salad(one serving)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
One serving is 1 bread, 1/8 vegetable, 2 fats.

title: dr. martin's mix
directions: Brown sausage in electric skillet; drain fat.
Add other ingredients; cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: black bean soup
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Place mixture in large saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.
Each serving can be garnished with teaspoon of fat-free sour cream.
Yields 3 servings.
Has 170 calories, less than 1 g. fat. Goood!

title: chocolate pie
directions: Add sugar, cocoa, salt and flour together; mix well.
Beat egg yolks.
Add milk, mixing thoroughly.
Add wet ingredients to dry ingredients; mix well, being sure there are no dry lumps in mixture.
Add vanilla; cook in heavy skillet or saucepan over direct heat until thick.
Cool and place in baked pie shell. Cover with meringue; brown slightly in oven.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in shallow greased baking dish.
Cover with soup.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover tightly with foil. Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
Uncover; pour off gravy and brown chicken quickly under broiler.
Serve gravy with rice.

title: orange coconut ring
directions: Melt 1/4 cup of the butter in 9-inch ring mold.
Add marmalade and coconut; mix well and spread evenly.
In large mixer bowl, combine sugar, eggs and 1/2 cup butter.
Blend well at lowest speed of mixer.
Add flour, baking powder and salt alternately with milk and orange extract; blend thoroughly at lowest speed of mixer.
Spoon batter evenly over marmalade mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes; invert onto serving plate. If desired, serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Note:

This recipe is good for taking to covered dish brunch. Reduce cooking time to 45 minutes and when done, remove from oven and cover with foil and then wrap in several thicknesses of newspaper and it will stay warm for an hour.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in flour and nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Mix
together
flour,
sugar and salt.	Add Crisco; mix until crumbly.
Beat together in small bowl, vinegar, egg and ice water; mix well.
Divide dough into 5 balls.
Wrap each in plastic
wrap; chill.
To
use
later,
freeze.
This freezes well and is always ready.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Line pie pan with pastry.
Combine corn syrup and sugar.
Add eggs, salt, butter and vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter until filling is smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for an additional 30 to 35 minutes.
Filling in center will be soft when pie is removed.
Chill.

title: chinese new year cookies
directions: Melt chips together in double boiler.
Stir in chow mein noodles and peanuts.
Drop onto wax paper and chill.

title: frosting for many cakes
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat to 270° to 290° on candy thermometer, soft crack stage; remove from heat.
Pour over egg whites.
Beat well.
May add mashed bananas for banana cake, drained crushed pineapple for pineapple cake, coconut for coconut cake and chopped pecans for pecan cake. Yield:
Enough for 3 layer cake, 12 servings.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: In a food processor or by hand, coarsely chop the cabbage and carrot.
In a small bowl, combine the mayonnaise, milk, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Stir into the cabbage mixture.
Chill until serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: praline squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lay out crackers so they touch each other in an ungreased 10 x 15-inch baking pan. Put the butter and brown sugar in a small saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat; cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes only. Pour mixture over graham crackers. Bake for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and let cool for 2 minutes only! Cut into squares while still warm. Store, tightly covered. Refrigerate. Keeps well.

title: fried peppers
directions: Use skillet and add oil.
Put all ingredients in skillet and cook to desired crispness.

title: nalesniki(crepes)
directions: Beat eggs; set aside.
Mix sugar, salt and flour well together and stir quickly into beaten eggs.
Add milk and beat again hard. Fill crepe pan with a little oil; add batter to hot skillet and lightly brown crepes.
Make them paper thin but only cook one side.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add lemon juice.
Chop cucumber, onion and almonds fine.
Add to jello.
Add cottage cheese and salad dressing.
Pour into greased mold; let set.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix soups, cheese and chicken broth. Add onion, tortillas (broken into pieces) and green chilies (chopped).
Bake in 2-quart casserole at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: strawberry preserves
