directions: Put 1/2 of sugar over berries and cook for 20 minutes.
Add lemon juice and rest of sugar.
Cook 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls(child snack recipe)
directions: Crush graham crackers until fine.
Soften peanut butter.
Mix crackers and peanut butter together.
Sweeten with Equal if desired.
Roll into balls and freeze.

title: sweet and sour green beans(serves 50)
directions: Heat sugar, oil and vinegar.
Pour over drained green beans and sliced onions.
Marinate overnight.
To serve, drain and serve cold.

title: green enchiladas
directions: *If using large tortillas, add another can of soup and extra cheese.

title: dirt dessert
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Set aside. Mix Cool Whip, pudding and milk in a large bowl.
Add cream mixture.
Crumble Oreo cookies in food processor.
Layer cookies, then cream mix, cookies, cream mix, then cookies in plastic flowerpot.
End with cookies.
Serve with trowel.
You may put plastic flowers in pot for decoration.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix together ground beef, salt, pepper and egg.
Mix in the rice.
Cook cabbage leaves in boiling salt water until just tender. Drain.

title: zippy beef casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook and stir meat until brown.
Drain fat.
Cook macaroni as directed on package.
In an ungreased 2-quart casserole dish, mix all ingredients, except potato chips. Cover and bake for 40 minutes.
Uncover.
Sprinkle with chips. Bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese danish
directions: Pat out onto a 9 x 13-inch pan the first package of crescent rolls.
Mix egg yolk, cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice.
Pour over rolls.
Put the second package of rolls on cheese mixture.
Beat egg whites and brush on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Put cookies in blender or use rolling pin.
Cream the oleo, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Mix pudding and milk.
Add whipped cream and combine all ingredients except cookies.
Layer cookies and cream filling in flowerpot or cake pan.
Makes enough for about two 6-inch pots.
Line pots with freezer bags, 1/2 gallon size.

title: egg noodle tuna bake
directions: Combine eggs and soup.
Add tuna, olives, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook noodles.
Combine noodles and sauce mixture.
Place in a 1-quart casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: grandma's mincemeat
directions: May add some tart jelly, if desired.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, milk and margarine.
Pour into baking dish.
Add sliced peaches with juice.
Bake at 375° until brown on top.
Five minutes before it is done, sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, depending on thickness or until brown or done.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add all canned ingredients, undrained. Add onion.
You may want to add 1 can water.
Serve with tortilla chips, shredded cheese and sour cream.

title: sour cream candle pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease and flour 9 x 3-inch spring-form pan with removable bottom.
Fill 6 ounce empty clean juice can, label removed, with dried beans.
Place in middle of prepared pan.
Combine flour, baking powder and baking soda in small bowl.
Beat butter and sugar in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in bourbon, rind and vanilla.
Alternately beat in sour cream with dry ingredients, until well blended.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Place all, except Certo, in a granite pan.
Cook over high heat, stirring constantly.
Bring to a full boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat; add Certo.
Stir well.
Skim.
Pour into glasses or jars and seal.
Paraffin may be melted and poured on top to seal if jars do not have lids.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Prepare chilies by opening and washing off seeds and juice. Butter casserole.
Place a layer of peppers, cheese, etc., ending with a layer of cheese on top.
Mix other ingredients and pour over.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Take out of oven and let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: cold salmon mousse(appetizer or light entree)
directions: Drain salmon and discard bones.
Mash well with a fork and combine with lemon juice, salt and cayenne.
Sprinkle gelatin over cold water to soften.
Put in a pan of boiling water in double boiler and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add to salmon mix, then add mayonnaise and whipped cream.
Pour into a 1-quart mold and chill until firm.
Unmold on a cold serving platter and garnish with watercress and deviled eggs.

title: grits and greens
directions: Bring chicken broth and heavy cream to a boil. Add the grits and cook. Then add parmesan cheese, tomatoes, crisp bacon and collard greens.

title: hawaiian pineapple cheese pie
directions: Whip softened cream cheese and sugar well.
Fold in the whipped cream, then the well drained pineapple. Spoon into pie shell.
Chill thoroughly about 2 hours, until filling is set. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: indonesian pork roast
directions: Sear roast on all sides in hot oil.
Drain of excess fat. Combine next 6 ingredients in a measuring cup and add to roast. Cover and simmer 2 1/2 hours.
(works well in oven too!)
Serve with fried rice and white rice.

title: crabmeat and wild rice
directions: Add a pinch of garlic salt and a little Tabasco sauce.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: italian delight
directions: Cook spaghetti, drain, rinse and set asid.e
Brown ground beef and drain excess fat.
Saute margarine, chopped onion and chopped bell pepper.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, until hot throughout. Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar; beat again.
Add oil and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add these all together.
Add apples and nuts last.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: creamy veggie combo
directions: Place veggies in a 9 x 13-inch buttered casserole dish.
Melt the butter in saucepan.
To this add the Pepperidge Farm dressing and the grated cheese.
Beat the eggs, soup, mayo, onion and salt and pepper together; pour mixture over the top of the veggies. Cover with dressing mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: paul bunyan burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients and then add beef.
Makes 18 burgers.

title: cranberry pecan salad
directions: Mix dry jellos in 7 X 10 glass baking dish.
Add hot water, mix until dissolved.
Add cranberries, stir thoroughly.
Add pineapple, stir well.
Add orange juice, celery and pecans.
Let set.

title: old fashioned egg custard
directions: Warm milk. Sift salt and sugar together. Add to milk. Beat eggs slightly and add to milk mixture. Pour into slightly baked crust. Cover with nutmeg. Bake until knife placed into pie comes out clean. Makes 2 pies.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix together cabbage, water and salt.
Let stand at least 1 hour.
Drain.
Mix sugar and vinegar; bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage; mix well.
Pack and freeze.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
In medium saucepan, beat egg yolks; add 1/2 cup of sugar, pumpkin, cream, cinnamon and salt. Cook until custard consistency (about 8 minutes), stirring constantly.
Add dissolved gelatin to hot mixture.
Cool in refrigerator.
Beat egg whites stiff and add 1/2 cup of sugar. When gelatin mixture begins to thicken, fold in egg whites.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Put in refrigerator.
When set, top with whipped cream.

title: clam dip
directions: Soften cheese with fork; add clams and enough juice for desired consistency, then add seasonings.
Chill overnight.

title: green pea salad
directions: Mix everything together, except peas.
Add peas, chill, serve and enjoy!

title: old-time fruit cake
directions: Heat oven to 275°.
Line 2 loaf pans with brown paper (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch).
Mix sugar, molasses and eggs.
Beat vigorously with spoon or electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Sift together the 2 cups of flour, baking powder, salt and spices and stir in alternately with orange juice.
Mix the 1 cup of flour into the fruit and nuts; pour batter over fruit, mixing thoroughly.
Pour into prepared pans.
Place a pan of water on lower oven rack.
Bake cakes 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
After baking, let cakes stand 15 minutes before taking from pans.
Cool thoroughly on racks before removing paper.
Store by wrapping tightly in aluminum foil.
Place in covered jar in cool place to ripen.

title: buckwheat flatbread
directions: Combine dry
ingredients.
Add
water
in a slow stream for a soft, not sticky dough.
Divide and prepare for baking, making thin circles.
Bake at 350° until fully dried out.

title: oreo pudding
directions: Gently fold broken cookies into Cool Whip topping.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Sprinkle reserved cookie pieces over top. Refrigerate and enjoy.

title: oyster stew
directions: In top of double boiler melt the butter over direct heat, stirring constantly until smooth.
Gradually add the milk and cream, stirring constantly until boiling point is reached.
Add salt and pepper and stir.
Remove from heat.
Drain oysters and add liquid to the milk mixture, mixing well.
Place over hot water and cook for 15 minutes.
Add the oysters; stir and continue cooking until the oysters curl on the edges.
Place a lump of butter in each individual soup bowl and pour in the stew. Dividing the oysters as evenly as possible.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil milk on medium heat with rice until rice is cooked.
Add sugar.
Let cool for ten more minutes.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks with 4 tablespoons sugar and add lemon juice.
Cook over slow fire to custard stage.
Beat the egg whites with 2 tablespoons sugar and add to the hot lemon custard.
Whip the evaporated milk into the lemon custard and egg whites.

title: banana pudding
directions: Make instant pudding as directed.
When pudding begins to thicken, add sour cream and vanilla.
Layer bananas and wafers in a 9 x 13-inch pan or a large bowl.
Spread pudding between layers. Top with Cool Whip and chill.
Tastes better if chilled overnight.

title: zucchini stuffing casserole
directions: Cook the zucchini in boiling salted water until tender.
In saucepan, melt 4 tablespoons butter and cook the carrots and onion until done. Remove from heat. Add 1 1/2 cups stuffing, soup and sour cream. Gently stir in zucchini.
Turn into casserole bowl. Melt remaining butter and toss with remaining stuffing.
Put on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery soup

title: ham and asparagus
directions: Cook rice and place in casserole dish.
Cut ham in strips and roll around asparagus tips.
Lay on top of rice.
Heat cheese and milk together.
Pour over rest of ingredients.
Place in 350° oven until hot.

title: best ice cream
directions: Cook eggs and 4 cups milk together until slightly thick.
Cool and add remaining ingredients (no sugar is needed).
Freeze in ice cream maker.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: pollye's baked fruit
directions: Bring to boil water and oleo, beat in flour till well blended. Add eggs one at a time beating well with wooden spoon. DO NOT USE ELECTRIC MIXER. Spread in glass pan. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes. Pat more crust around edge to form crust. Cool completely.

title: waffles or pancakes
directions: Mix eggs and buttermilk, then dry ingredients.
Cook in a hot waffle iron.

title: sausage balls #1
directions: Have cheese at room temperature and mix with other ingredients.
Make in small balls, size of a quarter, and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
These freeze well and only need to be heated.

title: no pecan pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together the butter, sugar, eggs, syrup and vanilla.
Add oats and blend.
Pour into crust and bake about 50 to 55 minutes, until knife comes out clean.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Heat
soup,
margarine,
mayonnaise, onions and cheese. Add other ingredients.
Pour into greased dish. Top with whole Ritz crackers.
Bake,
covered,
minutes
at 350°. Remove cover and cook 10 minutes more.

title: betty white's meat loaf
directions: Combine ingredients and place in shallow baking pan.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fettuccini alfredo
directions: In large saucepan, stir together cream cheese, Parmesan cheese, margarine and milk over low heat until smooth.
Add fettuccini.
Toss lightly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tangy party meatballs
directions: Mix together lightly.
Gently roll into firm small balls (1 1/2-inch).
Set aside.
Prepare sauce.

title: parmesan vegetable toss
directions: In large bowl, combine broccoli, cauliflower and onion.
In small bowl, combine cheese, sugar, salt, basil and mayonnaise. Mix well.
Add dressing to vegetables; toss gently.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Just before serving, add bacon, lettuce, croutons and water chestnuts.
Toss lightly.
Makes 20 to 24 servings.

title: gladys's chili
directions: Cook meat and onions in little water until done.
Add other ingredients then beans.
Add enough water to cook on low heat for 30 to 45 minutes before taking off stove.

title: my sunday roast
directions: Brown roast; add onion soup mix and mushroom soup on top of roast.
Add water to roast, bake, covered, in 300° to 325° oven for 2 hours before adding potatoes (which have been cut lengthwise) and carrots (which have been cut lengthwise).
Finish cooking while at church.

title: cheese and squash delight
directions: Heat milk.
Add butter and pour over crumbs. Mix well. Add to squash.
Add cheese and seasonings.
Beat eggs until light.
Add to mixture.
Pour into a baking dish.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Buttered crumbs may be placed on top before baking.

title: spareribs
directions: Boil ribs for 30 minutes.
Combine sauce and pour over ribs. Let marinate for desired time.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Whip softened cheese until fluffy.
Beat in powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Gradually add milk; blend well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Turn into pie crust.
Freeze until firm.
Garnish with nuts.

title: orange and noodle aspic
directions: Cook the noodles as mentioned on the package.
Drain and rinse in cold water; drain again and cool the noodles.
Bring to a boil 1 cup pineapple juice.
Remove from the heat and add the orange Jell-O, stirring to dissolve the gelatin.
Then add the rest of the juice and let cool the mixture until it is half taken in Jell-O. Add the noodles, the orange sections and the diced cucumber.
Pour in an already buttered 1 1/2-quart mold and refrigerate.
To serve, unmold on lettuce.
Bon appetit!

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind vegetables and drain well. Put into large kettle and add other ingredients. Bring to a boil and cook for 30 minutes. Put in hot jars and seal. Makes about 20 pints.

title: applesauce-spice muffins
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and sugar.
Set aside.
Measure Raisin Bran cereal, applesauce and apple juice concentrate into large mixing bowl.
Stir to combine. Let stand 4 minutes or until cereal softens.
Add egg and oil to cereal mixture.
Beat well.
Add flour mixture, stirring only until combined.
Portion batter evenly into twelve 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 400° about 25 minutes or until golden.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: this veal stew belies its plain name
directions: Put olive oil in heavy skillet and heat garlic until it browns.
Remove garlic.
Add pieces of veal and brown them quickly.
Add consomme and just enough water to cover the meat. Bring to simmering boil; cover, reduce heat slightly and simmer for 2 hours or until meat is tender and falls from bones.
If cooked gently, there will be no need to add water.
There should be about 3/4 cup of broth left.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Add cream and sherry.
Boil, uncovered, for about 20 minutes to cook down to "consistency."
Good by itself, on noodles or on thin toast.

title: spinach surprise dip
directions: Thaw spinach and place in colander; squeeze out liquid.
Mix all ingredients together in large bowl until well blended.
Cover bowl and refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: marinated summer salad
directions: Combine all ingredients for 4 to 8 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: crab bites
directions: Soften cheese and butter to room temperature.
Mix with next 6 ingredients.
Add crabmeat or shrimp (flaked).
Mix well.
Spread on muffins.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
When firm, cut each half muffin into 8 pieces.
Place into plastic bags and freeze until needed.

title: mexican caesar salad
directions: Break up lettuce; put into bowl with onion, tomatoes, olives and cheese, mix.
Add tortilla chips broken up and then toss with dressing.

title: hot buttered rum mix
directions: Mix together; divide into freezer tubs.
Keep frozen.
Place 1 large tablespoon in cup of boiling water; add liquor of your choice.
Also good in coffee.

title: pea pickin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 3 buttered and floured cake pans.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 300°.

title: fried cod(baccala)
directions: Amounts depend on quantity of baccala.

title: creamy chocolate mousse
directions: Combine milk and pudding mix in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until mixture begins to boil, stirring constantly.
Cook 5 minutes, then add cream cheese.
Continue cooking, beating until well blended.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into a lightly oiled 1-quart mold or dish.
Place wax paper on top.
Chill until firm. Unmold (if desired).
May be served with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: lemon pie
directions: Cream
sugar,
lemon
juice
and
cornstarch.
Beat egg yolks, lightly,
add
to	sugar,	lemon
juice and cornstarch mixture. Mix
and
gradually add to boiling water. Cook until thick, about 4 minutes.	Let
cool.
Beat
egg
whites and add sugar gradually and
1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar, until stiff and put on pie crust top. Bake at 425° until brown.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press cookie dough in a large pizza pan and bake at 375° about 12 minutes or until light brown. Set aside to cool. Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla. Spread over cooled crust. Arrange any selected variety of fruit.

title: german sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cover and chill overnight.
Drain before serving.
Serve as side dish or relish for bratwurst or burgers. Will keep one week.

title: james beard's toll house cookies
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cajun onion chicken
directions: Place chicken in 11 x 14 x 2-inch dish.
Mix water and soup mix; pour over chicken.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: punch bowl dessert
directions: Tear cake into pieces, place in a large bowl.
Mix confectioners sugar with Carnation milk.
Add sour cream, mix together.
Mix strawberries and glaze.
Pour over torn cake and cover with Cool Whip.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Add onion and thyme. Cook, stirring, until tender. Do not brown. Slice potatoes and toss with parsley, salt and pepper. Heat cream, chicken broth and nutmeg in saucepan to boiling. Spread 1/3 of potatoes in 8-inch square baking dish.
Layer with 1/2 the onions, another third of the potatoes, onions, then remaining potatoes.
Pour cream broth mixture on top. Cover with foil. Bake 30 minutes. Baste potatoes with cream and bake 30 minutes more.

title: mama's baked spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Cook spaghetti and
rinse
with tap water.
Take 8-inch square baking dish and
cover bottom with half of the spaghetti.
Pour sauce over	noodles,
then	lay
cheese
(out
of
a package of 4 long slices
in
Kraft 6 ounce pack) side by side on top of sauce. This
should just fit.
Add another layer of spaghetti, sauce and the other 2 pieces of cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with meatballs.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Chop meat and onions. Add cream cheese. Mix well. Serve with crackers.

title: batter bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large mixing bowl; stir in ginger and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Let stand in warm place until mixture begins to bubble.
Add remaining sugar, oil, milk, salt and 3 cups flour.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer or by hand until smooth.
Pour on floured board and knead lightly.
Divide dough in 2 balls.
Place in greased 1 pound coffee can.
Place greased plastic lid on and let dough raise until top pops off.

title: enchiladas verdes
directions: Place chicken in saucepan, pour over stock and bring to boil. Reduce heat
and simmer 20 minutes.
Transfer breast to a
plate and
reserve
stock.
Remove
skin	and
bones
from chicken, cut meat
into small pieces.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Beat in 1/2
cup cream.
Stir in onions, add chicken then put aside. Roast
and	skin
peppers.	Chop
and
put in blender.
Add tomatoes, chilies, coriander and 1/4 cup chicken stock.
Blend to puree.
Pour
in remaining 1 1/2 cups cream, egg, salt and pepper.
Blend 10 seconds longer.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip tortillas
in
sauce, place some chicken mix on top and roll
up. Complete
for all tortillas.
Place side by side in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over, then sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: cola salad
directions: Mix juice from pineapple and Bing cherries with jello.
Bring to a boil; when cool, add the Coke.
Add fruit when jello begins to set.
Crumble package of cream cheese and add it with the nuts to the salad.
Chill.

title: layered salad deluxe
directions: Layer first 6 ingredients in order listed in large salad bowl. Combine salad dressing mix, sour cream and mayo; mix well. Spread over top of salad to edges.
Cover tightly and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Toss gently before serving.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: apple-cinnamon oat bran muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°.
Sift together the flours with the cinnamon, nutmeg and baking soda.
Add the oat bran.
Then peel, core and coarsely chop the apples.
Toss the chopped apples with the oat bran mixture.
Mix in the apple juice concentrate, then fill the juice container 1/3 full with water (about 1/2 cup).
Add this and mix just enough to moisten.
Spoon the batter into nonstick or lightly oil-sprayed muffin tins and bake for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook the broccoli in salted water until tender.
Drain. Combine the mayonnaise, soup, cheese and eggs and blend.
Pour over broccoli and top with crushed cheese crackers.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
This freezes well.
Bake about 10 minute before you freeze.

title: ham and corn casserole
directions: Mix until well blended.
Spoon into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle all over with 1 cup soft buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cocoa mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl; add mayonnaise, water and vanilla. Beat 3 minutes. Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Cool and frost.

title: italian chicken
directions: Soak chicken in eggs overnight.
Shake chicken pieces in Italian bread crumbs.
Brown in oil or margarine.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover top of chicken with Farmers or Monterey Jack cheese.
Pour 1 can chicken broth over top.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Enjoy!

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, salt and mustard; add onion and vinegar.
Pour oil slowly into mixture as you beat at low speed on mixer.
Mix well. Add 1 teaspoon celery seed and toss with salad.

title: amish friendship bread starter
directions: Day 1:
In glass or plastic bowl, combine 3 cups sugar, 3 cups flour and 3 cups milk.
Stir with wooden or plastic spoon.
Cover bowl loosely with paper towel.
Keep at room temperature.

title: pork and beans
directions: Soak beans in
salt
water
overnight,
then boil until beans are nearly soft.
Make a sauce of remaining ingredients. Fill cans 3/4 full of beans.
Add
liquid
and cold pack 2 1/2 hours.
Bacon can be added.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Melt butter.
Blend in flour.
Slowly add milk and cook until smooth and thickened.
Add salt, pepper and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Pour over macaroni and sprinkle with bread crumbs and remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, soup, sour cream, onion, 1 stick margarine, cheese, salt and pepper thoroughly.
Place into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix corn flakes and 1/2 stick melted margarine. Spread over potato mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: skillet apple pie
directions: Melt margarine in skillet.
Add apples and cook slow until golden brown.
Add the rest of the ingredients and cook slowly for about 2 minutes.
Pour in individual or regular baked crust.
Top with whipped topping if desired.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Boil potatoes until done and don't use them until they are cool (may cook them the day before).
Dice the potatoes and sprinkle heavily with lemon pepper; add other ingredients.
Put in a casserole dish and cook about 30 minutes at 300°.
Then sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and cook a few more minutes.
(Use 1 medium potato per person.)

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Preheat oven to 275°.
Lay chicken in bottom of dish.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl and then spread over top of chicken.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Cream butter and part of sugar mixture. Blend vanilla, milk and remaining sugar mixture into creamed mixture until desired spreading consistency.

title: double boiler bread pudding
directions: Put sugar in top of double boiler; add bread which has been toasted, buttered and cubed.
Add raisins.
Beat eggs slightly; add milk and salt.
Pour over other ingredients without stirring. Cover and put over bottom of double boiler which is half full of water; cook 1 hour with water gently boiling.
Brown sugar makes a sauce.
Very good served warm.

title: toasted mushroom rolls
directions: Peel mushrooms and dice.
Saute 5 minutes in butter.
Blend in flour, Accent and salt.
Stir in cream and simmer until thick. Add chives and lemon juice.
Blend well.
Roll bread slices thin. Spread with mixture and roll up.
Cut in half and toast on all sides about 20 minutes in 400°
oven.

title: pastor guy's heavenly deviled eggs
directions: Cover eggs in large pan with water.
Bring slowly to a boil; simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and run cold water on them for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove shells immediately.
While eggs are cooking, chop the following very, very fine:
onion, celery and green olives.
Set aside.
Cut eggs lengthwise; remove yolks and place in mixing bowl.
After you have removed all the yolks, mash with a fork until smooth in texture.
Add the following ingredients:
horseradish, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, mayonnaise, salt, pepper, garlic powder, onion, celery and olives.
Combine all ingredients well with a fork until mixed and smooth.
You may need a little more mayonnaise.
To put the filling in the egg halves, you may use a large pastry bag with a large open tip or spoon the ingredients into the egg halves.
You will have sufficient filling to more than fill the yolk hole.
To complete your Heavenly Deviled Eggs, arrange egg halves on a bed of lettuce and sprinkle with paprika.
Enjoy!

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except corn flakes.
Turn into a greased casserole dish.
Top with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are done.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain and save pineapple juice; melt butter in the microwave and pour into 10-inch round cake pan; stir brown sugar into melted butter. Arrange pineapple slices on top of butter mixture. Put Maraschino cherries in center of slices. Make pound cake mix according to box except use pineapple juice instead of milk. Pour over all in cake pan. Bake 45 - 50 minutes at 350°. Cool 5 minutes, then invert onto a plate. Pineapple slices will then be the topping.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Mix well together eggs, soda,
buttermilk
and
vanilla.
Melt and mix together margarine, cocoa
and
1 cup water.
Bring to boil.
Pour egg mixture
into flour mixture; mix well.
Add margarine mixture and mix
well. Spray
1/2 x 11 x 1 1/2-inch pan with Pam. Pour mixture into pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
One-half cup milk and 1/2 teaspoon vinegar = 1/2 cup buttermilk.)

title: mexican salad #2
directions: Toss with dressing to follow.

title: pudding cake
directions: Mix together and bake as directed on cake mix.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a medium mixing bowl combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, 3 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Blend in milk, melted oleo and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Pour batter into an 8 x 8 or a 9 x 9 inch pan.
In small bowl combine remaining 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar, and remaining 4 tablespoons cocoa; sprinkle mixture evenly over batter; pour hot water over top.
Do not stir.
Bake 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Let stand 15 minutes; spoon into dessert dishes, spoon sauce from bottom of pan over top.
Garnish as desired. 8 or 10 servings.
Be sure and do not stir after adding water.

title: pepper, onion and tomato salad
directions: Toss lettuce, tomatoes and peppers in a bowl with desired amount of vinaigrette.
Garnish with red onion rings.

title: champagne punch
directions: Mix in order of ingredients listed.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine sausage, bread crumbs, sage, eggs, onion and parsley and form balls.
Brown in skillet and drain.

title: layered spinach salad
directions: Remove and discard spinach stems.
Rinse leaves well; drain and pat dry.
Tear spinach into bite-sized pieces and arrange evenly in salad bowl.
Evenly layer cucumber slices, radish, green onion and eggs.
Spread dressing over top.
Cover; chill up to 24 hours. Just before serving, sprinkle with bacon and peanuts.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: green chilli
directions: Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Brown in skillet with 1 tablespoon oil.
Cut up chillies and tomatoes and add to chicken. Simmer about 10 or 15 minutes.
Serve over yellow rice.
Boneless pork chops can be substituted for chicken.

title: apple oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray baking sheets with nonstick cooking spray. Combine the oats, flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt in large bowl. In a medium bowl, cream brown sugar and margarine until pale and fluffy. Add apple, egg and vanilla; beat until combined. Add the oats mixture. Stir to blend. Drop the dough by tablespoon onto baking sheets. Flatten with the back of the spoon. Bake until lightly browned, 12 to 15 minutes. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: date nut bars
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Add baking powder and salt.
Sift again.
Combine with brown sugar.
Add melted shortening to beaten eggs and combine with dry ingredients.
Add chopped nuts and dates.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese.
Add condensed milk.
Add lemon and vanilla.
Pour into pie crust and chill.

title: breakfast rolls
directions: Mix together flour, salt and
baking powder.
Add cream and mix until dough follows fork around bowl.
Roll
out
on a lightly floured board to a 6 x 12-inch rectangle.
Spread with soft butter and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Roll up like jelly roll
and
cut in 1-inch slices.
Arrange
in
greased
round 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° (hot) for 20
to 25 minutes.
Invert over serving plate. Serve hot.

title: lasagne
directions: Fry ground beef until brown (I add salt, pepper, onion and mushrooms when frying ground beef).
Drain off grease.
Add sauce. Bring to a slow boil on low heat.
Prepare noodles according to directions.
Using a medium size casserole dish, place half of noodles on bottom.
Place half of ground beef mixture on noodles. Sprinkle half of cheese on top.
Add remaining noodles.
Top with rest of ground beef and cheese.
Heat in oven at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Lightly grease cookie sheet. Cut crescents into 3 diamond shape pieces. Place sausage on crescent and roll up. Place on cookie sheet and bake until golden brown.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients; add the liquids.
Mix at medium speed for two minutes.
Add the eggs and vanilla.
Beat two minutes more.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 325° in two 9-inch pans for 25 to 30 minutes; 9 x 13-inch pan for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli; add onion, raisins and cooked bacon.
Chill. In a small bowl, mix Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar.
Put on broccoli mix just before serving.
You can add slivered almonds if you like.

title: nana's mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together 10 minutes.
Cook on 200° for 1/2 hour.
Eat it when done.
Yum-yum.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; bone and skin.
Cook celery and onion in butter until soft.
Heat mushroom soup, chicken soup and broth; pour over stuffing, onion and celery and mix.
Butter baking dish; place boned chicken.
Cover with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix together.
Mix well.
Put into refrigerator for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Because it's made without milk, it will keep for up to 5 days.
No kneading.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned at 400°.
Makes about 3 dozen rolls.

title: beaumont inn corn pudding
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Combine and add milk and eggs; mix well.
Pour into oblong glass dish.
Bake slowly for 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven, or until done.
Stir from bottom every 5 minutes.
It may be the intermittent stirring that produces the luscious custardy consistency.

title: baked beans
directions: Clean beans and parboil in cold water with soda.
Let come to a rolling boil.
Take off immediately; drain and rinse.
Put in hot water with salt.
Boil until tender.
Mix together ketchup, brown sugar and dry mustard.
Add to beans and stir in other ingredients.
Put strips of bacon on top of beans.
Chunks of ham may also be added before baking.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: wesson oil cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and sift through sifter.
Add Wesson oil and sour milk or buttermilk; mix thoroughly.
Nuts may be added if desired.
Bake in loaf pan at 350°.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve cherry Jell-O in 1 cup of boiling water.
Add 1 can cherry pie filling.
Put in serving dish and chill in refrigerator.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown together beef, peppers and onion; drain off grease and add salt, pepper, garlic salt and soy sauce to taste; set aside. Bring to a boil 1 cup water; add bouillon cube and rice.
Mix well; then add tomatoes with liquid.
Mix in beef mixture and tomato sauce.
Simmer until done.
If too dry, add water a little at a time.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Scald milk in double boiler. Beat eggs until smooth.
Mix cornstarch and sugar together. Add to eggs. Stir until smooth. Add to hot milk.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat. Stir in butter and coconut.
Let cool. Add 1/2 cup Cool Whip to the filling. Garnish with the rest of the Cool Whip and sprinkle top with toasted coconut.

title: spicy cocktail meatballs
directions: Place lamb, 2 teaspoons cumin, ginger, cloves, cinnamon, 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg, 1/2 teaspoon pepper, cayenne pepper and 1/4 cup sour cream in bowl.
Attach bowl and flat beater.
On stir speed, mix 30 seconds.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Bake on a 101/2 x 15 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes until browned. Remove meatballs from pan and place into a 10-inch skillet.

title: old fashioned peach cobbler
directions: Combine 3/4 cup sugar and peaches, let stand for 20 minutes. Melt margarine in bottom of 1 1/2-quart baking dish in oven.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and add milk.
Stir briskly.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with peaches.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: The cream cheese, sour cream and oleo should be at room temperature.
Combine and stir in remaining ingredients.

title: tomato soup
directions: Wash and cut up tomatoes.
Chop onions, celery, parsley and bay leaves.
Add to tomatoes; cook until celery is tender.
Put through sieve.
Combine flour and butter until you have a smooth paste.
Thin with a small amount of cooled tomato juice.
Add to boiling soup, stirring to prevent scorching.
Add salt, sugar and pepper; cook 15 more minutes on low, stirring to prevent scorching.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut up the rhubarb and spread in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle package of cherry Jell-O over rhubarb. Sprinkle sugar over Jell-O.
Add miniature marshmallows.
Mix yellow cake mix according to box directions and pour over mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: carrot muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together (real good). Pour into greased muffin pans, filling each about 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° until done, sample by touch.

title: mom's dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill.
For different variety, add one spoon of mayonnaise.

title: mixed pickles
directions: Cut vegetables in chunks and put in salt overnight.
Drain. Mix sugar, mustard and turmeric in vinegar to cover.
Heat through.
Add white mustard seed, if desired.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Add sugar, flavoring and oil; beat well.
Add flour and cinnamon.
Fold in zucchini and nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: abbey cakes
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening together and add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Spray muffin tins with Pam or grease thoroughly with shortening.
Bake at 325°
approximately 15 minutes. Remove from oven and dip entire muffin in melted margarine (about 6 tablespoons).
Roll in mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Wash potatoes and cook	whole with peeling on (about 30 minutes).
When done, remove
peeling
and	slice
into baking dish.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil water in large soup pot with the bouillon cubes; add the butter and vegetables.
Fifteen minutes later add the potatoes. Add cooked chicken or turkey and noodles.
Cook for another 15 minutes then add 1 can cream of chicken or mushroom soup.
Stir and serve!!

title: popovers
directions: Grease and flour 6 custard cups completely.
Blend all ingredients together for 30 seconds.
Fill the custard cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: human "puppy chow"
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients together.
Measure cereal into large mixing bowl.
Put powdered sugar into large brown paper sack. Pour cereal mixture into sack.
Shake and toss altogether.

title: date sticks
directions: Bake in 300° oven.
Will make one 10 x 15-inch pan.
Cut while still warm and dust with 4 tablespoons powdered sugar and 1 tablespoon flour.

title: opal's pie crust(makes 5 shells or 2 double crusts and one shell.)
directions: Stir together the flour and oatmeal.

With pastry blender or 2 knives, blend in the Crisco until it resembles size of small peas. With a fork, stir in the water slowly until it forms a ball. Divide into small balls to roll and fit 9-inch pie plates.
These can be made ahead and frozen either separately in Ziploc bags or stacked with wax paper between the plates and sealed in plastic bags.

title: sesame toffee bars
directions: Toast sesame seed in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla and mix well. Stir in nuts.
Sift flour with spices and add to creamed mixture. Mix well.
Spread 1/4-inch thick onto a 13 x 15-inch baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
While baking, melt chocolate pieces in double boiler over hot water.
Spread chocolate over baked cookies while hot.
Sprinkle top with sesame seed and cut into bars while warm.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: cherry pizza
directions: Make pizza dough according to directions and spread it out on a cookie sheet pan.
Spread cherry filling on top and sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake until dough is done (according to directions on the package).
Apple filling can also be used with raisins.

title: crunchy cole slaw
directions: Put oil, vinegar, sugar and seasoning in container.
Remaining goes in serving bowl.
Shake oil mixture up well and pour over colelsaw mix just before serving.

title: diabetic - chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking pan; do not let them overlap. Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Mix soup, milk, sour cream and drained mushrooms into a sauce.
Spread over chicken.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.
Serve with noodles or over whole wheat toast.
Makes 6 servings.
Serving Size:
1 breast half, plus 1/3 cup sauce.

title: margaret rozell's fruit salad
directions: Mix yogurt, salad dressing and instant pudding.
Mix until creamy.
Add fruits.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve lime jello in hot water, then add the cold water. Pour into a 14 x 10 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until set, then dissolve lemon jello in water.
Over heat, dissolve marshmallows in jello. Remove from heat and add pineapple juice and cream cheese.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in pineapple.
When cooled, add whipped cream and mayonnaise.
Chill until thick, then pour over lime jello.
Chill until set.
Dissolve cherry jello in hot water, then add cold water.
Chill until syrupy.
Pour over pineapple layer. Chill until firm.

title: syrup pie
directions: Beat, Beat, Beat.
Cook on top of stove until pretty thick and pour into partially baked crust.
Bake at 300-350° until firm.

title: banana punch
directions: Combine sugar and water; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat. Add fruit and juices.
Pour into 2 (13 x 9-inch) pans and freeze. When ready to serve, cut or break slush into a punch bowl and add ginger ale.

title: sunset salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bowl and separate oranges into sections. Lay oranges, cream cheese and almonds on top of lettuce.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over salad.

title: red cake waldorf astoria
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Make a paste of food coloring and cocoa and add to creamed mixture.
Add buttermilk alternately with sifted flour and salt.
Add vanilla. Mix soda and vinegar, then add to mixture, blending only.
Bake around 30 minutes at 350° in 2 (8 or 9-inch) pans greased and floured.
Cool on rack.
Split layers in two to make 4 layers.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and margarine in mixer. Add vinegar, vanilla and coconut. Put in unbaked pie crust. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.

title: wassail(hot spiced cider)
directions: Tie spices in cheesecloth or place in tea holder.
Heat cider, sugar and spices.
Simmer 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine with all ingredients except flour, salt and soda.
Sift them together.
Add 1 cup flour mixture at a time, beating after each addition.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and cocoa, mixing well. Add milk and cook over low heat until hot. Add egg yolks. Cook until thick. Add salt, butter and vanilla.
Pour into cool pie shell.

title: old time flap jacks
directions: Add the flour to the buttermilk and shortening until slightly stiff.
Drop with tablespoon in hot oil or shortening in skillet. Fry until brown on both sides.
Mash down slightly after you turn them once. A good substitute for biscuits.

title: corned beef loaf
directions: Very popular meat loaf.
Make the night before you plan to use it.

title: batterway rolls
directions: Pour warm water in large mixing bowl; add yeast.
Let stand a few minutes; stir to dissolve.
Add half the flour, sugar, salt, shortening and egg.
Start mixer on medium speed and beat until smooth 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stop mixer.
Add rest of flour and stir by hand until flour disappears.
Scrape batter down from sides of bowl.
Cover bowl with waxed paper and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 30 minutes.

title: white sour cream coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions for a 2-layer cake. Cut each layer in half with a piece of thread or floss to make 4 layers. Mix sugar, sour cream and coconut. Divide equally and spread between layers. Let cool completely before frosting.

title: berry freezer jam
directions: Combine berries and sugar in 5-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Epsom salts.
Stir for 5 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal. Let cool, then store in freezer.

title: microwave red hot apple jelly
directions: Combine apple juice and pectin in a 3-quart microwave-safe bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap or waxed paper and bring to a boil in the microwave oven on High setting (about 12 to 14 minutes). Stir twice.
Remove from oven; add sugar and cinnamon candies, stirring well.
Return to microwave; cook until mixture returns to a rolling boil, about 10 to 12 minutes, stirring occasionally. Boil hard one minute.
Remove from oven.
Skim foam if necessary. Pour hot into hot, sterilized jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace. Adjust caps.
Process 5 minutes in boiling water bath.
Do not attempt to process in microwave oven.
Yield:
About 6 half pints.

title: orange apricot salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar.
Stir over low heat.
Remove, add jello, baby food, and cream cheese.
Fold in cool whip.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill until thick.
Can top with crushed pecans.

title: foil wrapped dinner
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut meat in serving size pieces.
Rinse frozen peas.
Use four 18 x 15-inch square pieces of aluminum foil.
Divide meat, peas, carrots and potatoes.
Put on each square foil.
Stir soups together; spoon on top of vegetables and meat.
Wrap securely in foil.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 50 minutes or until tender.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes.
Serves 4.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Mix all ingredients with exception of milk chocolate Kisses. Chill for 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake for 12 minutes.
Remove from oven and press Kisses into cookie.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: seminole victory stew
directions: Brown the veal in the shortening in a heavy metal pot. Remove the veal and set aside. Stir the flour into the pan drippings. Cook for 2 minutes, stirring constantly; remove from the heat. Add the consomm and wine and mix well. Cook until thickened and smooth, stirring constantly. Add the veal and onions. Season with salt and pepper. Simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 hours. Serve over a bed of noodles. Makes 6 servings.

title: layered dip
directions: Layer in 13 x 9-inch pan, starting with refried beans and layering each ingredient in order listed.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: swiss steak
directions: Roll steak in flour.
Brown in skillet with oil.
Put in crock-pot or Dutch oven.
Add vegetables; cook on medium in crock-pot for about 6 to 8 hours or in Dutch oven at 375° until meat is tender.
Try this over rice!

title: asparagus and pea casserole
directions: Assemble ingredients.
Place a layer of asparagus in casserole and a layer of peas.
Slice hard-boiled egg over this. Repeat layering process.
Make a cheese sauce by melting butter in saucepan; carefully mix in flour, then milk.
Add cheese.
Cook over low heat until slightly thickened and cheese melts.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour cheese sauce over casserole.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: turkey orzo soup
directions: Saute onion in a little margarine.
Combine the first 5 ingredients and cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Add orzo, salt, pepper and parsley and cook until orzo are done.

title: blueberry crunch bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Make well in center. Add remaining ingredients; stir just until moistened through. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: stir-n-roll pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Pour oil and milk onto measuring cup; mix with flour.
Press into balls.
Cut into halves.
Place half between waxed paper.
Lightly dampen table top to prevent slipping.
Roll out until circle reaches edges.
Peel off top paper.
Place paper side up in pie pan.
Peel off paper.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Start with lettuce and put each item, one on top of the other, in order listed.
Make several hours ahead or a day ahead.
Cover with Saran Wrap or aluminum foil to seal and refrigerate.

title: english christmas pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl. Add sufficient sherry or brandy to make it moist. (All family members should take a turn at stirring, they each make a wish). Put mixture in a bowl. Cover with wax paper and a pudding cloth. Steam for 4 hours. The pudding then can be put in a cool dry place for up to 18 months. Steam another 3 hours before serving. Turn out onto plate. Put a sprig of holly on top. Pour a little hot brandy over the top and ignite! This is sufficient for a pudding.

title: punch
directions: Fill Cool Whip carton with water and put flower on top. Freeze.
Put in punch bowl.

title: easy dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers. Pack into hot, sterilized jars with pieces of dill. Add a clove of garlic to each jar. Boil 3 1/2 cups water, 2 cups vinegar and 3/4 cup salt for about 5 minutes and pour over cucumbers, filling jars to 1/2-inch from top. Seal at once. Makes about 8 quart jars.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large skillet, cook and stir ground beef until light brown; drain off fat.
Add onion and green pepper; cook until onion is tender.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, chili powder, salt and pepper; mix well.
Pour into ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake 1 hour.

title: creamy dutch apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish, melt butter in oven.
Sprinkle in crumbs.
Press on bottom of dish.

title: blue cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts, into a ball.
Chill.
Roll into chopped walnuts to cover.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine with sugar and eggs.
Stir in sour cream and mashed bananas.
Stir baking soda, baking powder and salt into flour.
Add flour mixture and beat on low speed.

title: millie's spicy party spread
directions: In mixer bowl, beat together cream cheese and Cheddar cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in 1 cup sour cream and taco mix. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Fold in chilies.
Turn into 9-inch spring-form pan.
Place on baking sheet and bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 350° or until center is almost set.
Cook in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.

title: chocolate covered strawberries
directions: Put chips, butter and corn syrup in the top of a double boiler and heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture melts and is smooth. Transfer chocolate mixture to a small metal bowl and set bowl in a pan of warm water. Hold each strawberry by its leaves and/or stem and dip into chocolate mixture, coating bottom 2/3 of the berry. Allow excess chocolate to drip back into pan. Place covered berries on waxed paper lined baking sheet and refrigerate until chocolate is set, at least 30 minutes. Serve these berries the same day they are prepared.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: In a 2-quart covered casserole, arrange 1 layer sliced potatoes, 1 layer onions (sliced), 1 layer crumbled raw lean ground beef and salt and pepper to taste.
Add Great Northern beans.
Pour tomato sauce over top.
Sprinkle chili powder and garlic salt on top.
Cover and bake 2 hours at 300°.
Check for doneness after 1 1/2 hours.
Top with cheese in last few minutes of cooking.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Slash the roast and insert slices of garlic in the slits.
Rub well with salt and pepper and place in a glass or earthenware bowl.
Cover the top with one of the onions, sliced.
Heat together the water, vinegar, lemon slices and pickling spices and pour the hot marinade over the bowl.
Cover tightly and let stand 2 or 3 days before cooking.
Turn the meat occasionally so that it will be marinated evenly throughout.

title: best-of-the-season fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail.
Slice banana, stir into fruit cocktail. Wash fresh fruit.
Peel, if necessary.
Cut up into bite-sized pieces.
Stir fresh fruit into fruit cocktail.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine together; add sugar and cool.
Add eggs, flour, salt, baking powder, vanilla, almond extract and zucchini.
Spread in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: wine and chicken
directions: Prepare chicken and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Melt margarine in electric frypan.
Add chicken and brown on both sides. Sprinkle parsley flakes over and add 1/4 cup white wine.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour, turning pieces occasionally.
Makes nice gravy, too, when thickened.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat and add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hearty hodgepodge soup
directions: Brown first 4 ingredients.
Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer.

title: baked garlic
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut top from garlic head.
Remove loose skin but do not peel.
Wipe with damp paper towel and place in shallow baking dish or cookie sheet.
Bake for 45 minutes or until soft.
Spread garlic on toasted French bread instead of butter.

title: carrousel salad bowl
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on box; drain. While still hot, drizzle with oil and vinegar. Add onion, seasonings and cheese. Toss well. Gently mix in remaining ingredients. Let cool. Serve on salad greens.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, except sour cream, together; stir well and bake in 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly. Fold in sour cream and heat 10 minutes longer.
Serve with tortilla chips or line the pan with corn tortillas before adding filling.
If using tortillas, they may be softened in chicken broth.

title: apple chutney
directions: Pare, core and slice apples.
Mince onions and peppers and add to apples, along with vinegar, raisins, jelly and the rest of the ingredients.
Boil until thick, stirring constantly.
Pack boiling hot into hot, sterilized jars.
Seal.

title: brown sugar pie
directions: Combine
eggs,	brown
sugar
and
salt; mix well.
Mix flour and
margarine together.
Add half and half and flavorings.
Pour into
two
9-inch
unbaked	pie
shells.
Bake 10 minutes at
450° then 30 or more minutes at 300° or until you shake the pies and they are settled.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Mix and bake in layers at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: marinated pork steak
directions: At least 4 hours before serving, prepare pork steaks with meat tenderizer.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
Place steaks in a 13 x 9-inch pan in which the rest of the ingredients, except pineapple rings, have been mixed.
Cover; refrigerate at least 3 hours, turning meat once.

title: carrot cake #2
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease tube pan.
In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking soda and cinnamon.
Whisk in oil, baby food and eggs until smooth.
Fold in pineapple with juice and coconut and pour into pan.
Bake for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: orange-and-sunflower rice stuffing
directions: Combine the rice and water in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover tightly and cook on High for 3 to 5 minutes, or until the water is absorbed.
Stir the remaining ingredients into the rice at the end of cooking.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake or use ready-made pound cake.
Mix vanilla pudding. Place one layer of cake in punch bowl.

Pour in some fruit cocktail (no juices), 1 can cherry pie filling, one layer of pudding, some crushed pineapple and a layer of Cool Whip. Sprinkle chopped pecans, shredded coconut and chocolate chips over Cool Whip layer.
Start another layer except add blueberry pie filling in place of cherry.
You can keep going and put as many layers or as much fruit as you like.
End with a layer of Cool Whip.

title: apple crumble
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Combine 1/2 cup of sugar and 1 ounce of flour in a bowl.
Combine lemon juice and apples.
Mix with sugar mixture.
Put in a baking dish.
Mix butter, remaining flour and cinnamon.
Add remaining 1/2 cup of sugar.
Sprinkle mixture over apples and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is golden.

title: turkey-poppy seed casserole
directions: In a large skillet, cook turkey, onion and pepper; drain if necessary.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook noodles; drain.
In a small bowl, combine the cheeses, yogurt and poppy seed.
Toss the cheese mixture with the hot noodles.
Layer 3/4 of the noodle mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon in meat mixture over center, leaving a 1 to 2-inch border of uncovered noodles.
Layer remaining noodles over the meat.
Bake in covered dish for 30 minutes at 375°.
Uncover; bake for 10 to 15 minutes more, or until heated through.

title: western chili sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and heat to boiling.
Simmer about 2 hours and fill hot sterilized jars.
Seal.

title: oriental flank steak
directions: Mix the green onions with the rest of the ingredients except the steak to make marinade.
Place steak in a glass dish.
Pour marinade over steak.
Cover and turn occasionally for 8 hours or more.
Drain meat and grill.
(I have frozen steak and marinade for up to 2 months.)

title: lasagna
directions: In a medium bowl, combine sauce, Italian sausage and ground beef.
In a separate medium bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, 3/4 cup Parmesan cheese and parsley.
Pour 3/4 cup sauce mixture in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer one-third of the noodles, half of the Ricotta mixture, one-third of the remaining sauce and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese in pan.
Repeat layers.
Top with remaining noodles and sauce, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese and 3/4 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Put in a funnel and place in hot oil.

title: baked cod with crabmeat
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place clean cod fillets in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish coated with cooking spray.
In a medium bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Mix well until moist.
Pour mixture over fillets and pat down gently.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes with a fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: saucy franks
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, stir preserves and barbecue sauce. Diagonally cut frankfurters into 3/4-inch pieces; add to saucepan. Stirring over medium heat, bring to a boil and simmer until meat pieces are plumped.
Remove from heat.
In a small bowl, stir water into cornstarch until smooth.
Stir into hot mixture.
Return to heat and boil for 1 to 2 minutes or until thickened.
Transfer to a chafing dish.
Garnish with orange slice.
Serve hot with wooden picks.
Makes 20 to 25 servings.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Chop onion and pepper fine; mix all ingredients and bake at 325° for 1 hour in covered casserole.
(Also works well on top of wood stove.)

title: dark-chocolate walnut drops
directions: About 2 hours before serving or up to 2 weeks ahead, mix ingredients together.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet. Into large bowl, measure all ingredients except walnuts.
With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until blended.
Increase speed to high; beat 1 minute, occasionally scraping bowl with spatula.
With rubber spatula, stir in walnuts.
Drop mixture by rounded tablespoonfuls, 1 inch apart, onto cookie sheets.
Bake 15 minutes.
With pancake turner, remove cookies to wire racks; cool. Store cookies in tightly covered container to use up within 2 weeks.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Make white sauce by combining margarine, flour, water and bouillon.
Add broccoli and cheese.
Spice to taste.

title: corky's pulled butter mints
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in heavy saucepan.
Stir until mixture dissolves and starts cooking.
Do not stir again.
Place candy thermometer in and cook on medium-high heat until 279° (soft crack).
Pour on a cold buttered marble slab.
Pour flavoring and color on candy.

title: egg salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve on toasted bread.

title: spareribs and sauerkraut
directions: Cut ribs in serving size pieces and place in flat baking dish. Add water.
Bake slowly for 2 hours.
Take from oven and season with salt and pepper.
Pour kraut over them (juice and all). Sprinkle on brown sugar and bake 1 hour more at 300°.

title: el's killer wings
directions: Rinse wings with cold running water; blot dry with paper towels.
Using sharp knife or kitchen scissors, remove tip portions (freeze to use for chicken stock).
Cut through triangle of skin at wing joint; bend parts backward to pop joint.
Cut through joint, dividing wing into separate sections; remove and discard any visible fat.
In large glass baking dish or large food-storage bag, place wings; drizzle with about 1/4 cup of hot sauce.
Cover dish and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.

title: chocolate coated bananas
directions: You will need 6 wooden ice cream sticks.
Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Place peanuts on waxed paper.
Insert one stick lengthwise into banana.
Dip each banana into chocolate, then roll in peanuts.
Place on dish lined with waxed paper and refrigerate 30 minutes.

title: philly cream cheese cream puff ring
directions: Bring water and margarine to boil.
Add flour and salt.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms ball.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Drop 10 (1/2 cupfuls) of dough on lightly greased cookie sheet to form a 9-inch ring.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 55 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from cookie sheet immediately.
Cool. Combine cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Reserve 1/2 cup cream cheese mixture; fold whipped cream and bananas into remaining mixture.
Chill.
Carefully cut top from ring; fill with whipped cream mixture.
Replace top.
Add remaining sugar, chocolate and milk to reserved cream cheese mixture.
Mix well.
Spread over ring.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a baking dish; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: caramel pie
directions: Cream yolks, sugar and flour; add milk.
Stir into melted sugar.
Stir and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with either meringue or whipped cream.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Cut the sirloin into thin strips.
Brown in Crisco.
Add onions and garlic; cook until onion is tender.
Combine soup, sour cream, mushrooms, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over meat and cook over low heat until done.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: my famous potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on until a fork can be inserted and potato falls apart easily.
Boil eggs for 10 minutes.
While potatoes and eggs are boiling chop the celery.
After eggs are done chop the eggs.
After potatoes are done chop potatoes into chunks.
Place potatoes, eggs and celery in a large bowl.
Mix them with the mayonnaise and the mustard.
Add celery salt to taste.
Feeds a crowd.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Drain juice from fruit and mix with margarine, white and brown sugar in a saucepan.
Thicken with enough cornstarch to make thick.
Mix with fruit and put in 8 x 10-inch baking dish.

title: harvard beet spice cake
directions: Beat butter with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs; beat well.
Blend beets in electric food blender until smooth.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with beets to butter mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in walnuts.
Turn batter into greased, lightly floured 9-cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool on rack for 30 minutes before removing from pan.
Sift confectioners sugar over top of cooled cake.

title: cucumbers with dressing
directions: In a bowl, combine mayo, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Add cucumbers; stir to coat.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.

title: chocolate fudge pudding
directions: Sift first five ingredients together.
Pour into large mixing bowl.
Stir in milk and shortening.
Spread in a 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with cocoa and sugar mixture.
Pour hot water over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be topped with scoop of ice cream or whipped cream.
Serves 6.

title: old fashioned pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all ingredients, except pie crust, until smooth.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 425° for 15 minutes or at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: dietetic spiced apple rings
directions: Place spices in piece of dampened cheesecloth; tie to form bag. Place spice bag and apple juice in large saucepan; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Combine 2 quarts water, lemon juice and salt in large bowl.
Core apples; cut crosswise into 1/2-inch slices.
Place slices in lemon juice mixture as soon as cut to prevent discoloration.
Cut slices of large apples in half, if desired.
Drain about 1/4 of the apple slices; drop into boiling spiced juice.
Cook just until wilted. Spoon slices immediately into hot sterilized pint jars, leaving 1-inch headspace.
Add 1/4 teaspoon almond extract to each jar. Cover with hot juice, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Clean jar rims. Place lids on jars; tighten rings firmly, but do not force. Process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.
Yields 5 to 6 pints.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl and bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.

title: he man cake
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and hold.
Mix remaining 4 ingredients together in large bowl; hold.
Combine the 2 mixtures with mixer (batter will be very thin).
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: french breakfast puffs
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, 1/2 cup sugar (leaving 1/2 cup extra) and 1 egg.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Stir sifted mixture into the cream mixture alternately with 1/2 cup milk.

title: petit pecan pie
directions: Mix together well and put a scant teaspoonful of mixture into each pastry shell. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: baked black olive minestrone
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut beef into 1 1/4-inch cubes.
Mix together beef, onion, garlic, salt and pepper in a Dutch oven or heavy saucepan.
Add olive oil and stir to coat meat evenly.
Brown uncovered in preheated oven about 40 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Add broth, water and Italian seasoning.
Cover and cook 1 hour until meat is almost tender. Remove from oven and stir in tomatoes, beans, olives and liquor, carrots and macaroni.
Sprinkle sliced zucchini on top.
Cover and return pan to oven to bake 40 to 45 minutes longer until macaroni is tender.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
Makes 3 1/2 quarts.

title: pumpkin ice cream
directions: Soften ice cream.
Stir in pumpkin, brown sugar and pumpkin pie spice.
Freeze.
Makes a little over a quart.

title: old time spaghetti sauce
directions: About 2 hours and 15 minutes before serving, in hot salad oil in a large skillet, brown garlic.
Remove and in the same oil, saute onion until tender.
Add crumbled meat and sprinkle in flour.
Cook until meat is loose and a red color, stirring while cooking.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring occasionally. Simmer, covered, 2 hours.
If desired, serve immediately or freeze (directions below).
Makes about 2 quarts of spaghetti sauce.

title: whole wheat french bread
directions: Combine flour (both) and salt in large bowl; dissolve yeast in warm water. Add to flour; mix well with wooden spoon until dough no longer clings to bowl. Turn onto lightly floured board; knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes. Place in greased bowl. Cover and let rise until doubled (1 1/2 hours). Punch down. Divide in half.

Turn each half onto lightly floured board. Sprinkle with flour. Roll each half into a 15 x 3-inch rectangle; dust off the flour. Knead each half 10 minutes. Bring edges up and pinch together tightly. Carefully place loaves, pinched side down, on lightly floured baking sheet. Cover with a towel. Let rise 45 minutes. Cut 3 slashes about 1/4 inch deep in top of each loaf. Preheat oven to 450° and spray inside oven with water to create steam. Put loaves in oven.
Spray oven again to create steam. Bake until loaves sound hollow when tapped, about 30 minutes. Remove from oven and spray bread lightly with water. Cool on wire racks.

title: bean soup
directions: Soak beans as
directed
on package.
Drain most of the water after soaking.
Add rest of the ingredients, bringing to a boil, then simmer for at least 3 hours.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Place peaches in pastry shell.
Mix together the sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon.
Gradually add the cream.
Pour over peaches.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.
You may also use blackberries or strawberries for this recipe.

title: japanese chicken wings
directions: Cut each chicken wing into 3 parts, separating at joints (use wing tips later for stock or freezer).
In 12 x 9-inch baking pan, mix remaining ingredients.
Add chicken wings.
Turn to coat well. Let marinate at least 1 hour or longer, turning occasionally, or cover overnight.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake chicken in marinade uncovered for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, turning occasionally.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Stir in milk or buttermilk, pecans, candied cherries and dates.
Sift together sifted flour, salt and soda.
Add to other ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peaches, water and 1/2 cup of sugar into a medium saucepan and bring to a boil.
Mix all other ingredients together, including the other 1/2 cup of sugar.
Pour into a greased pan. Pour the hot peach mixture over the batter.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Make pie dough, spray with Pam. Dust hands with powdered sugar and spread on cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 20-25 minutes.
Mix a filling of 8 oz. cream cheese, 1/2 c. sugar and 1 tsp. vanilla.
Spread on cooled crust.
Top with favorite fruit, cut up. Strawberries, blueberries, pineapple, kiwi, mandarin oranges, grapes, peaches, etc.

title: pineapple cream cheese squares
directions: Combine crumbs, sugar and butter.
Press into bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.
Let cool. Prepare whipped topping mix as directed on package.
Blend cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar together.
Fold in prepared topping, spoon into crumb-lined pan, spreading evenly.
Chill until set.
Drain pineapple, measuring syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water and add measured liquid.
Chil until thickened.
Arrange 9 pineapple slices on cream cheese mixture.
Spoon on gelatin, chill until firm (about 3 hours).
Cut into squares.
Top with whipped topping.
Makes 9 servings.

title: crispy chocolate bars
directions: Combine chocolate and butterscotch morsels and peanut butter in large saucepan.
Stir over low heat until smooth.
Add Kellogg's corn flakes cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Spread mixture into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Let stand at room temperature about 10 minutes before cutting into bars.
Bars are easily removed from pan.
Yields 32 bars, 1 x 2 inches.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce in bottom of full size 4-inch serving pan.
Layer onions, celery, pepper and radishes on lettuce.
Layer thawed peas over vegetables.
Layer chopped eggs over peas.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar, spread over entire pan; seal edges.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon over mayonnaise.
Refrigerate overnight, covered.
Garnish with radishes before serving.
Yields 100 servings.

title: fry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients; add enough milk to make it biscuit consistency.
Roll out dough and cut in desired size pieces.
Fry in hot oil until browned on both sides.

title: make-ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350° if using right away.
Mash all ingredients together.
Place in greased casserole dish (can spray dish with Pam) and bake for 30 minutes.

title: taco chicken salad
directions: Place tortillas on large baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Turn over and coat lightly with spray.
Sprinkle garlic powder and red pepper over tortillas. Bake 6 minutes more until crisp; set aside.
Coat large nonstick skillet with spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Saute onion until tender.
Add chicken and tomatoes and chillies.
Stir well.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir in sour cream.
Place tortillas on individual plates.
Top each with 1 cup lettuce. Spoon chicken mixture evenly over lettuce.
Sprinkle with Cheddar and cilantro.
Serve with salsa.

title: hot grape-nuts with oatmeal
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a microwave-safe bowl. Microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir before serving.

title: low-fat carrot-pineapple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large bowl, stir together the flour, oats, baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices.
In another bowl, stir together the pineapple, yogurt, Egg Beaters, Butter Buds and vanilla.
Stir in brown and white sugars until blended.
Make a well in the center of the flour mixture; stir in liquid just to moisten.
Stir in the carrots and raisins.
Spoon the batter into muffin cups that have been lined with muffin papers.
Bake for 15 to 17 minutes.
Yields 24 muffins.

title: cajun spice blend
directions: Mix ingredients in blender or food processor.
Use in sauces, on meats, in marinades and on popcorn.
Can be used as a blacken seasoning for fish or chicken.

title: cheesy vegetable casserole
directions: Cut cheese into cubes; place in pan with 1/4 cup butter.
Heat over medium heat until melted and smooth, stirring often.
Place vegetables in a 1-quart casserole dish.
Pour cheese mixture over and mix well.
Melt remaining butter; stir in cracker crumbs; sprinkle over top of casserole.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat well in about 1 tablespoon oil in Dutch oven.
Pour off excess fat.
Add water, onion, cabbage and seasonings.
Bring to boil over low heat.
Turn down and simmer about 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add raw vegetables and cook 45 minutes longer over medium-low heat.
Add tomatoes and V-8 juice.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer about 15 minutes more.
Remove meat and cut into pieces of edible size and return to kettle.

title: nila's jelly pastries
directions: Sift flour and salt on wax paper.
Cream butter with cream cheese and sour cream in medium bowl until fluffy and light.
Stir in flour.
Mix until blended, then knead.
Mix in bowl until smooth.
Cover.
Chill several hours until firm enough to roll.

title: chip casserole
directions: Break up chips; put into a baking dish.
Fry hamburger meat with onions, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Pour over chips. Add soup to mixture and pour over chips; top with cheese.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine margarine, flour and pecans; mix well.
Press into oblong glass baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip; blend thoroughly.
Spread over crust and chill. Combine pudding mixes and milk; beat 2 minutes.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding; sprinkle with pecans.

title: rosemary sugar snap peas
directions: Combine all ingredients in a nonstick pan.
Stir-fry until peas are crisp-tender, about 10 minutes.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Brown wings in butter and garlic.
When wings are almost brown, remove garlic and fry wings until they are completely browned on all sides; set aside.

title: bean salad
directions: Marinate vegetables in ingredients listed several hours or a few days prior to serving.
Keeps well for weeks.

title: seafoam
directions: Beat egg whites and salt at speed 8 for 3 minutes in large bowl.
Boil sugar, corn syrup and water together until it forms a hard ball.
Pour syrup slowly into beaten whites while beating at speed 8.
Continue beating until mix passes glossy stage.
Add nuts and vanilla and continue beating until mix forms a peak. Pour on buttered platter or drop on waxed paper.

title: pink panther salad
directions: Dice apples
in small cubes;
drain pineapple well. Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate for several hours.

title: cheesy beef rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix first 9 ingredients (5 cups mixture).
Split rolls in half lengthwise.
Spread cut sides of each half with heaping 3/4 cup meat mixture.
Place on foil-lined baking sheet.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings, about 630 calories each.

title: apple and bleu cheese appetizer
directions: Stretch dough out to fit your pizza pan.
Lightly brush with olive oil.
Arrange apple slices over dough.
Sprinkle bleu cheese over pizza.
Sprinkle black pepper and thyme to taste.
Bake in 350 degree oven until done.

title: corn pudding
directions: Blend half a bag of corn in blender until pureed. Add remaining ingredients, except corn. Stir in remaining corn. Pour in greased casserole dish and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into graham cracker pie crust. Refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Break into small pieces and layer bottom of 13x9 cake pan.
Mix soups together, spread over chicken. Make stove top stuffing as directed on the box, then spread over top of the layer of soup.
Bake at 350 for 20 minutes.

title: onion-chicken
directions: Place chicken in a greased 9-inch square dish.
Arrange potatoes around chicken.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken and potatoes.
Bake uncovered at 350° for one hour and 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with onions and cook 10 more minutes.

title: spring cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
This will be a thin layer.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix softened cream cheese, peanut butter, milk and 10x sugar. Add Cool Whip and pour mixture into graham cracker crust.
Freeze. Thaw 1/2 hour before serving.

title: raisin oatmeal bread
directions: Soften the oatmeal in boiling water.
Let sit for 1/2 hour. Add butter, honey, raisins, cinnamon and salt.
Soften yeast in warm water.
Add to oatmeal mixture.
Add 2 cups flour and beat. Add 2 more cups flour and then knead in last 2 cups flour.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch down and shape into 2 loaves.
Let rise and bake for 45 minutes in a preheated 325° oven.
Can easily be frozen and reheated.
Great toasted for breakfast!

title: filled cookies
directions: Note:
When the batter gets hard to mix with a mixer, stir in remaining flour.

title: pork loin roast
directions: Place loin in pan, then place all vegetables around the roast. Spread bay leaf on top of meat. Bake, covered, at 325° until tender.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: You must get all items ready, as once you start mixing the cake, it must be finished fairly quick!
Preheat the oven to 350° and grease a 9 x 12-inch pan.
