Make the pudding on the stove in a large pan.
When the pudding begins to thicken, add the cake mix. Blend quickly and turn the mixture into the cake pan.
Top with the chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let cheese and sausage set out until room temperature.
Add Bisquick.
Mix; knead with hands and roll into balls.
Bake at 350° until brown on top, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hershey chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar
in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend
well.
Combine
flour,
cocoa, baking soda and salt; blend into creamed
mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie
sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 9 minutes.
(Do not
overbake!)
Cool on cookie sheet until set, about 1 minute.
Yields 4 1/2 dozen.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, coconut and baking soda. Roll into balls and press or crisscross with fork dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: wedding punch
directions: Make a syrup from the 6 cups of water and 4 pounds of sugar. Mix together with the rest of the ingredients, except ginger ale. When ready to serve, add the ginger ale. Red food coloring may also be added. This will serve about 50.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
broccoli,
pour in casserole dish.
Combine mushroom soup, milk and pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese. Combine Bisquick
and
margarine
until crumbly;
sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: pickled okra
directions: Trim the tough stems from the okra.
Pack okra into 4 pint jars (sterilize the jars before use).
Add 1 tablespoon of dill and 1 clove garlic to each jar.
Bring to a boil the vinegar, water and salt.
Pour over okra and seal the jars in a water bath. Let ripen for 3 weeks at least.
Serve cold.

title: ziti bake for eight
directions: Prepare ziti according to directions.
Drain and set aside. Cook beef for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir into Ricotta cheese, the next 5 ingredients and 1/2 of sauce until well mixed. Add ziti and toss gently to coat well.
Spoon mixture into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Pour remaining sauce evenly over ziti mixture. Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: dish of dirt
directions: In each of 4 dessert dishes, place 2 tablespoons cookie crumbs.
Top each with 1/2 cup ice cream, remaining 2 tablespoons cookie crumbs and 1 tablespoon syrup.
Garnish with gummy worms and whipped topping.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken breasts, uncovered, for 30 minutes; set aside. Combine in large bowl the cabbage, carrots, chopped red pepper, water chestnuts, chopped green onions, almonds, sesame seed and Top Ramen noodles, crunched up into bite size pieces.
Cut up chicken breasts into 1/2-inch pieces; add to cabbage mixture.
In small bowl, combine vinegar, sugar, oil, Top Ramen seasoning packets and soy sauce; stir until well blended.
Pour over cabbage mixture; toss to coat.
May prepare same day or refrigerate overnight. Makes 12 (1-cup) servings.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Stir melted Hershey bars into Cool Whip whipped topping. Mix until well blended. Spread mixture into pie crust. Refrigerate until firm.

title: linguini and shrimp
directions: Clean and de-vein shrimp then butterfly them and set aside.
In a frying pan pour oil (enough to cover bottom of pan).
Add chopped garlic, dried red peppers then saut for about 2 minutes.
Add wine, shrimp, and knife tip of anchovy paste and saut 2 more minutes Remove from heat and sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Serve over linguini noodles.
Best served with red wine.

title: mexican lasagna(don't cook anything first!)
directions: Combine beef, beans, oregano and garlic powder.
Place 4 noodles in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 mixture over noodles.
Top with 4 more noodles and remaining mixture.
Cover with 4 more noodles.
Combine water and salsa; pour over all. Cover tight with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: kathy's too-easy fudge
directions: Make sure all utensils are completely dry.

(Moisture will cause hard spots in the coating.) Melt block of candy coating in a double boiler or microwave, stirring occasionally and remove from heat when almost melted. Stir until completely melted.
Thoroughly stir in can of frosting and add any additional ingredients desired - nuts, marshmallow.
Pour into 8 x 8 pan lined with wax paper.
Let cool. Cut. Enjoy.

title: instant russian tea mix
directions: Mix all together.
Use 2 tablespoons mix in cup of hot water. Good on cold winter day!

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Simmer for 1 hour.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Put apples in pineapple juice.
Drain apples (save juice). To the juice, add sugar, eggs, flour and vinegar.
Cook until thick; cool.
Add cooked mixture, pineapple and nuts to apples. Add Cool Whip.
Garnish with chopped nuts.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together and spread in the pan.
Sprinkle a little paprika and parsley flakes on top for color.
Bake for approximately 25 minutes.
Cut into pieces.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: old-fashioned coal flower
directions: Place coal in a glass dish.
Pour water, salt, bluing, ammonia and food coloring over coal.
Crystals will form within 24 hours.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and cherry fruit filling. Mix until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 34 to 40 minutes, or until cake springs back when lightly touched.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil and cook for 10 minutes. Add Certo.
Bring back to a boil and cook 1 minute.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Take off foam.
Pour into glasses and seal with wax or caps.

title: sunday round roast
directions: Salt and pepper roast on both sides.
Mix remainder of salt and pepper with flour.
Dredge roast on both sides.
Melt fat in roaster or iron skillet.
Sear roast to a medium brown on both sides to hold juices in meat.
Turn heat down.
Add 2 cups of hot water.
Add onions and cook for 1 hour with cover.
Add tomatoes and salt to taste.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon bits on top.

title: hot sausage - bean dip
directions: In skillet break sausage into small pieces. Cook slowly until browned, about 10 minutes. Drain off fat. In blender, combine cooked sausage, beans, shredded cheese, catsup, mustard and hot pepper sauce. Blend until smooth, stopping occasionally to scrape down sides of blender.

title: quick party punch
directions: Chill 3 cans of Punch and 1 can of juice in refrigerator until ready.
Mix Punch and juice in punch bowl.
Scoop out frozen Punch and stir in.
This will keep it cold.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: pickled mushrooms
directions: In tightly covered jar, shake dressing mix, vinegar and water. Add salad oil, sugar, garlic and red pepper sauce; shake to mix. Stir in onion rings and mushrooms.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours.

title: flour tortillas
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt together.
Mix in the shortening.
Add hot water.
Mix until dough sticks together. Add flour, a little at a time, to knead.

title: cheese dip
directions: Put all ingredients in a slow cooker for 1 hour.
Serve with chips.

title: lazy wife's pie
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar and milk.
Melt the margarine in pan in oven.
Place fruit in pan with margarine.
Pour the mixture over the fruit.
Bake in 375° oven until brown.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Crush graham crackers finely and place in 11 x 7-inch pan, covering the bottom 1/4-inch thick.
Add enough melted margarine to cause graham crackers to hold together, stirring well with fork.
Press firmly in pan and place in freezer to set while preparing filling.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender. Drain and mix other ingredients in casserole dish.
Top with crackers. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato preserves
directions: Boil tomatoes and sugar for 20 minutes.
Remove from stove and add Jell-O.
Stir well.
Put in jelly glasses.

title: lemon bisk jello
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and sugar.
Let it thicken until like syrup.
Fold in the whipped canned milk, rind and juice of lemon.
Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with either vanilla wafer crumbs or graham cracker crumbs.
Pour mixture on top of crumbs; sprinkle top with crumbs.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Follow directions for cake mix.
Mix Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut together.
While cake is hot, make holes all in it. Pour milk and cream over top.
Let cool.
Mix Cool Whip and coconut.
Put on cake.

title: tallerine
directions: In 12 x 18 baking pan layer noodles, cottage cheese, sauce and Mozzarella. Repeat, ending with noodles, sauce, Mozzarella cheese.
Sprinkle 1 Tbsp. parsley and 1/2 tsp. ground oregano on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. It might take a little longer. Sauce can be made days ahead and frozen if necessary to keep. Lasagna can be cooled day before needed and re-heated.
It is usually better re-heated.
Can freeze any left over.

title: old-fashioned banana pudding
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Gradually add flour alternately with milk.
Stir constantly until mixture thickens.
Pour over bananas and vanilla wafers.
Stir mixture together.
Let set until ready to serve (large recipe).

title: coconut pie(no crust)
directions: Mix and pour into pie plate.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.
Makes 1 pie.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Mix Crisco into flour mixture.
Mix egg and vinegar together and add to flour mixture.
Add water; refrigerate at least 5 minutes.
Makes 3 crusts.

title: cole slaw
directions: Chop cabbage.
Add sugar and small amount of vinegar to taste. Add pinch of salt.
Small amount of milk added last.

title: cheese spaghetti
directions: Brown ground chuck; drain grease.
Add onions and bell peppers.
Add soups and can of water.
Simmer for 30 to 45 minutes until thickened.
Add olives and Velveeta.
Cook on low until Velveeta is melted.
Add cooked spaghetti.

title: three cheese chicken enchiladas
directions: Place tortillas on baking sheet; place in a 350° oven for about 5 minutes.
In large bowl, stir together the sour cream and cream cheese until smooth.
Stir in salt, cumin, pepper, chicken, 1 cup Jack cheese, Cheddar cheese and green onions.
Place 1/2 cup mix in center of each tortilla.
Fold 2 edges of tortilla to overlap in center.
Place, seal side down, in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan; bake for 15 minutes.
Pour salsa over enchiladas; bake for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining 1 cup Jack cheese over salsa.
Return to oven for 1 to 2 minutes.

title: tortellini soup
directions: In a large pot, heat oil until hot.
Add leeks and saute 5 minutes.
Add carrots and celery.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Add tomatoes and liquid; simmer 10 minutes.

title: veggie chili
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and zucchini in oil in medium stock pan until tender. Add beans, tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Mix well. Add spices.
Mix well again.
Add water.
Bring mixture to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve topped with low-fat sharp Cheddar cheese.
Makes about 8 to 10 (1 cup) servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheeses stand until soft.
Add onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix with electric mixer until fluffy.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Shape into ball.
Roll into parsley and chill.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding with 3 cups of juice from canned fruit, adding water to make the 3 cups.
Cool and add fruit.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: mama martz cheese souffle
directions: Layer half of bread and half of cheese in 1 1/2-quart casserole, greased.
Repeat layers, ending in cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt, mustard and pepper in blender.
Blend well and pour over bread and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix together water and yeast, then add sugar, salt, shortening and egg.

I use mixer for this, then add a couple cups of flour and continue to use mixer, then just keep adding flour and mix by hand. After you can handle the dough easily, you have enough flour. Place dough in large bowl and cover with damp towel; keep moistening towel as it dries.
Let rise overnight.
Roll dough into balls small enough to fit 3 in each muffin cup.
Let raise at 85° until double in size.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: green bean casserole(prep time:  10 minutes.  cook time:  30 minutes.  feeds 8.)
directions: In 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and dash of pepper.
Stir in beans and 1/2 can of onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Stir; top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pistachio pudding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed with electric mixer for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Remove and finish cooling on racks.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper.
Brown hamburger meat; drain off grease.
Add onion and pepper to meat and cook together for 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.
Mix other ingredients together in a large pie plate.
Add meat mixture.
Stir altogether.
Cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gremolata bruschetta
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cut 12 (1/2-inch) slices from bread; set aside.
In bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Spread mixture over bread slices.
Arrange in single layer on cookie sheet.
Bake for about 15 minutes, until bread is golden brown.
Makes 12.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; place in 2 pie shells.
Use 2 remaining pie shells for top, sealing edges.
Cut 6 small slits in crusts to prevent boiling over.
Bake for 40 minutes at 375°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: spanish rice(use microwave)
directions: Fry bacon in same casserole that you'll use and crumble into pieces.
Place all ingredients in dish.
Stir to mix.
Cook 8 minutes on High power to microwave.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Blend together Bisquick, eggs and oil.
Add Italian seasoning, garlic and cheese.
Stir in sliced zucchini and onions.
Dump mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Test to make sure it is cooked through.

title: spicy pumpkin loaf
directions: Cream the sugar and oil in a bowl. Add eggs and pumpkin.
Mix well. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with 2/3 cup water, mixing well after each addition. Stir in pecans.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until loaves test done. Remove from pans to cool.

title: carrot and cheese mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool.
Add orange or lemon juice to cream cheese and cream until smooth.
Add carrot, sugar, salt, pepper and parsley to cream cheese.
Gradually add cooled gelatin and pour mixture into a mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce leaves.
Serve with mayonnaise or salad dressing.

title: chili meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Pour chili into a large mixing bowl. Stir in the eggs.
Add the onion, green pepper, salt and meat broken into pieces.
Tilt the bowl and cut through the mixture with a fork until blended.
Tender mixing makes tender meat loaf.
Shape into loaf and turn out into a greased shallow pan; smooth into shape.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Use tight fitting pan with cover or use foil.
Pour rice in bottom of pan or dish.
Sprinkle chicken pieces with sage, salt and pepper.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Mix together and pour over chicken water and mushroom soup.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Slice and boil carrots until tender and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill in refrigerator overnight before serving.

title: barbecued beef(great way to use leftover, cold roast beef)
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, mustard, lemon juice, salt, paprika, pepper, cold water, butter, onion slices and green pepper. Simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Add catsup and beef. Refrigerate.

title: stuffed mushroom caps
directions: Microwave bacon until crisp.
Clean, dry and carefully remove stems (use stems for soups, sauces, etc.).
Stuff mushrooms with mixture of ingredients above.
Do not heap mixture on mushrooms as it will melt and be lost.
Arrange about 12 mushrooms (as uniform in size as possible) in a circle on plate.
Microwave on Roast about 2 1/2 minutes or until heated through.

title: wassail
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven, heat water, cinnamon sticks and cloves to boiling.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Cover and let steep for 10 minutes.
Remove tea bags and spices.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: creamy frosting
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar.
Add flour, one tablespoon at a time, milk and vanilla.
Beat 15 to 20 minutes until sugar dissolves.

title: honey baked goose
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Clean and cut onions, carrots and potatoes into bite size pieces.
Pour one cup of melted bacon grease into bottom of large casserole dish.
Cook carrots and potatoes in microwave oven for five minutes on High.

title: blueberry icebox cake
directions: Cut cake into 3 or 4 layers.
Whip Dream Whip according to directions on the package.
Add granulated sugar, powdered sugar and cream cheese; mix well and whip.
Put between the layers and on top of the cake.
Put in refrigerator and chill, then pour blueberries over the top of the cake.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Keeps well in refrigerator.
Strawberry or cherry topping may be substituted for blueberry.

title: super patties
directions: Mix by hand all ingredients except the fine bread crumbs and oil.
Shape into 6 patties, 1/2 to 1 inch thick.
Coat in bread crumbs and fry in oil over medium heat until brown on both sides and cooked through.

title: strawberry jello pie
directions: In large bowl, dissolve jello with boiling water; when completely dissolved, add frozen strawberries.
Mix well and put in refrigerator until partially set.
Take out and add Cool Whip. Mix well and pour into pie crust.
Put back into refrigerator until completely set.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender and drain.
Add rice, soup and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Combine all ingredients except chips and chill the mixture until firm.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Dip these balls into melted chocolate or butterscotch chips and let harden on waxed paper.

title: strata
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Place cubed bread in bottom of pan and top with cheese.
Brown sausage; drain and place on top of cheese.
Beat eggs with milk; add mustard.
Pour over meat. Refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, dilute soup with milk.
Pour over all ingredients.
Bake at 300° for almost 2 hours.

title: peppermint white chocolate candy
directions: Crush candy in food processor.
Melt chocolate in double boiler, stirring constantly.
Add candy.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet.
Chill until set.
Break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.
Can use lemon drops or spearmint pieces.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan.
While hot, punch holes all over cake and pour hot mixture of cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk.
Let cool completely and spread Cool Whip over cake.
Top with coconut.

title: aros caldo
directions: In a large pot or wok, saute garlic, onions and ginger root. Brown chicken (skin removed, if desired).
Add rice and 12 cups water.
Season with patis or fish sauce.
Cook until rice is done; it will be soupy.

title: almond cookies
directions: Combine the eggs and sugar and mix it in a bowl.
Add the flour and mix.
Melt the butter (let it be a little burnt) and add.
Add the almond slices.
Mix well and let it cool in the refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Thinly spread 1 tablespoon each of the dough on a cookie plate.
Bake for 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: oreo dessert
directions: Crumble Oreos in bottom of cake pan.
Slice ice cream and layer on top of cookies.
Pour fudge over this and top with Cool Whip and freeze.
Take out when ready to eat.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat with chopped onion.
Add spaghetti sauce and mushroom steak sauce.
Add eggs and grated yellow cheese.
Simmer. Add rosemary.
Cook noodles according to package directions. Grate Jack and Tillamook cheeses and mix with cottage cheese. Layer in baking dish or pan.
Start with noodles, meat mixture, then cheese mixture (save some for top).
Alternate until pan is 1/4-inch from top.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until bubbles around sides.
Makes large amount; extra can be frozen.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: crab stuffed shrimp
directions: Mix crab meat, cracker crumbs, season salt, lite dressing and egg white in bowl until the mixture has consistency of potato salad.
Into the split side of each shrimp put 1 Tbsp. of mixture, molding the shrimp around the stuffing.
Brush with butter and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in a pie tin at 400° for approximately 10 minutes or until shrimp have turned white.

title: chick-a-dorf salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Chill while covered.
Serve on bed of lettuce.
Serves 4.

title: modern swedish dream potatoes
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add onion and fries.
Cook stirring constantly until potatoes are hot.
Remove from heat and add cereal, cheese, salt and pepper; mix well.
Put into a shallow buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine sour cream and eggs; pour over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: Cream the margarine and brown sugar. Add flour and nuts to make a crumb mixture.
Reserve 1 cup of topping.
Press remainder of mixture into bottom of an 8-inch square, ungreased pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin butter
directions: In a large saucepan, combine pumpkin, pumpkin pie spice and pectin; mix well.
Stirring constantly, bring mixture to a boil. Quickly add the sugar.
When the mixture returns to a boil, cook for 1minute.
Remove from heat; skim off any foam.
Ladle hot into jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust lids.
Process in a boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
Yield: about 3 pints.

title: peachy orange cake
directions: Mix with fork and spread into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: potato kugel
directions: Saute onion in oil until tender.
Remove from heat.
Working quickly, finely grate potatoes.
Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Pour into greased shallow 1 1/2 quart dish.
Bake at 400° one hour or until golden and crusty.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cucumber cream sauce
directions: Peel and seed cucumber.
Grate enough cucumber to measure 1/2 cup.
Combine grated cucumber with remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Cover and chill.

title: crab soup
directions: Cook and simmer all ingredients except crabmeat and vegetables for 2 hours.
Add crabmeat.
Continue to cook and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add vegetables and cook until they are done.

title: carnival casserole
directions: Heat olive oil and add onions and green peppers. Cook until tender. Add ground beef and cook until brown. Pour out 1/4 cup of liquid from can of tomatoes and save. Add tomatoes, syrup and seasonings. Bring to boil; cover and simmer for 15 minutes. Find and remove bay leaf from mixture.

title: stuffed baked potatoes(microwave)
directions: Microwave potatoes until done.
Allow potatoes to stand at room temperature for 2 to 3 minutes after baking.
Cut a thin slice from the top of each potato.
Caution, potato will be hot.
With spoon, remove the potato pulp from each potato, leaving a thin shell.

title: angel hair pasta and chicken in parmesan cheese
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
Add sauce pack and chicken to pasta and serve.
Simple and delicious.

title: chicken delight
directions: Mix all ingredients, except butter and corn flakes.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Mix corn flakes with melted butter. Spread on top and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: apple batter pudding
directions: Slice apples in a pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Pour batter over apples.
Bake at 350° until done.
Serve with ice cream.
Add sugar to apples to taste if serving without ice cream.

title: banana nut loaf
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 315 to 350° until done, about 1 hour.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Bring butter, sugar and milk to a full, rolling boil in saucepan, stirring constantly.
Boil until it gets to soft ball stage or boil 5 minutes over medium heat.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan; let cool and cut.

title: key lime pie
directions: Fold juice into condensed milk.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture. Pour into crusts.
Sprinkle crumbs on top and refrigerate before serving.

title: creamy coconut icing
directions: Soften cream cheese and margarine.
Mix together.
Add sugar, then coconut and pecans.
Will frost a 2 layer cake or 9 x 13-inch sheet cake.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese and chives to taste.
Add 4 to 5 shakes Accent and 4 to 5 shakes Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Roll in chipped beef.
Serve with crackers.

title: coca-cola cake with frosting
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs and mix well.
Mix together flour, salt, baking soda in small bowl.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk to creamed sugar and butter mixture. Blend at low speed to blend and then on medium speed for 1 minute. Add cola and marshmallows.
Blend well.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool about 1/2 hour, then frost.

title: stingy cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add dry ingredients, flavoring, 1 egg and 1 yolk.
Spread batter in a greased square pan.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Beat egg white; spread on top.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons brown sugar over the top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crispy bacon coleslaw
directions: All of the measurements are on the "generous" side.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In bowl, blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons of margarine until smooth.
Add next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles; firmly pressing perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup of meat mixture onto center of each rectangle.
Pull 4 corners of dough to the top and seal. Brush tops with the remaining 1 tablespoon margarine.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix well and shape into balls the size of a walnut.

title: esther's potato salad
directions: Boil small potatoes; peel and slice into bowl when cooled. Fry or microwave bacon until crisp; measure slightly less than 1/2 cup and add this to 1 1/2 cups water, vinegar and sugar, plus salt and pepper to taste.
Boil vigorously for more than 5 minutes (can be microwaved).

title: easy fudge frosting
directions: Boil together (full rolling boil) for 1 minute, then add 1 teaspoon vanilla, beating with spoon until thick.
Pour on cake.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef; add onion, celery, green pepper and sauces. Cook macaroni and add to soup.
Simmer approximately 15 minutes.

title: ham, cabbage and noodles
directions: In extra large skillet melt margarine; add onions and saute. Add ham, cabbage and water.
Simmer till cabbage is crispy tender. Add cooked drained noodles, salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer to combine flavors about 10 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Cabbage is best crispy.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sunshine blueberry loaf
directions: Combine margarine and sugar.
Blend in eggs and lemon rind. Add combined dry ingredients alternately with orange juice, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in blueberries and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 15 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes; remove from pan.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix hash browns, soup, garlic salt, sour cream and cheese together and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and pour over potatoes.
Crumble potato chips over top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: aunt irene's noodles
directions: The thinner the egg noodles the better.
Cook the noodles according to directions being sure to add enough salt to the water.
Do not overcook these noodles; be sure they are "dente". Place in a large casserole dish.
Add the two sticks of butter. Add the sour cream and the poppy seeds.
Season again with salt and a lot of pepper.

title: nifty carrots(even good for your hearing!)
directions: Place cooked carrots in a shallow casserole.
Combine next 6 ingredients and pour over carrots. Combine butter and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over top. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: smooth hot cheese dip
directions: *Can substitute chili peppers for jalapeno peppers.

title: cheese and chilies on rye
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add enough mayonnaise to spread on rye bread.
Broil until golden brown.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until peak forms.
Gradually beat in sugar, vinegar and vanilla.
Continue beating until very stiff. Fold in pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a greased baking sheet. Bake at 300° for 15 or 20 minutes or until firm.
You may add food colorings for different seasons of the year.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream sugar, cocoa and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour, coconut and pecans.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.
When done, spread jar of Marshmallow Creme on hot cake.
Cool, then frost.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Make cake layers and cool completely.
Prepare instant pudding according to the package.
Refrigerate to set up.
Place 1 cake layer in the bottom of 6-quart punch bowl.
Add in layers 1/2 of ingredients in the following order: pudding, cherry pie filling, fruit cocktail, pineapple, coconut, nuts and topping.
Add the second cake layer and continue in same order using remainder of ingredients.
Garnish top with cherries, nuts or more coconut. Refrigerate.
Makes 35 servings.
When serving, spoon down side to at least first cake layer to get some of all ingredients.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease a medium size pizza pan.
Mix first 5 ingredients and spread on pizza pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°; remove and allow to cool.
Cream the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and nondairy whipped topping.
Spread on cooled crust.
Arrange fruit on top.
Drain the pineapple really well.
Refrigerate.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: south of the border
directions: Cook ground beef and onion together; drain.
Put ground beef mixture in baking dish, then add green chilis and Cheddar cheese soup.
Mix together egg, flour, milk and salt.
Pour over ground beef mixture and bake at 350° until top is brown.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Cut chicken into large chunks.
Wash, dry and bread.
Fry 5 minutes on each side on low heat.
Pour in bouillon cube, lemon juice, wine, lemon slices and flour. Cook for 10 to 15 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour, eggs, margarine and vanilla well.
Stir in chocolate chips, pecans and coconut.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Put into 9 x 13-inch cake pan (this will be thick).
Pat mixture up sides of pan.
Mix last three ingredients.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cool, cut into small pieces.

title: beef quiche
directions: Brown beef, onions and peppers.
Beat eggs; add milk, then mayonnaise, cornstarch and cheese.
Drain beef mixture; add to egg mixture and stir.
Pour in pie shell and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashioned candied potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Peel and slice sweet potatoes into 1 1/2-inch thick slices. Cook and drain. Arrange potatoes in buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Combine all other ingredients; boil for 5 minutes. Pour over potatoes. Bake 50 minutes, basting occasionally.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain off fat.
Add other ingredients and simmer 45 to 60 minutes.
Add water if needed.
Can simmer a long time, like chili.
Crock-pot works great!

title: boyfriend cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars and butter.
Add eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Add flour and baking soda.
Fold in oatmeal and chips.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Lightly brown ground beef, onion and garlic in frying pan. Pour off excess dripping.
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, Parmesan cheese, Italian seasoning and salt and pepper.
Cook slowly, covered, 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Mix cottage cheese and nutmeg.
Spread 1 cup of meat sauce on bottom of 13 x 9-inch dish.
Then add noodles, meat sauce, cottage cheese spiced, noodles, meat sauce, Mozzarella sauce, noodles and rest of meat sauce.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo in saucepan.
Mix corn, cornbread mix and eggs. Pour into buttered dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix milk and sugar, add one stick melted margarine. Mix yeast and warm water, add to other mixture.

Add flour and mix well. Knead and place in a warm place to rise. When double in size, roll out and cut in diamond shape pieces. Dip in other stick of melted margarine and place in tube pan overlapping.
Let rise till double again or about 1 1/2 hours. Bake at 350° for 35-45 minutes.

title: diggety squares
directions: Melt butter or margarine in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients and add to pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Cut in squares.

title: graham cracker pie crust
directions: Microwave butter on High for about 45 seconds to melt.
Stir in crumbs and brown sugar.
Press mixture against bottom and sides of pie plate.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes a 9-inch pie crust.
Use a 9-inch glass pie plate.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In saucepan, bring water to a boil; stir in onion-mushroom recipe soup mix.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, blended with cream and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring just to the boiling point, then simmer, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened, about 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese until melted.
In a 2-quart casserole, arrange broccoli; top with cheese sauce, then bread crumbs and butter pats.
Bake for 15 minutes, or until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix the cream cheese, butter, sugar and Cool Whip well.
Mix the pudding, milk and vanilla well.
Mix both mixtures together.

title: pennsylvania dutch squirrel or ham pot pie
directions: Roast squirrels or ham (save broth); pick meat and discard bones.
In an 8-quart stew pot, add meat, broth, potatoes and onion.
Fill 1/2 full with water.
Bring to boil.
While bringing to boil, prepare dough.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Drop one at a time into boiling pot.
Simmer, uncovered, until fully cooked.

title: sassy chicken salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine tomatoes, mayonnaise and honey.
Stir chicken, celery, grapes and pecans.
Cover and chill.
May be served in hollowed out melons, avocados or papayas.
Serves 6.

title: fudge cake
directions: Melt
butter.
Mix
all
ingredients together well with mixer. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: grandma kate's sugar cookies
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together with electric mixer until smooth.
Add flour and cream of tartar.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Top with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chinese cabbage salad
directions: Toss cabbage, noodles, green onions and almonds in a bowl. Mix oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and Accent together and pour over salad just before serving.

title: angel food cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift cake flour and 3/4 cup sugar, 4 times.
In a large bowl, beat egg whites, cream of tartar, salt and vanilla until stiff enough to hold soft peaks.
Add remaining sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating after each addition. Continue beating until meringue holds stiff peaks.
Sift about 1/4 of flour mixture over egg whites mixture.
Fold in gently with spatula.
Fold in remaining flour by fourths.
Carefully pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes until top springs back. Cool completely with pan inverted upside down.

title: zesty ripe olive dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, cover and let stand for 1 hour. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix pumpkin, milk, salt, sugar, eggs and spice.
Mix well and pour in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over the pumpkin mixture.
Pour melted margarine over that, evenly. Sprinkle chopped nuts on top.
Bake at 325° about an hour and 15 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.
Serve Cool Whip, if desired.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Heat tomatoes and butter in saucepan over moderate heat, just until butter melts. Mix in bread crumbs, sugar, salt and pepper. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cookies without sugar, butter or eggs
directions: Mix and drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 48 cookies for about 25 cents.

title: mocha mix
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
To serve, spoon 1 to 2 tablespoons mix and 3/4 cup boiling water together. Can garnish with whipped cream.

title: laurine's waldorf salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten well.
Mix good.
Put plastic wrap over bowl and serve on a lettuce leaf.

title: shrimp pilau
directions: In small bowl, combine vinegar, paprika, chili pepper, oregano, cumin, thyme, salt, garlic and water.
Place fish in shallow bowl with bay leaf.
Pour marinade over; leave for several hours at room temperature.
Stir occasionally.
Drain fish on paper towel.
Sprinkle with salt; dust with flour.
Heat oil (at least 1/2-inch deep).
Fry until golden brown.
Keep warm in oven at 200°.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender, combine soup and sour cream. Stir in carrots, squash and onions. Mix stuffing and butter. Spread half of stuffing in baking dish. Pour squash mixture over stuffing. Top with rest of stuffing mix. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken(cousin patty's)
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Lay raw chicken in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs and salad oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat. Stir in vanilla, crushed pineapple (and juice), bananas, and 1 cup of nuts.
Mix well.
Use either three 9-inch pans or tube, or bundt pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes, or until done.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely before icing.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix pineapple, eggs, sugar, flour and salt.
Melt butter and soak bread in butter.
Put bread on top.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: tangy short ribs
directions: In large skillet, heat margarine.
Roll beef ribs in flour to coat.
Brown all sides of ribs.
Remove to baking pan.
Keep drippings in skillet.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until tender.
Meanwhile, about 15 minutes before meat is done, add 4 tablespoons flour, salt and pepper to remaining drippings in skillet.
Stir to blend.
Stir in beef broth and cook over medium heat until thickened (about 3 to 5 minutes).
Add lemon juice, mustard and dill weed.
Bring back to boil.
Remove excess fats from baking pan and add sauce to ribs and keep hot.
Serve with egg noodles.

title: pluck-it bread
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.
Place one can of "cut-up" biscuits in a Bundt pan.
Pour 1/3 of the sugar mixture over biscuits.
Repeat procedure with each can. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and then turn out.

title: ken's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Place in loaf pan or casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: zucchini bread #1
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Sift together rest of ingredients.
Add to first mixture; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured bread tins.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in Dutch oven; cook over low heat until candy thermometer registers 300°.
Remove from heat; stir in soda, water and vanilla.
Spread mixture onto a warm buttered 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Allow peanut brittle to cool; break into pieces.
Yields about 2 pounds.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together and stir with a spoon.
Put the rest of the ingredients in your mixer, one at a time.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: fruit punch
directions: Chill white grape juice and ginger ale until very cold.
Pour into a punch bowl together to mix.
Ice rings may be made from another recipe of punch, adding fresh berries and fresh mint leaves.
Freeze until firm.
Unmold and add to punch at serving time.
This is a light and refreshing punch.

title: basic microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix together ingredients and seasonings.
Mold into a rounded loaf.
Spread 2 tablespoons additional ketchup over top of loaf. Cover loosely with plastic wrap.
Microwave at Medium-High (7) for 25 to 30
minutes.
When oven signals, remove meat loaf and let stand about 10 minutes to firm before serving.
